32 enum {
33 SIZE_ARR_NORM = 8

36 CFEM_DG_NSSolver::CFEM_DG_NSSolver() : CFEM_DG_EulerSolver() {
37 
38  /*--- Basic array initialization ---*/
39  CD_Visc = nullptr; CL_Visc = nullptr; CSF_Visc = nullptr; CEff_Visc = nullptr;
40  CMx_Visc = nullptr; CMy_Visc = nullptr; CMz_Visc = nullptr;
41  CFx_Visc = nullptr; CFy_Visc = nullptr; CFz_Visc = nullptr;
42 
43  /*--- Surface-based array initialization ---*/
44  Surface_CL_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CD_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CSF_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CEff_Visc = nullptr;
45  Surface_CFx_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CFy_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CFz_Visc = nullptr;
46  Surface_CMx_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CMy_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CMz_Visc = nullptr;
47  MaxHeatFlux_Visc = nullptr; Heat_Visc = nullptr;
48 
49  /*--- Set the SGS model to NULL and indicate that no SGS model is used. ---*/
50  SGSModel = nullptr;
51  SGSModelUsed = false;
52 }
53 
54 CFEM_DG_NSSolver::CFEM_DG_NSSolver(CGeometry *geometry, CConfig *config, unsigned short iMesh)
55  : CFEM_DG_EulerSolver(geometry, config, iMesh) {
56 
57  /*--- Array initialization ---*/
58  CD_Visc = nullptr; CL_Visc = nullptr; CSF_Visc = nullptr; CEff_Visc = nullptr;
59  CMx_Visc = nullptr; CMy_Visc = nullptr; CMz_Visc = nullptr;
60  CFx_Visc = nullptr; CFy_Visc = nullptr; CFz_Visc = nullptr;
61 
62  Surface_CL_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CD_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CSF_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CEff_Visc = nullptr;
63  Surface_CFx_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CFy_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CFz_Visc = nullptr;
64  Surface_CMx_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CMy_Visc = nullptr; Surface_CMz_Visc = nullptr;
65  MaxHeatFlux_Visc = nullptr; Heat_Visc = nullptr;
66 
67  /*--- Initialize the solution and right hand side vectors for storing
68  the residuals and updating the solution (always needed even for
69  explicit schemes). ---*/
70 
71  //LinSysSol.Initialize(nPoint, nPointDomain, nVar, 0.0);
72  //LinSysRes.Initialize(nPoint, nPointDomain, nVar, 0.0);
73 
74  /*--- Non dimensional coefficients ---*/
75  CD_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
76  CL_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
77  CSF_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
78  CMx_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
79  CMy_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
80  CMz_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
81  CEff_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
82  CFx_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
83  CFy_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
84  CFz_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
85 
86  Surface_CL_Visc = new su2double[config->GetnMarker_Monitoring()];
87  Surface_CD_Visc = new su2double[config->GetnMarker_Monitoring()];
88  Surface_CSF_Visc = new su2double[config->GetnMarker_Monitoring()];
89  Surface_CEff_Visc = new su2double[config->GetnMarker_Monitoring()];
90  Surface_CFx_Visc = new su2double[config->GetnMarker_Monitoring()];
91  Surface_CFy_Visc = new su2double[config->GetnMarker_Monitoring()];
92  Surface_CFz_Visc = new su2double[config->GetnMarker_Monitoring()];
93  Surface_CMx_Visc = new su2double[config->GetnMarker_Monitoring()];
94  Surface_CMy_Visc = new su2double[config->GetnMarker_Monitoring()];
95  Surface_CMz_Visc = new su2double[config->GetnMarker_Monitoring()];
96 
97  Heat_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
98  MaxHeatFlux_Visc = new su2double[nMarker];
99 
100  /*--- Init total coefficients ---*/
101 
102  Total_CD = 0.0; Total_CL = 0.0; Total_CSF = 0.0;
103  Total_CMx = 0.0; Total_CMy = 0.0; Total_CMz = 0.0;
104  Total_CEff = 0.0;
105  Total_CFx = 0.0; Total_CFy = 0.0; Total_CFz = 0.0;
106 
107  /*--- Read farfield conditions from config ---*/
108 
109  Viscosity_Inf = config->GetViscosity_FreeStreamND();
110  Prandtl_Lam = config->GetPrandtl_Lam();
111  Prandtl_Turb = config->GetPrandtl_Turb();
112  Tke_Inf = config->GetTke_FreeStreamND();
113 
114  /*--- Set the SGS model in case an LES simulation is carried out ---*/
115 
116  if(config->GetKind_Solver() == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_LES) {
117 
118  /* Make a distinction between the SGS models used and set SGSModel and
119  SGSModelUsed accordingly. */
120  switch( config->GetKind_SGS_Model() ) {
121 
122  case TURB_SGS_MODEL::IMPLICIT_LES:
123  SGSModel = nullptr;
124  SGSModelUsed = false;
125  break;
126 
127  case TURB_SGS_MODEL::SMAGORINSKY:
128  SGSModel = new CSmagorinskyModel;
129  SGSModelUsed = true;
130  break;
131 
132  case TURB_SGS_MODEL::WALE:
133  SGSModel = new CWALEModel;
134  SGSModelUsed = true;
135  break;
136 
137  case TURB_SGS_MODEL::VREMAN:
138  SGSModel = new CVremanModel;
139  SGSModelUsed = true;
140  break;
141 
142  default:
143  SU2_MPI::Error("Unknown SGS model encountered", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
144  }
145  }
146  else {
147 
148  /* No LES, so no SGS model needed.
149  Set the pointer to NULL and the boolean to false. */
150  SGSModel = nullptr;
151  SGSModelUsed = false;
152  }
153 }
154 
155 CFEM_DG_NSSolver::~CFEM_DG_NSSolver() {
156 
157  delete [] CD_Visc;
158  delete [] CL_Visc;
159  delete [] CSF_Visc;
160  delete [] CMx_Visc;
161  delete [] CMy_Visc;
162  delete [] CMz_Visc;
163  delete [] CFx_Visc;
164  delete [] CFy_Visc;
165  delete [] CFz_Visc;
166  delete [] CEff_Visc;
167 
168  delete [] Surface_CL_Visc;
169  delete [] Surface_CD_Visc;
170  delete [] Surface_CSF_Visc;
171  delete [] Surface_CEff_Visc;
172  delete [] Surface_CFx_Visc;
173  delete [] Surface_CFy_Visc;
174  delete [] Surface_CFz_Visc;
175  delete [] Surface_CMx_Visc;
176  delete [] Surface_CMy_Visc;
177  delete [] Surface_CMz_Visc;
178 
179  delete [] Heat_Visc;
180  delete [] MaxHeatFlux_Visc;
181 
182  delete SGSModel;
183 }
184 
185 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::Friction_Forces(const CGeometry* geometry, const CConfig* config) {
186 
187  /* Allocate the memory for the work array and initialize it to zero to avoid
188  warnings in debug mode about uninitialized memory when padding is applied. */
189  vector<su2double> workArrayVec(sizeWorkArray, 0.0);
190  su2double *workArray = workArrayVec.data();
191 
192  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
193  /*--- The skin friction is computed using the laminar viscosity and ---*/
194  /*--- velocity gradients. This is correct when integration to the wall ---*/
195  /*--- is performed, but not when wall functions are used. Hence, this ---*/
196  /*--- function must be modified when wall functions are implemented. ---*/
197  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
198 
199  /* Determine the number of faces that are treated simultaneously
200  in the matrix products to obtain good gemm performance. */
201  const unsigned short nPadInput = config->GetSizeMatMulPadding();
202  const unsigned short nFaceSimul = nPadInput/nVar;
203 
204  /* Determine the minimum padded size in the matrix multiplications, which
205  corresponds to 64 byte alignment. */
206  const unsigned short nPadMin = 64/sizeof(passivedouble);
207 
208  /* Constant factor present in the heat flux vector. */
209  const su2double factHeatFlux_Lam = Gamma/Prandtl_Lam;
210 
211  /*--- Get the information of the angle of attack, reference area, etc. ---*/
212  const su2double Alpha = config->GetAoA()*PI_NUMBER/180.0;
213  const su2double Beta = config->GetAoS()*PI_NUMBER/180.0;
214  const su2double RefLength = config->GetRefLength();
215  auto Origin = config->GetRefOriginMoment(0);
216 
217  /*--- Evaluate reference values for non-dimensionalization. ---*/
218  const su2double RefHeatFlux = config->GetHeat_Flux_Ref();
219 
220  const su2double factor = 1.0 / AeroCoeffForceRef;
221 
222  /*--- Variables initialization ---*/
223  AllBound_CD_Visc = 0.0; AllBound_CL_Visc = 0.0; AllBound_CSF_Visc = 0.0;
224  AllBound_CMx_Visc = 0.0; AllBound_CMy_Visc = 0.0; AllBound_CMz_Visc = 0.0;
225  AllBound_CFx_Visc = 0.0; AllBound_CFy_Visc = 0.0; AllBound_CFz_Visc = 0.0;
226 
227  AllBound_HeatFlux_Visc = 0.0; AllBound_MaxHeatFlux_Visc = 0.0; AllBound_CEff_Visc = 0.0;
228 
229  for(unsigned short iMarker_Monitoring=0; iMarker_Monitoring<config->GetnMarker_Monitoring(); ++iMarker_Monitoring) {
230  Surface_CL_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] = 0.0; Surface_CD_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] = 0.0;
231  Surface_CSF_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] = 0.0; Surface_CEff_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] = 0.0;
232  Surface_CFx_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] = 0.0; Surface_CFy_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] = 0.0;
233  Surface_CFz_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] = 0.0; Surface_CMx_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] = 0.0;
234  Surface_CMy_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] = 0.0; Surface_CMz_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] = 0.0;
235  }
236 
237  /*--- Loop over the Navier-Stokes markers ---*/
238  for(unsigned short iMarker=0; iMarker<nMarker; ++iMarker) {
239 
240  /* Check if this boundary must be monitored. */
241  const unsigned short Monitoring = config->GetMarker_All_Monitoring(iMarker);
242  if(Monitoring == YES) {
243 
244  /* Easier storage of the boundary condition. */
245  const unsigned short Boundary = config->GetMarker_All_KindBC(iMarker);
246 
247  /*--- Obtain the origin for the moment computation for a particular marker ---*/
248  for(unsigned short iMarker_Monitoring=0; iMarker_Monitoring<config->GetnMarker_Monitoring();
249  ++iMarker_Monitoring) {
250  string Monitoring_Tag = config->GetMarker_Monitoring_TagBound(iMarker_Monitoring);
251  string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker);
252  if (Marker_Tag == Monitoring_Tag)
253  Origin = config->GetRefOriginMoment(iMarker_Monitoring);
254  }
255 
256  /* Check for a boundary for which the viscous forces must be computed. */
257  if((Boundary == HEAT_FLUX) || (Boundary == ISOTHERMAL)) {
258 
259  /*--- Determine the prescribed heat flux or prescribed temperature. ---*/
260  bool HeatFlux_Prescribed = false, Temperature_Prescribed = false;
261  su2double Wall_HeatFlux = 0.0, Wall_Temperature = 0.0;
262 
263  const string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker);
264  if(Boundary == HEAT_FLUX) {
265  HeatFlux_Prescribed = true;
266  Wall_HeatFlux = config->GetWall_HeatFlux(Marker_Tag);
267  }
268  else {
269  Temperature_Prescribed = true;
270  Wall_Temperature = config->GetIsothermal_Temperature(Marker_Tag)
271  / config->GetTemperature_Ref();
272  }
273 
274  /*--- Forces initialization at each Marker ---*/
275  CD_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0; CL_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0; CSF_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0;
276  CMx_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0; CMy_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0; CMz_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0;
277  CFx_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0; CFy_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0; CFz_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0;
278 
279  Heat_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0; MaxHeatFlux_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0; CEff_Visc[iMarker] = 0.0;
280 
281  su2double ForceViscous[] = {0.0, 0.0, 0.0};
282  su2double MomentViscous[] = {0.0, 0.0, 0.0};
283 
284  /* Easier storage of the boundary faces for this boundary marker. */
285  const unsigned long nSurfElem = boundaries[iMarker].surfElem.size();
286  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem = boundaries[iMarker].surfElem.data();
287 
288  /* Check if a wall treatment is used. */
289  if( boundaries[iMarker].wallModel ) {
290 
291  /*--- Wall treatment is used, so the wall shear stress and heat flux
292  are computed using the wall model. As the interpolation of data
293  of the exchange point is different for each element, it is not
294  possible to treat multiple faces simultaneously. So here just
295  a loop over the number of faces is carried out. ---*/
296  for(unsigned long l=0; l<nSurfElem; ++l) {
297 
298  /* Get the required information from the corresponding standard face. */
299  const unsigned short ind = surfElem[l].indStandardElement;
300  const su2double *weights = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetWeightsIntegration();
301 
302  /* Loop over the donors for this boundary face. */
303  for(unsigned long j=0; j<surfElem[l].donorsWallFunction.size(); ++j) {
304 
305  /* Easier storage of the element ID of the donor and set the pointer
306  where the solution of this element starts. Note that VecWorkSolDOFs
307  must be used and not VecSolDOFs, because it is possible that a donor
308  is a halo element, which are not stored in VecSolDOFs. */
309  const unsigned long donorID = surfElem[l].donorsWallFunction[j];
310  const unsigned short timeLevel = volElem[donorID].timeLevel;
311  const unsigned short nDOFsElem = volElem[donorID].nDOFsSol;
312  const su2double *solDOFsElem = VecWorkSolDOFs[timeLevel].data()
313  + nVar*volElem[donorID].offsetDOFsSolThisTimeLevel;
314 
315  /* Determine the number of integration points for this donor and
316  interpolate the solution for the corresponding exchange points. */
317  const unsigned short nIntThisDonor = surfElem[l].nIntPerWallFunctionDonor[j+1]
318  - surfElem[l].nIntPerWallFunctionDonor[j];
319 
320  blasFunctions->gemm(nIntThisDonor, nVar, nDOFsElem, surfElem[l].matWallFunctionDonor[j].data(),
321  solDOFsElem, workArray, config);
322 
323  /* Loop over the integration points for this donor element. */
324  for(unsigned short i=surfElem[l].nIntPerWallFunctionDonor[j];
325  i<surfElem[l].nIntPerWallFunctionDonor[j+1]; ++i) {
326 
327  /* Easier storage of the actual integration point. */
328  const unsigned short ii = surfElem[l].intPerWallFunctionDonor[i];
329 
330  /* Determine the normal, wall velocity and coordinates
331  for this integration point. */
332  const su2double *normals = surfElem[l].metricNormalsFace.data() + ii*(nDim+1);
333  const su2double *gridVel = surfElem[l].gridVelocities.data() + ii*nDim;
334  const su2double *Coord = surfElem[l].coorIntegrationPoints.data() + ii*nDim;
335 
336  /* Determine the velocities and pressure in the exchange point. */
337  const su2double *solInt = workArray
338  + nVar*(i-surfElem[l].nIntPerWallFunctionDonor[j]);
339 
340  su2double rhoInv = 1.0/solInt[0];
341  su2double vel[] = {0.0, 0.0, 0.0};
342  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k) vel[k] = rhoInv*solInt[k+1];
343 
344  su2double vel2Mag = vel[0]*vel[0] + vel[1]*vel[1] + vel[2]*vel[2];
345  su2double eInt = rhoInv*solInt[nVar-1] - 0.5*vel2Mag;
346 
347  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(solInt[0], eInt);
348  const su2double Pressure = FluidModel->GetPressure();
349  const su2double Temperature = FluidModel->GetTemperature();
350  const su2double LaminarViscosity= FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
351 
352  /* Subtract the prescribed wall velocity, i.e. grid velocity
353  from the velocity in the exchange point. */
354  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k) vel[k] -= gridVel[k];
355 
356  /* Determine the tangential velocity by subtracting the normal
357  velocity component. */
358  su2double velNorm = 0.0;
359  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k) velNorm += normals[k]*vel[k];
360  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k) vel[k] -= normals[k]*velNorm;
361 
362  /* Determine the magnitude of the tangential velocity as well
363  as its direction (unit vector). */
364  su2double velTan = sqrt(vel[0]*vel[0] + vel[1]*vel[1] + vel[2]*vel[2]);
365  velTan = max(velTan,1.e-25);
366 
367  su2double dirTan[] = {0.0, 0.0, 0.0};
368  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k) dirTan[k] = vel[k]/velTan;
369 
370  /* Compute the wall shear stress and heat flux vector using
371  the wall model. */
372  su2double tauWall, qWall, ViscosityWall, kOverCvWall;
373 
374  boundaries[iMarker].wallModel->WallShearStressAndHeatFlux(Temperature, velTan,
375  LaminarViscosity, Pressure,
376  Wall_HeatFlux, HeatFlux_Prescribed,
377  Wall_Temperature, Temperature_Prescribed,
378  FluidModel, tauWall, qWall,
379  ViscosityWall, kOverCvWall);
380 
381  /* Update the viscous forces and moments. Note that the force direction
382  is the direction of the tangential velocity. */
383  const su2double dForceMag = tauWall*weights[ii]*normals[nDim]*factor;
384  su2double dForces[] = {0.0, 0.0, 0.0}, dCoor[] = {0.0, 0.0, 0.0};
385  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k) {
386  dCoor[k] = Coord[k] - Origin[k];
387  dForces[k] = dForceMag*dirTan[k];
388  ForceViscous[k] += dForces[k];
389  }
390 
391  if(nDim == 2) {
392  MomentViscous[2] += (dForces[1]*dCoor[0] - dForces[0]*dCoor[1])/RefLength;
393  }
394  else {
395  MomentViscous[0] += (dForces[2]*dCoor[1] - dForces[1]*dCoor[2])/RefLength;
396  MomentViscous[1] += (dForces[0]*dCoor[2] - dForces[2]*dCoor[0])/RefLength;
397  MomentViscous[2] += (dForces[1]*dCoor[0] - dForces[0]*dCoor[1])/RefLength;
398  }
399 
400  /* Update the heat flux and maximum heat flux for this marker. */
401  Heat_Visc[iMarker] += qWall*weights[i]*normals[nDim];
402  MaxHeatFlux_Visc[iMarker] = max(MaxHeatFlux_Visc[iMarker], fabs(qWall));
403  }
404  }
405  }
406 
407  } else {
408 
409  /*--- Integration to the wall is used so the wall data must be computed.
410  Loop over the faces of this boundary. Multiple faces are treated
411  simultaneously to improve the performance of the matrix
412  multiplications. As a consequence, the update of the counter l
413  happens at the end of this loop section. ---*/
414  for(unsigned long l=0; l<nSurfElem;) {
415 
416  /* Determine the end index for this chunk of faces and the padded
417  N value in the gemm computations. */
418  unsigned long lEnd;
419  unsigned short ind, llEnd, NPad;
420 
421  MetaDataChunkOfElem(surfElem, l, nSurfElem, nFaceSimul,
422  nPadMin, lEnd, ind, llEnd, NPad);
423 
424  /* Get the required information from the corresponding standard face. */
425  const unsigned short nInt = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
426  const unsigned short nDOFsFace = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNDOFsFace();
427  const unsigned short nDOFsElem = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNDOFsElem();
428  const su2double *basisFace = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetBasisFaceIntegration();
429  const su2double *derBasisElem = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetMatDerBasisElemIntegration();
430  const su2double *weights = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetWeightsIntegration();
431 
432  /* Set the pointers for the local work arrays. */
433  su2double *solInt = workArray;
434  su2double *gradSolInt = solInt + NPad*nInt;
435  su2double *solCopy = gradSolInt + NPad*nInt*nDim;
436 
437  /* Loop over the faces that are treated simultaneously. */
438  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
439  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
440 
441  /* Easier storage of the DOFs of the face. */
442  const unsigned long *DOFs = surfElem[l+ll].DOFsSolFace.data();
443 
444  /* Copy the solution of the DOFs of the face such that it is
445  contiguous in memory. */
446  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFsFace; ++i) {
447  const su2double *solDOF = VecSolDOFs.data() + nVar*DOFs[i];
448  su2double *sol = solCopy + NPad*i + llNVar;
449  for(unsigned short mm=0; mm<nVar; ++mm)
450  sol[mm] = solDOF[mm];
451  }
452  }
453 
454  /* Call the general function to carry out the matrix product to determine
455  the solution in the integration points. */
456  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt, NPad, nDOFsFace, basisFace, solCopy, solInt, config);
457 
458  /*--- Store the solution of the DOFs of the adjacent elements in contiguous
459  memory such that the function blasFunctions->gemm can be used to compute
460  the gradients solution variables in the integration points of the face. ---*/
461  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
462  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
463  const unsigned long lll = l + ll;
464 
465  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFsElem; ++i) {
466  const su2double *solDOF = VecSolDOFs.data() + nVar*surfElem[lll].DOFsSolElement[i];
467  su2double *sol = solCopy + NPad*i + llNVar;
468  for(unsigned short mm=0; mm<nVar; ++mm)
469  sol[mm] = solDOF[mm];
470  }
471  }
472 
473  /* Compute the gradients in the integration points. Call the general function to
474  carry out the matrix product. */
475  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*nDim, NPad, nDOFsElem, derBasisElem, solCopy, gradSolInt, config);
476 
477  /* Determine the offset between r- and -s-derivatives, which is also the
478  offset between s- and t-derivatives. */
479  const unsigned short offDeriv = NPad*nInt;
480 
481  /* Make a distinction between two and three space dimensions
482  in order to have the most efficient code. */
483  switch( nDim ) {
484 
485  case 2: {
486 
487  /* Two dimensional simulation. Loop over the number of faces treated
488  simultaneously. */
489  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
490  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
491  const unsigned long lll = l + ll;
492 
493  /* Loop over the integration points of this surface element. */
494  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
495 
496  /* Easier storage of the solution, its gradients, the normals,
497  the metric terms and the coordinates of this integration point. */
498  const su2double *sol = solInt + i*NPad + llNVar;
499  const su2double *solDOFDr = gradSolInt + i*NPad + llNVar;
500  const su2double *solDOFDs = solDOFDr + offDeriv;
501  const su2double *normals = surfElem[lll].metricNormalsFace.data()
502  + i*(nDim+1);
503  const su2double *metricTerms = surfElem[lll].metricCoorDerivFace.data()
504  + i*nDim*nDim;
505  const su2double *Coord = surfElem[lll].coorIntegrationPoints.data()
506  + i*nDim;
507 
508  /* Easier storage of the metric terms. */
509  const su2double drdx = metricTerms[0];
510  const su2double drdy = metricTerms[1];
511  const su2double dsdx = metricTerms[2];
512  const su2double dsdy = metricTerms[3];
513 
514  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the solution. */
515  const su2double drhodx = solDOFDr[0]*drdx + solDOFDs[0]*dsdx;
516  const su2double drudx = solDOFDr[1]*drdx + solDOFDs[1]*dsdx;
517  const su2double drvdx = solDOFDr[2]*drdx + solDOFDs[2]*dsdx;
518  const su2double drEdx = solDOFDr[3]*drdx + solDOFDs[3]*dsdx;
519 
520  const su2double drhody = solDOFDr[0]*drdy + solDOFDs[0]*dsdy;
521  const su2double drudy = solDOFDr[1]*drdy + solDOFDs[1]*dsdy;
522  const su2double drvdy = solDOFDr[2]*drdy + solDOFDs[2]*dsdy;
523  const su2double drEdy = solDOFDr[3]*drdy + solDOFDs[3]*dsdy;
524 
525  /* Compute the velocities and static energy in this
526  integration point. */
527  const su2double DensityInv = 1.0/sol[0];
528  const su2double u = DensityInv*sol[1];
529  const su2double v = DensityInv*sol[2];
530  const su2double TotalEnergy = DensityInv*sol[3];
531  const su2double StaticEnergy = TotalEnergy - 0.5*(u*u + v*v);
532 
533  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the velocities and
534  static energy in this integration point and also the
535  divergence of the velocity. */
536  const su2double dudx = DensityInv*(drudx - u*drhodx);
537  const su2double dudy = DensityInv*(drudy - u*drhody);
538 
539  const su2double dvdx = DensityInv*(drvdx - v*drhodx);
540  const su2double dvdy = DensityInv*(drvdy - v*drhody);
541 
542  const su2double dStaticEnergydx = DensityInv*(drEdx - TotalEnergy*drhodx)
543  - u*dudx - v*dvdx;
544  const su2double dStaticEnergydy = DensityInv*(drEdy - TotalEnergy*drhody)
545  - u*dudy - v*dvdy;
546  const su2double divVel = dudx + dvdy;
547 
548  /* Compute the laminar viscosity. */
549  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(sol[0], StaticEnergy);
550  const su2double ViscosityLam = FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
551 
552  /* Set the value of the second viscosity and compute the
553  divergence term in the viscous normal stresses. */
554  const su2double lambda = -TWO3*ViscosityLam;
555  const su2double lamDivTerm = lambda*divVel;
556 
557  /* Compute the viscous stress tensor and the normal flux.
558  Note that there is a plus sign for the heat flux, because
559  the normal points into the geometry. */
560  const su2double tauxx = 2.0*ViscosityLam*dudx + lamDivTerm;
561  const su2double tauyy = 2.0*ViscosityLam*dvdy + lamDivTerm;
562  const su2double tauxy = ViscosityLam*(dudy + dvdx);
563 
564  const su2double qHeatNorm = ViscosityLam*factHeatFlux_Lam
565  * (dStaticEnergydx*normals[0]
566  + dStaticEnergydy*normals[1]);
567 
568  /* Update the viscous force and moment. Note that the normal
569  points into the geometry, hence the minus sign for the stress. */
570  const su2double scaleFac = weights[i]*normals[nDim]*factor;
571  const su2double Fx = -scaleFac*(tauxx*normals[0] + tauxy*normals[1]);
572  const su2double Fy = -scaleFac*(tauxy*normals[0] + tauyy*normals[1]);
573 
574  ForceViscous[0] += Fx;
575  ForceViscous[1] += Fy;
576 
577  const su2double dx = Coord[0] - Origin[0];
578  const su2double dy = Coord[1] - Origin[1];
579 
580  MomentViscous[2] += (Fy*dx - Fx*dy)/RefLength;
581 
582  /* Update the heat flux and maximum heat flux for this marker. */
583  Heat_Visc[iMarker] += qHeatNorm*weights[i]*normals[nDim]*RefHeatFlux;
584  MaxHeatFlux_Visc[iMarker] = max(MaxHeatFlux_Visc[iMarker], fabs(qHeatNorm));
585  }
586  }
587 
588  break;
589  }
590 
591  /*------------------------------------------------------------------*/
592 
593  case 3: {
594 
595  /* Three dimensional simulation. Loop over the number of faces treated
596  simultaneously. */
597  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
598  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
599  const unsigned long lll = l + ll;
600 
601  /* Loop over the integration points of this surface element. */
602  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
603 
604  /* Easier storage of the solution, its gradients, the normals,
605  the metric terms and the coordinates of this integration point. */
606  const su2double *sol = solInt + i*NPad + llNVar;
607  const su2double *solDOFDr = gradSolInt + i*NPad + llNVar;
608  const su2double *solDOFDs = solDOFDr + offDeriv;
609  const su2double *solDOFDt = solDOFDs + offDeriv;
610  const su2double *normals = surfElem[lll].metricNormalsFace.data()
611  + i*(nDim+1);
612  const su2double *metricTerms = surfElem[lll].metricCoorDerivFace.data()
613  + i*nDim*nDim;
614  const su2double *Coord = surfElem[lll].coorIntegrationPoints.data()
615  + i*nDim;
616 
617  /* Easier storage of the metric terms. */
618  const su2double drdx = metricTerms[0];
619  const su2double drdy = metricTerms[1];
620  const su2double drdz = metricTerms[2];
621 
622  const su2double dsdx = metricTerms[3];
623  const su2double dsdy = metricTerms[4];
624  const su2double dsdz = metricTerms[5];
625 
626  const su2double dtdx = metricTerms[6];
627  const su2double dtdy = metricTerms[7];
628  const su2double dtdz = metricTerms[8];
629 
630  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the solution. */
631  const su2double drhodx = solDOFDr[0]*drdx + solDOFDs[0]*dsdx + solDOFDt[0]*dtdx;
632  const su2double drudx = solDOFDr[1]*drdx + solDOFDs[1]*dsdx + solDOFDt[1]*dtdx;
633  const su2double drvdx = solDOFDr[2]*drdx + solDOFDs[2]*dsdx + solDOFDt[2]*dtdx;
634  const su2double drwdx = solDOFDr[3]*drdx + solDOFDs[3]*dsdx + solDOFDt[3]*dtdx;
635  const su2double drEdx = solDOFDr[4]*drdx + solDOFDs[4]*dsdx + solDOFDt[4]*dtdx;
636 
637  const su2double drhody = solDOFDr[0]*drdy + solDOFDs[0]*dsdy + solDOFDt[0]*dtdy;
638  const su2double drudy = solDOFDr[1]*drdy + solDOFDs[1]*dsdy + solDOFDt[1]*dtdy;
639  const su2double drvdy = solDOFDr[2]*drdy + solDOFDs[2]*dsdy + solDOFDt[2]*dtdy;
640  const su2double drwdy = solDOFDr[3]*drdy + solDOFDs[3]*dsdy + solDOFDt[3]*dtdy;
641  const su2double drEdy = solDOFDr[4]*drdy + solDOFDs[4]*dsdy + solDOFDt[4]*dtdy;
642 
643  const su2double drhodz = solDOFDr[0]*drdz + solDOFDs[0]*dsdz + solDOFDt[0]*dtdz;
644  const su2double drudz = solDOFDr[1]*drdz + solDOFDs[1]*dsdz + solDOFDt[1]*dtdz;
645  const su2double drvdz = solDOFDr[2]*drdz + solDOFDs[2]*dsdz + solDOFDt[2]*dtdz;
646  const su2double drwdz = solDOFDr[3]*drdz + solDOFDs[3]*dsdz + solDOFDt[3]*dtdz;
647  const su2double drEdz = solDOFDr[4]*drdz + solDOFDs[4]*dsdz + solDOFDt[4]*dtdz;
648 
649  /* Compute the velocities and static energy in this
650  integration point. */
651  const su2double DensityInv = 1.0/sol[0];
652  const su2double u = DensityInv*sol[1];
653  const su2double v = DensityInv*sol[2];
654  const su2double w = DensityInv*sol[3];
655  const su2double TotalEnergy = DensityInv*sol[4];
656  const su2double StaticEnergy = TotalEnergy - 0.5*(u*u + v*v + w*w);
657 
658  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the velocities and
659  static energy in this integration point and also the
660  divergence of the velocity. */
661  const su2double dudx = DensityInv*(drudx - u*drhodx);
662  const su2double dudy = DensityInv*(drudy - u*drhody);
663  const su2double dudz = DensityInv*(drudz - u*drhodz);
664 
665  const su2double dvdx = DensityInv*(drvdx - v*drhodx);
666  const su2double dvdy = DensityInv*(drvdy - v*drhody);
667  const su2double dvdz = DensityInv*(drvdz - v*drhodz);
668 
669  const su2double dwdx = DensityInv*(drwdx - w*drhodx);
670  const su2double dwdy = DensityInv*(drwdy - w*drhody);
671  const su2double dwdz = DensityInv*(drwdz - w*drhodz);
672 
673  const su2double dStaticEnergydx = DensityInv*(drEdx - TotalEnergy*drhodx)
674  - u*dudx - v*dvdx - w*dwdx;
675  const su2double dStaticEnergydy = DensityInv*(drEdy - TotalEnergy*drhody)
676  - u*dudy - v*dvdy - w*dwdy;
677  const su2double dStaticEnergydz = DensityInv*(drEdz - TotalEnergy*drhodz)
678  - u*dudz - v*dvdz - w*dwdz;
679  const su2double divVel = dudx + dvdy + dwdz;
680 
681  /* Compute the laminar viscosity. */
682  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(sol[0], StaticEnergy);
683  const su2double ViscosityLam = FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
684 
685  /* Set the value of the second viscosity and compute the
686  divergence term in the viscous normal stresses. */
687  const su2double lambda = -TWO3*ViscosityLam;
688  const su2double lamDivTerm = lambda*divVel;
689 
690  /* Compute the viscous stress tensor and the normal flux.
691  Note that there is a plus sign for the heat flux, because
692  the normal points into the geometry. */
693  const su2double tauxx = 2.0*ViscosityLam*dudx + lamDivTerm;
694  const su2double tauyy = 2.0*ViscosityLam*dvdy + lamDivTerm;
695  const su2double tauzz = 2.0*ViscosityLam*dwdz + lamDivTerm;
696 
697  const su2double tauxy = ViscosityLam*(dudy + dvdx);
698  const su2double tauxz = ViscosityLam*(dudz + dwdx);
699  const su2double tauyz = ViscosityLam*(dvdz + dwdy);
700 
701  const su2double qHeatNorm = ViscosityLam*factHeatFlux_Lam
702  * (dStaticEnergydx*normals[0]
703  + dStaticEnergydy*normals[1]
704  + dStaticEnergydz*normals[2]);
705 
706  /* Update the viscous force and moment. Note that the normal
707  points into the geometry, hence the minus sign for the stress. */
708  const su2double scaleFac = weights[i]*normals[nDim]*factor;
709 
710  const su2double Fx = -scaleFac*(tauxx*normals[0] + tauxy*normals[1]
711  + tauxz*normals[2]);
712  const su2double Fy = -scaleFac*(tauxy*normals[0] + tauyy*normals[1]
713  + tauyz*normals[2]);
714  const su2double Fz = -scaleFac*(tauxz*normals[0] + tauyz*normals[1]
715  + tauzz*normals[2]);
716 
717  ForceViscous[0] += Fx;
718  ForceViscous[1] += Fy;
719  ForceViscous[2] += Fz;
720 
721  const su2double dx = Coord[0] - Origin[0];
722  const su2double dy = Coord[1] - Origin[1];
723  const su2double dz = Coord[2] - Origin[2];
724 
725  MomentViscous[0] += (Fz*dy - Fy*dz)/RefLength;
726  MomentViscous[1] += (Fx*dz - Fz*dx)/RefLength;
727  MomentViscous[2] += (Fy*dx - Fx*dy)/RefLength;
728 
729  /* Update the heat flux and maximum heat flux for this marker. */
730  Heat_Visc[iMarker] += qHeatNorm*weights[i]*normals[nDim]*RefHeatFlux;
731  MaxHeatFlux_Visc[iMarker] = max(MaxHeatFlux_Visc[iMarker], fabs(qHeatNorm));
732  }
733  }
734 
735  break;
736  }
737  }
738 
739  /* Update the value of the counter l to the end index of the
740  current chunk. */
741  l = lEnd;
742  }
743  }
744 
745  /*--- Project forces and store the non-dimensional coefficients ---*/
746  if (nDim == 2) {
747  CD_Visc[iMarker] = ForceViscous[0]*cos(Alpha) + ForceViscous[1]*sin(Alpha);
748  CL_Visc[iMarker] = -ForceViscous[0]*sin(Alpha) + ForceViscous[1]*cos(Alpha);
749  CEff_Visc[iMarker] = CL_Visc[iMarker] / (CD_Visc[iMarker]+EPS);
750  CMz_Visc[iMarker] = MomentViscous[2];
751  CFx_Visc[iMarker] = ForceViscous[0];
752  CFy_Visc[iMarker] = ForceViscous[1];
753  }
754  if (nDim == 3) {
755  CD_Visc[iMarker] = ForceViscous[0]*cos(Alpha)*cos(Beta)
756  + ForceViscous[1]*sin(Beta)
757  + ForceViscous[2]*sin(Alpha)*cos(Beta);
758  CL_Visc[iMarker] = -ForceViscous[0]*sin(Alpha) + ForceViscous[2]*cos(Alpha);
759  CSF_Visc[iMarker] = -ForceViscous[0]*sin(Beta)*cos(Alpha)
760  + ForceViscous[1]*cos(Beta)
761  - ForceViscous[2]*sin(Beta)*sin(Alpha);
762  CEff_Visc[iMarker] = CL_Visc[iMarker]/(CD_Visc[iMarker] + EPS);
763  CMx_Visc[iMarker] = MomentViscous[0];
764  CMy_Visc[iMarker] = MomentViscous[1];
765  CMz_Visc[iMarker] = MomentViscous[2];
766  CFx_Visc[iMarker] = ForceViscous[0];
767  CFy_Visc[iMarker] = ForceViscous[1];
768  CFz_Visc[iMarker] = ForceViscous[2];
769  }
770 
771  AllBound_CD_Visc += CD_Visc[iMarker];
772  AllBound_CL_Visc += CL_Visc[iMarker];
773  AllBound_CSF_Visc += CSF_Visc[iMarker];
774  AllBound_CMx_Visc += CMx_Visc[iMarker];
775  AllBound_CMy_Visc += CMy_Visc[iMarker];
776  AllBound_CMz_Visc += CMz_Visc[iMarker];
777  AllBound_CFx_Visc += CFx_Visc[iMarker];
778  AllBound_CFy_Visc += CFy_Visc[iMarker];
779  AllBound_CFz_Visc += CFz_Visc[iMarker];
780 
781  AllBound_HeatFlux_Visc += Heat_Visc[iMarker];
782  AllBound_MaxHeatFlux_Visc = max(AllBound_MaxHeatFlux_Visc,
783  MaxHeatFlux_Visc[iMarker]);
784 
785  /*--- Compute the coefficients per surface ---*/
786  for(unsigned short iMarker_Monitoring=0; iMarker_Monitoring<config->GetnMarker_Monitoring();
787  ++iMarker_Monitoring) {
788  string Monitoring_Tag = config->GetMarker_Monitoring_TagBound(iMarker_Monitoring);
789  string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker);
790  if (Marker_Tag == Monitoring_Tag) {
791  Surface_CL_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] += CL_Visc[iMarker];
792  Surface_CD_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] += CD_Visc[iMarker];
793  Surface_CSF_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] += CSF_Visc[iMarker];
794  Surface_CEff_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] += CEff_Visc[iMarker];
795  Surface_CFx_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] += CFx_Visc[iMarker];
796  Surface_CFy_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] += CFy_Visc[iMarker];
797  Surface_CFz_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] += CFz_Visc[iMarker];
798  Surface_CMx_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] += CMx_Visc[iMarker];
799  Surface_CMy_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] += CMy_Visc[iMarker];
800  Surface_CMz_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring] += CMz_Visc[iMarker];
801  }
802  }
803  }
804  }
805  }
806 
807 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
808 
809  /*--- Parallel mode. The data from all ranks must be gathered.
810  Determine the size of the communication buffer. ---*/
811  const unsigned long nCommSize = 9*config->GetnMarker_Monitoring() + 10;
812 
813  /*--- Define the communication buffers and store to local data in
814  the local buffer. ---*/
815  vector<su2double> locBuf(nCommSize), globBuf(nCommSize);
816 
817  unsigned long ii = 0;
818  locBuf[ii++] = AllBound_CD_Visc; locBuf[ii++] = AllBound_CL_Visc;
819  locBuf[ii++] = AllBound_CSF_Visc; locBuf[ii++] = AllBound_CMx_Visc;
820  locBuf[ii++] = AllBound_CMy_Visc; locBuf[ii++] = AllBound_CMz_Visc;
821  locBuf[ii++] = AllBound_CFx_Visc; locBuf[ii++] = AllBound_CFy_Visc;
822  locBuf[ii++] = AllBound_CFz_Visc; locBuf[ii++] = AllBound_HeatFlux_Visc;
823 
824  for(unsigned short i=0; i<config->GetnMarker_Monitoring(); ++i) {
825  locBuf[ii++] = Surface_CL_Visc[i]; locBuf[ii++] = Surface_CD_Visc[i];
826  locBuf[ii++] = Surface_CSF_Visc[i]; locBuf[ii++] = Surface_CFx_Visc[i];
827  locBuf[ii++] = Surface_CFy_Visc[i]; locBuf[ii++] = Surface_CFz_Visc[i];
828  locBuf[ii++] = Surface_CMx_Visc[i]; locBuf[ii++] = Surface_CMy_Visc[i];
829  locBuf[ii++] = Surface_CMz_Visc[i];
830  }
831 
832  /* Sum up all the data from all ranks. The result will be available on all ranks. */
833  if (config->GetComm_Level() == COMM_FULL) {
834  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(locBuf.data(), globBuf.data(), nCommSize, MPI_DOUBLE,
835  MPI_SUM, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
836  }
837 
838  /*--- Copy the data back from globBuf into the required variables. ---*/
839  ii = 0;
840  AllBound_CD_Visc = globBuf[ii++]; AllBound_CL_Visc = globBuf[ii++];
841  AllBound_CSF_Visc = globBuf[ii++]; AllBound_CMx_Visc = globBuf[ii++];
842  AllBound_CMy_Visc = globBuf[ii++]; AllBound_CMz_Visc = globBuf[ii++];
843  AllBound_CFx_Visc = globBuf[ii++]; AllBound_CFy_Visc = globBuf[ii++];
844  AllBound_CFz_Visc = globBuf[ii++]; AllBound_HeatFlux_Visc = globBuf[ii++];
845 
846  AllBound_CEff_Visc = AllBound_CL_Visc/(AllBound_CD_Visc + EPS);
847 
848  for(unsigned short i=0; i<config->GetnMarker_Monitoring(); ++i) {
849  Surface_CL_Visc[i] = globBuf[ii++]; Surface_CD_Visc[i] = globBuf[ii++];
850  Surface_CSF_Visc[i] = globBuf[ii++]; Surface_CFx_Visc[i] = globBuf[ii++];
851  Surface_CFy_Visc[i] = globBuf[ii++]; Surface_CFz_Visc[i] = globBuf[ii++];
852  Surface_CMx_Visc[i] = globBuf[ii++]; Surface_CMy_Visc[i] = globBuf[ii++];
853  Surface_CMz_Visc[i] = globBuf[ii++];
854 
855  Surface_CEff_Visc[i] = Surface_CL_Visc[i]/(Surface_CD_Visc[i] + EPS);
856  }
857 
858  /* Determine the maximum heat flux over all ranks. */
859  su2double localMax = AllBound_MaxHeatFlux_Visc;
860  if (config->GetComm_Level() == COMM_FULL) {
861  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&localMax, &AllBound_MaxHeatFlux_Visc, 1, MPI_DOUBLE,
862  MPI_MAX, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
863  }
864 #endif
865 
866  /*--- Update the total coefficients (note that all the nodes have the same value)---*/
867  Total_CD += AllBound_CD_Visc;
868  Total_CL += AllBound_CL_Visc;
869  Total_CSF += AllBound_CSF_Visc;
870  Total_CEff = Total_CL / (Total_CD + EPS);
871  Total_CMx += AllBound_CMx_Visc;
872  Total_CMy += AllBound_CMy_Visc;
873  Total_CMz += AllBound_CMz_Visc;
874  Total_CFx += AllBound_CFx_Visc;
875  Total_CFy += AllBound_CFy_Visc;
876  Total_CFz += AllBound_CFz_Visc;
877 
878  /*--- Update the total coefficients per surface (note that all the nodes have the same value)---*/
879  for (unsigned short iMarker_Monitoring=0; iMarker_Monitoring<config->GetnMarker_Monitoring();
880  ++iMarker_Monitoring) {
881  Surface_CL[iMarker_Monitoring] += Surface_CL_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring];
882  Surface_CD[iMarker_Monitoring] += Surface_CD_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring];
883  Surface_CSF[iMarker_Monitoring] += Surface_CSF_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring];
884  Surface_CEff[iMarker_Monitoring] = Surface_CL[iMarker_Monitoring] / (Surface_CD[iMarker_Monitoring] + EPS);
885  Surface_CFx[iMarker_Monitoring] += Surface_CFx_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring];
886  Surface_CFy[iMarker_Monitoring] += Surface_CFy_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring];
887  Surface_CFz[iMarker_Monitoring] += Surface_CFz_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring];
888  Surface_CMx[iMarker_Monitoring] += Surface_CMx_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring];
889  Surface_CMy[iMarker_Monitoring] += Surface_CMy_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring];
890  Surface_CMz[iMarker_Monitoring] += Surface_CMz_Visc[iMarker_Monitoring];
891  }
892 }
893 
894 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::SetTime_Step(CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver_container, CConfig *config,
895  unsigned short iMesh, unsigned long Iteration) {
896 
897  /* Check whether or not a time stepping scheme is used. */
898  const bool time_stepping = config->GetTime_Marching() == TIME_MARCHING::TIME_STEPPING;
899 
900  /* Allocate the memory for the work array and initialize it to zero to avoid
901  warnings in debug mode about uninitialized memory when padding is applied. */
902  vector<su2double> workArrayVec(sizeWorkArray, 0.0);
903  su2double *workArray = workArrayVec.data();
904 
905  /* Constant factor present in the heat flux vector, namely the ratio of
906  thermal conductivity and viscosity. */
907  const su2double factHeatFlux_Lam = Gamma/Prandtl_Lam;
908  const su2double factHeatFlux_Turb = Gamma/Prandtl_Turb;
909 
910  /* Constant ratio of the second viscosity and the viscosity itself. */
911  const su2double lambdaOverMu = -TWO3;
912 
913  /* The eigenvalues of the viscous Jacobian, scaled by the kinematic viscosity,
914  are 1.0, 2.0 + lambdaOverMu and kOverCv/Mu. The last is variable due to the
915  possible presence of an eddy viscosity, but the first two are constant and
916  the maximum can be determined. */
917  const su2double radOverNuTerm = max(1.0, 2.0+lambdaOverMu);
918 
919  /* Store the number of metric points per DOF, which depends
920  on the number of dimensions. */
921  const unsigned short nMetricPerPoint = nDim*nDim + 1;
922 
923  /* Determine the number of elements that are treated simultaneously
924  in the matrix products to obtain good gemm performance. */
925  const unsigned short nPadInput = config->GetSizeMatMulPadding();
926  const unsigned short nElemSimul = nPadInput/nVar;
927 
928  /* Determine the minimum padded size in the matrix multiplications, which
929  corresponds to 64 byte alignment. */
930  const unsigned short nPadMin = 64/sizeof(passivedouble);
931 
932  /* Initialize the minimum and maximum time step. */
933  Min_Delta_Time = 1.e25; Max_Delta_Time = 0.0;
934 
935  /* Easier storage of the CFL number. Note that if we are using explicit
936  time stepping, the regular CFL condition has been overwritten with the
937  unsteady CFL condition in the config post-processing (if non-zero). */
938 
939  const su2double CFL = config->GetCFL(iMesh);
940 
941  /*--- Explicit time stepping with imposed time step (eventually will
942  allow for local time stepping with this value imposed as the time
943  for syncing the cells). If the unsteady CFL is set to zero (default),
944  it uses the defined unsteady time step, otherwise it computes the time
945  step based on the provided unsteady CFL. Note that the regular CFL
946  option in the config is always ignored with time stepping. ---*/
947  if (time_stepping && (config->GetUnst_CFL() == 0.0)) {
948 
949  /*--- Loop over the owned volume elements and set the fixed dt. ---*/
950  for(unsigned long l=0; l<nVolElemOwned; ++l)
951  VecDeltaTime[l] = config->GetDelta_UnstTimeND();
952 
953  } else {
954 
955  /*--- Check for a compressible solver. ---*/
956  if(config->GetKind_Regime() == ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE) {
957 
958  /*--- Loop over the owned volume elements. Multiple elements are treated
959  simultaneously to improve the performance of the matrix
960  multiplications. As a consequence, the update of the counter l
961  happens at the end of this loop section. ---*/
962  for(unsigned long l=0; l<nVolElemOwned;) {
963 
964  /* Determine the end index for this chunk of elements and the padded
965  N value in the gemm computations. */
966  unsigned long lEnd;
967  unsigned short ind, llEnd, NPad;
968 
969  MetaDataChunkOfElem(volElem, l, nVolElemOwned, nElemSimul, nPadMin,
970  lEnd, ind, llEnd, NPad);
971 
972  /* Get the required data from the corresponding standard element. */
973  const unsigned short nDOFs = volElem[l].nDOFsSol;
974  const su2double *matDerBasisSolDOFs = standardElementsSol[ind].GetMatDerBasisFunctionsSolDOFs();
975 
976  unsigned short nPoly = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNPoly();
977  if(nPoly == 0) nPoly = 1;
978 
979  /*--- Set the pointers for the local arrays. ---*/
980  su2double *solDOFs = workArray;
981  su2double *gradSolDOFs = solDOFs + nDOFs*NPad;
982 
983  /* Determine the offset between the r-derivatives and s-derivatives, which is
984  also the offset between s- and t-derivatives, of the solution in the DOFs. */
985  const unsigned short offDerivSol = NPad*volElem[l].nDOFsSol;
986 
987  /*--- Compute the gradients of the conserved variables if a subgrid
988  scale model for LES is used. ---*/
989  if( SGSModelUsed ) {
990 
991  /* Copy the solution of the DOFs into solDOFs for this chunk of elements. */
992  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
993 
994  /* Easier storage of the solution of this element. */
995  const unsigned long lInd = l + ll;
996  const su2double *sol = VecSolDOFs.data() + nVar*volElem[lInd].offsetDOFsSolLocal;
997 
998  /* Loop over the DOFs and copy the data. */
999  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
1000  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFs; ++i)
1001  for(unsigned short mm=0; mm<nVar; ++mm)
1002  solDOFs[i*NPad+llNVar+mm] = sol[i*nVar+mm];
1003  }
1004 
1005  /* Call the general function to carry out the matrix product to determine
1006  the gradients in the DOFs of this chunk of elements. */
1007  blasFunctions->gemm(nDOFs*nDim, NPad, nDOFs, matDerBasisSolDOFs, solDOFs, gradSolDOFs, config);
1008  }
1009 
1010  /*--- Make a distinction between 2D and 3D for optimal performance. ---*/
1011  switch( nDim ) {
1012 
1013  case 2: {
1014 
1015  /*--- 2D simulation. Loop over the chunk of elements. ---*/
1016  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
1017  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
1018  const unsigned long lInd = l + ll;
1019 
1020  /* Compute the length scale of this element and initialize the
1021  inviscid and viscous spectral radii to zero. */
1022  const su2double lenScaleInv = nPoly/volElem[lInd].lenScale;
1023  const su2double lenScale = 1.0/lenScaleInv;
1024 
1025  su2double charVel2Max = 0.0, radViscMax = 0.0;
1026 
1027  /* Loop over the DOFs of the element to determine the time step. */
1028  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFs; ++i) {
1029  const su2double *solDOF = VecSolDOFs.data()
1030  + nVar*(volElem[lInd].offsetDOFsSolLocal + i);
1031  const su2double *gridVel = volElem[lInd].gridVelocitiesSolDOFs.data()
1032  + i*nDim;
1033 
1034  /* Compute the velocities and the internal energy per unit mass. */
1035  const su2double DensityInv = 1.0/solDOF[0];
1036  const su2double u = DensityInv*solDOF[1];
1037  const su2double v = DensityInv*solDOF[2];
1038  const su2double StaticEnergy = DensityInv*solDOF[3] - 0.5*(u*u + v*v);
1039 
1040  /*--- Compute the maximum value of the wave speed. This is a rather
1041  conservative estimate. ---*/
1042  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(solDOF[0], StaticEnergy);
1043  const su2double SoundSpeed2 = FluidModel->GetSoundSpeed2();
1044  const su2double SoundSpeed = sqrt(fabs(SoundSpeed2));
1045 
1046  const su2double radx = fabs(u-gridVel[0]) + SoundSpeed;
1047  const su2double rady = fabs(v-gridVel[1]) + SoundSpeed;
1048  const su2double charVel2 = radx*radx + rady*rady;
1049 
1050  charVel2Max = max(charVel2Max, charVel2);
1051 
1052  /* Compute the laminar kinematic viscosity and check if an eddy
1053  viscosity must be determined. */
1054  const su2double muLam = FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
1055  su2double muTurb = 0.0;
1056 
1057  if( SGSModelUsed ) {
1058 
1059  /* Set the pointers to the locations where the gradients
1060  of this DOF start. */
1061  const su2double *solDOFDr = gradSolDOFs + i*NPad + llNVar;
1062  const su2double *solDOFDs = solDOFDr + offDerivSol;
1063 
1064  /* Compute the true value of the metric terms in this DOF. Note that in
1065  metricTerms the metric terms scaled by the Jacobian are stored. */
1066  const su2double *metricTerms = volElem[lInd].metricTermsSolDOFs.data()
1067  + i*nMetricPerPoint;
1068  const su2double JacInv = 1.0/metricTerms[0];
1069 
1070  const su2double drdx = JacInv*metricTerms[1];
1071  const su2double drdy = JacInv*metricTerms[2];
1072 
1073  const su2double dsdx = JacInv*metricTerms[3];
1074  const su2double dsdy = JacInv*metricTerms[4];
1075 
1076  /*--- Compute the Cartesian gradients of the independent solution
1077  variables from the gradients in parametric coordinates and the metric
1078  terms in this DOF. ---*/
1079  const su2double drhodx = solDOFDr[0]*drdx + solDOFDs[0]*dsdx;
1080  const su2double drudx = solDOFDr[1]*drdx + solDOFDs[1]*dsdx;
1081  const su2double drvdx = solDOFDr[2]*drdx + solDOFDs[2]*dsdx;
1082 
1083  const su2double drhody = solDOFDr[0]*drdy + solDOFDs[0]*dsdy;
1084  const su2double drudy = solDOFDr[1]*drdy + solDOFDs[1]*dsdy;
1085  const su2double drvdy = solDOFDr[2]*drdy + solDOFDs[2]*dsdy;
1086 
1087  /*--- Compute the Cartesian gradients of the velocities. ---*/
1088  const su2double dudx = DensityInv*(drudx - u*drhodx);
1089  const su2double dvdx = DensityInv*(drvdx - v*drhodx);
1090  const su2double dudy = DensityInv*(drudy - u*drhody);
1091  const su2double dvdy = DensityInv*(drvdy - v*drhody);
1092 
1093  /* Compute the eddy viscosity. */
1094  const su2double dist = volElem[lInd].wallDistanceSolDOFs[i];
1095  muTurb = SGSModel->ComputeEddyViscosity_2D(solDOF[0], dudx, dudy,
1096  dvdx, dvdy, lenScale,
1097  dist);
1098  }
1099 
1100  /*--- Determine the viscous spectral radius. ---*/
1101  const su2double mu = muLam + muTurb;
1102  const su2double kOverCv = muLam*factHeatFlux_Lam
1103  + muTurb*factHeatFlux_Turb;
1104  const su2double factHeatFlux = kOverCv/mu;
1105 
1106  const su2double radVisc = DensityInv*mu*max(radOverNuTerm, factHeatFlux);
1107 
1108  /* Update the maximum value of the viscous spectral radius. */
1109  radViscMax = max(radViscMax, radVisc);
1110  }
1111 
1112  /*--- Compute the time step for the element and update the minimum and
1113  maximum value. Take the factor for time accurate local time
1114  stepping into account for the minimum and maximum. ---*/
1115  const su2double dtInv = lenScaleInv*(sqrt(charVel2Max) + radViscMax*lenScaleInv);
1116 
1117  VecDeltaTime[lInd] = CFL/dtInv;
1118 
1119  const su2double dtEff = volElem[lInd].factTimeLevel*VecDeltaTime[lInd];
1120  Min_Delta_Time = min(Min_Delta_Time, dtEff);
1121  Max_Delta_Time = max(Max_Delta_Time, dtEff);
1122  }
1123 
1124  break;
1125  }
1126 
1127  /*------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1128 
1129  case 3: {
1130 
1131  /*--- 3D simulation. Loop over the chunk of elements. ---*/
1132  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
1133  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
1134  const unsigned long lInd = l + ll;
1135 
1136  /* Compute the length scale of this element and initialize the
1137  inviscid and viscous spectral radii to zero. */
1138  const su2double lenScaleInv = nPoly/volElem[lInd].lenScale;
1139  const su2double lenScale = 1.0/lenScaleInv;
1140 
1141  su2double charVel2Max = 0.0, radViscMax = 0.0;
1142 
1143  /* Loop over the DOFs of the element to determine the time step. */
1144  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFs; ++i) {
1145  const su2double *solDOF = VecSolDOFs.data()
1146  + nVar*(volElem[lInd].offsetDOFsSolLocal + i);
1147  const su2double *gridVel = volElem[lInd].gridVelocitiesSolDOFs.data()
1148  + i*nDim;
1149 
1150  /* Compute the velocities and the internal energy per unit mass. */
1151  const su2double DensityInv = 1.0/solDOF[0];
1152  const su2double u = DensityInv*solDOF[1];
1153  const su2double v = DensityInv*solDOF[2];
1154  const su2double w = DensityInv*solDOF[3];
1155  const su2double StaticEnergy = DensityInv*solDOF[4] - 0.5*(u*u + v*v + w*w);
1156 
1157  /*--- Compute the maximum value of the wave speed. This is a rather
1158  conservative estimate. ---*/
1159  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(solDOF[0], StaticEnergy);
1160  const su2double SoundSpeed2 = FluidModel->GetSoundSpeed2();
1161  const su2double SoundSpeed = sqrt(fabs(SoundSpeed2));
1162 
1163  const su2double radx = fabs(u-gridVel[0]) + SoundSpeed;
1164  const su2double rady = fabs(v-gridVel[1]) + SoundSpeed;
1165  const su2double radz = fabs(w-gridVel[2]) + SoundSpeed;
1166  const su2double charVel2 = radx*radx + rady*rady + radz*radz;
1167 
1168  charVel2Max = max(charVel2Max, charVel2);
1169 
1170  /* Compute the laminar kinematic viscosity and check if an eddy
1171  viscosity must be determined. */
1172  const su2double muLam = FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
1173  su2double muTurb = 0.0;
1174 
1175  if( SGSModelUsed ) {
1176 
1177  /* Set the pointers to the locations where the gradients
1178  of this DOF start. */
1179  const su2double *solDOFDr = gradSolDOFs + i*NPad + llNVar;
1180  const su2double *solDOFDs = solDOFDr + offDerivSol;
1181  const su2double *solDOFDt = solDOFDs + offDerivSol;
1182 
1183  /* Compute the true value of the metric terms in this DOF. Note that in
1184  metricTerms the metric terms scaled by the Jacobian are stored. */
1185  const su2double *metricTerms = volElem[lInd].metricTermsSolDOFs.data()
1186  + i*nMetricPerPoint;
1187  const su2double JacInv = 1.0/metricTerms[0];
1188 
1189  const su2double drdx = JacInv*metricTerms[1];
1190  const su2double drdy = JacInv*metricTerms[2];
1191  const su2double drdz = JacInv*metricTerms[3];
1192 
1193  const su2double dsdx = JacInv*metricTerms[4];
1194  const su2double dsdy = JacInv*metricTerms[5];
1195  const su2double dsdz = JacInv*metricTerms[6];
1196 
1197  const su2double dtdx = JacInv*metricTerms[7];
1198  const su2double dtdy = JacInv*metricTerms[8];
1199  const su2double dtdz = JacInv*metricTerms[9];
1200 
1201  /*--- Compute the Cartesian gradients of the independent solution
1202  variables from the gradients in parametric coordinates and the metric
1203  terms in this DOF. ---*/
1204  const su2double drhodx = solDOFDr[0]*drdx + solDOFDs[0]*dsdx + solDOFDt[0]*dtdx;
1205  const su2double drux = solDOFDr[1]*drdx + solDOFDs[1]*dsdx + solDOFDt[1]*dtdx;
1206  const su2double drvx = solDOFDr[2]*drdx + solDOFDs[2]*dsdx + solDOFDt[2]*dtdx;
1207  const su2double drwx = solDOFDr[3]*drdx + solDOFDs[3]*dsdx + solDOFDt[3]*dtdx;
1208 
1209  const su2double drhody = solDOFDr[0]*drdy + solDOFDs[0]*dsdy + solDOFDt[0]*dtdy;
1210  const su2double druy = solDOFDr[1]*drdy + solDOFDs[1]*dsdy + solDOFDt[1]*dtdy;
1211  const su2double drvy = solDOFDr[2]*drdy + solDOFDs[2]*dsdy + solDOFDt[2]*dtdy;
1212  const su2double drwy = solDOFDr[3]*drdy + solDOFDs[3]*dsdy + solDOFDt[3]*dtdy;
1213 
1214  const su2double drhodz = solDOFDr[0]*drdz + solDOFDs[0]*dsdz + solDOFDt[0]*dtdz;
1215  const su2double druz = solDOFDr[1]*drdz + solDOFDs[1]*dsdz + solDOFDt[1]*dtdz;
1216  const su2double drvz = solDOFDr[2]*drdz + solDOFDs[2]*dsdz + solDOFDt[2]*dtdz;
1217  const su2double drwz = solDOFDr[3]*drdz + solDOFDs[3]*dsdz + solDOFDt[3]*dtdz;
1218 
1219  /*--- Compute the Cartesian gradients of the velocities. ---*/
1220  const su2double dudx = DensityInv*(drux - u*drhodx);
1221  const su2double dudy = DensityInv*(druy - u*drhody);
1222  const su2double dudz = DensityInv*(druz - u*drhodz);
1223 
1224  const su2double dvdx = DensityInv*(drvx - v*drhodx);
1225  const su2double dvdy = DensityInv*(drvy - v*drhody);
1226  const su2double dvdz = DensityInv*(drvz - v*drhodz);
1227 
1228  const su2double dwdx = DensityInv*(drwx - w*drhodx);
1229  const su2double dwdy = DensityInv*(drwy - w*drhody);
1230  const su2double dwdz = DensityInv*(drwz - w*drhodz);
1231 
1232  /* Compute the eddy viscosity. */
1233  const su2double dist = volElem[lInd].wallDistanceSolDOFs[i];
1234  muTurb = SGSModel->ComputeEddyViscosity_3D(solDOF[0], dudx, dudy, dudz,
1235  dvdx, dvdy, dvdz, dwdx, dwdy,
1236  dwdz, lenScale, dist);
1237  }
1238 
1239  /*--- Determine the viscous spectral radius. ---*/
1240  const su2double mu = muLam + muTurb;
1241  const su2double kOverCv = muLam*factHeatFlux_Lam
1242  + muTurb*factHeatFlux_Turb;
1243  const su2double factHeatFlux = kOverCv/mu;
1244 
1245  const su2double radVisc = DensityInv*mu*max(radOverNuTerm, factHeatFlux);
1246 
1247  /* Update the maximum value of the viscous spectral radius. */
1248  radViscMax = max(radViscMax, radVisc);
1249  }
1250 
1251  /*--- Compute the time step for the element and update the minimum and
1252  maximum value. Take the factor for time accurate local time
1253  stepping into account for the minimum and maximum. ---*/
1254  const su2double dtInv = lenScaleInv*(sqrt(charVel2Max) + radViscMax*lenScaleInv);
1255 
1256  VecDeltaTime[lInd] = CFL/dtInv;
1257 
1258  const su2double dtEff = volElem[lInd].factTimeLevel*VecDeltaTime[lInd];
1259  Min_Delta_Time = min(Min_Delta_Time, dtEff);
1260  Max_Delta_Time = max(Max_Delta_Time, dtEff);
1261  }
1262 
1263  break;
1264  }
1265  }
1266 
1267  /* Update the value of the counter l to the end index of the
1268  current chunk. */
1269  l = lEnd;
1270  }
1271  }
1272  else {
1273 
1274  /*--- Incompressible solver. ---*/
1275 
1276  SU2_MPI::Error("Incompressible solver not implemented yet", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1277  }
1278 
1279  /*--- Compute the max and the min dt (in parallel). Note that we only
1280  do this for steady calculations if the high verbosity is set, but we
1281  always perform the reduction for unsteady calculations where the CFL
1282  limit is used to set the global time step. ---*/
1283  if ((config->GetComm_Level() == COMM_FULL) || time_stepping) {
1284 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1285  su2double rbuf_time = Min_Delta_Time;
1286  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&rbuf_time, &Min_Delta_Time, 1, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MIN, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
1287 
1288  rbuf_time = Max_Delta_Time;
1289  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&rbuf_time, &Max_Delta_Time, 1, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MAX, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
1290 #endif
1291  }
1292 
1293  /*--- For explicit time stepping with an unsteady CFL imposed, use the
1294  minimum delta time of the entire mesh. As Min_Delta_Time is scaled to
1295  the time step of the largest time level, a correction must be used
1296  for the time level when time accurate local time stepping is used. ---*/
1297  if (time_stepping) {
1298  for(unsigned long l=0; l<nVolElemOwned; ++l)
1299  VecDeltaTime[l] = Min_Delta_Time/volElem[l].factTimeLevel;
1300 
1301  config->SetDelta_UnstTimeND(Min_Delta_Time);
1302  }
1303  }
1304 }
1305 
1306 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::ADER_DG_AliasedPredictorResidual_2D(CConfig *config,
1307  CVolumeElementFEM *elem,
1308  const su2double *sol,
1309  const unsigned short nSimul,
1310  const unsigned short NPad,
1311  su2double *res,
1312  su2double *work) {
1313  /* Constant factor present in the heat flux vector. */
1314  const su2double factHeatFlux_Lam = Gamma/Prandtl_Lam;
1315  const su2double factHeatFlux_Turb = Gamma/Prandtl_Turb;
1316 
1317  /* Get the necessary information from the standard element. */
1318  const unsigned short ind = elem->indStandardElement;
1319  const unsigned short nInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
1320  const unsigned short nDOFs = elem->nDOFsSol;
1321  const su2double *matBasisInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetMatBasisFunctionsIntegration();
1322  const su2double *matDerBasisInt = matBasisInt + nDOFs*nInt;
1323  const su2double *matDerBasisSolDOFs = standardElementsSol[ind].GetMatDerBasisFunctionsSolDOFs();
1324  const su2double *basisFunctionsIntTrans = standardElementsSol[ind].GetBasisFunctionsIntegrationTrans();
1325  const su2double *weights = standardElementsSol[ind].GetWeightsIntegration();
1326 
1327  unsigned short nPoly = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNPoly();
1328  if(nPoly == 0) nPoly = 1;
1329 
1330  /* Compute the length scale of the current element for the LES. */
1331  const su2double lenScale = elem->lenScale/nPoly;
1332 
1333  /* Set the pointers for fluxes in the DOFs, the gradient of the fluxes in
1334  the integration points, the gradient of the solution in the DOFs and the
1335  divergence of the fluxes in the integration points. Note that some pointers
1336  point to the same physical location. This is because this memory can be
1337  used for different purposes. */
1338  su2double *fluxXDOF = work;
1339  su2double *fluxYDOF = fluxXDOF + NPad*nDOFs;
1340  su2double *gradFluxXInt = fluxYDOF + NPad*nDOFs;
1341  su2double *gradFluxYInt = gradFluxXInt + nDim*NPad*nInt;
1342  su2double *gradSolDOFs = gradFluxXInt;
1343  su2double *divFlux = work;
1344 
1345  /* Determine the offset between the r-derivatives and s-derivatives of the
1346  fluxes in the integration points and the offset between the r-derivatives
1347  and s-derivatives of the solution in the DOFs. */
1348  const unsigned short offDerivSol = NPad*nDOFs;
1349  const unsigned short offDerivFluxes = NPad*nInt;
1350 
1351  /* Store the number of metric points per integration point for readability. */
1352  const unsigned short nMetricPerPoint = 5; /* nDim*nDim + 1. */
1353 
1354  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1355  /*--- Construct the Cartesian fluxes in the DOFs. ---*/
1356  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1357 
1358  /* Compute the derivatives of the solution variables w.r.t. the parametric
1359  coordinates in the DOFs. */
1360  blasFunctions->gemm(nDOFs*nDim, NPad, nDOFs, matDerBasisSolDOFs, sol, gradSolDOFs, config);
1361 
1362  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
1363  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
1364 
1365  /*--- Loop over the DOFs to compute the Cartesian fluxes in the DOFs. ---*/
1366  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFs; ++i) {
1367 
1368  /* Set the pointers for the solution, its gradients and the fluxes
1369  for this DOF. */
1370  const unsigned short offDOF = i*NPad + simul*nVar;
1371  const su2double *solDOF = sol + offDOF;
1372  const su2double *solDOFDr = gradSolDOFs + offDOF;
1373  const su2double *solDOFDs = solDOFDr + offDerivSol;
1374  su2double *fluxX = fluxXDOF + offDOF;
1375  su2double *fluxY = fluxYDOF + offDOF;
1376 
1377  /* Set the pointer to the grid velocities at the location of the
1378  solution DOFS. THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL
1379  MOTION IS SPECIFIED, THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME
1380  INTEGRATION POINT MUST BE TAKEN. */
1381  const su2double *gridVel = elem->gridVelocitiesSolDOFs.data() + 2*i; /* nDim*i. */
1382 
1383  /* Compute the true value of the metric terms in this DOF. Note that in
1384  metricTerms the metric terms scaled by the Jacobian are stored. THIS
1385  IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED, THE
1386  DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST BE TAKEN. */
1387  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTermsSolDOFs.data()
1388  + i*nMetricPerPoint;
1389  const su2double JacInv = 1.0/metricTerms[0];
1390 
1391  const su2double drdx = JacInv*metricTerms[1];
1392  const su2double drdy = JacInv*metricTerms[2];
1393 
1394  const su2double dsdx = JacInv*metricTerms[3];
1395  const su2double dsdy = JacInv*metricTerms[4];
1396 
1397  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the independent solution variables
1398  from the gradients in parametric coordinates and the metric terms. */
1399  const su2double drhodx = solDOFDr[0]*drdx + solDOFDs[0]*dsdx;
1400  const su2double drudx = solDOFDr[1]*drdx + solDOFDs[1]*dsdx;
1401  const su2double drvdx = solDOFDr[2]*drdx + solDOFDs[2]*dsdx;
1402  const su2double drEdx = solDOFDr[3]*drdx + solDOFDs[3]*dsdx;
1403 
1404  const su2double drhody = solDOFDr[0]*drdy + solDOFDs[0]*dsdy;
1405  const su2double drudy = solDOFDr[1]*drdy + solDOFDs[1]*dsdy;
1406  const su2double drvdy = solDOFDr[2]*drdy + solDOFDs[2]*dsdy;
1407  const su2double drEdy = solDOFDr[3]*drdy + solDOFDs[3]*dsdy;
1408 
1409  /* Compute the velocities, pressure and laminar viscosity in this DOF. */
1410  const su2double DensityInv = 1.0/solDOF[0];
1411  const su2double u = DensityInv*solDOF[1];
1412  const su2double v = DensityInv*solDOF[2];
1413  const su2double TotalEnergy = DensityInv*solDOF[3];
1414  const su2double StaticEnergy = TotalEnergy - 0.5*(u*u + v*v);
1415 
1416  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(solDOF[0], StaticEnergy);
1417  const su2double Pressure = FluidModel->GetPressure();
1418  const su2double ViscosityLam = FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
1419 
1420  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the velocities and static energy. */
1421  const su2double dudx = DensityInv*(drudx - u*drhodx);
1422  const su2double dvdx = DensityInv*(drvdx - v*drhodx);
1423  const su2double dudy = DensityInv*(drudy - u*drhody);
1424  const su2double dvdy = DensityInv*(drvdy - v*drhody);
1425 
1426  const su2double dedx = DensityInv*(drEdx - TotalEnergy*drhodx) - u*dudx - v*dvdx;
1427  const su2double dedy = DensityInv*(drEdy - TotalEnergy*drhody) - u*dudy - v*dvdy;
1428 
1429  /* Compute the eddy viscosity, if needed, and the total viscosity. */
1430  su2double ViscosityTurb = 0.0;
1431  if( SGSModelUsed )
1432  ViscosityTurb = SGSModel->ComputeEddyViscosity_2D(solDOF[0], dudx, dudy,
1433  dvdx, dvdy, lenScale,
1434  elem->wallDistanceSolDOFs[i]);
1435  const su2double Viscosity = ViscosityLam + ViscosityTurb;
1436 
1437  /* Compute the total thermal conductivity divided by Cv. */
1438  const su2double kOverCv = ViscosityLam *factHeatFlux_Lam
1439  + ViscosityTurb*factHeatFlux_Turb;
1440 
1441  /* Set the value of the second viscosity and compute the divergence
1442  term in the viscous normal stresses. */
1443  const su2double lambda = -TWO3*Viscosity;
1444  const su2double lamDivTerm = lambda*(dudx + dvdy);
1445 
1446  /* Compute the viscous stress tensor. */
1447  const su2double tauxx = 2.0*Viscosity*dudx + lamDivTerm;
1448  const su2double tauyy = 2.0*Viscosity*dvdy + lamDivTerm;
1449  const su2double tauxy = Viscosity*(dudy + dvdx);
1450 
1451  /* The Cartesian fluxes in the x-direction. */
1452  const su2double uRel = u - gridVel[0];
1453  fluxX[0] = solDOF[0]*uRel;
1454  fluxX[1] = solDOF[1]*uRel + Pressure - tauxx;
1455  fluxX[2] = solDOF[2]*uRel - tauxy;
1456  fluxX[3] = solDOF[3]*uRel + Pressure*u - kOverCv*dedx - u*tauxx - v*tauxy;;
1457 
1458  /* The Cartesian fluxes in the y-direction. */
1459  const su2double vRel = v - gridVel[1];
1460  fluxY[0] = solDOF[0]*vRel;
1461  fluxY[1] = solDOF[1]*vRel - tauxy;
1462  fluxY[2] = solDOF[2]*vRel + Pressure - tauyy;
1463  fluxY[3] = solDOF[3]*vRel + Pressure*v - kOverCv*dedy - u*tauxy - v*tauyy;
1464  }
1465  }
1466 
1467  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1468  /*--- Compute the derivatives of the Cartesian fluxes w.r.t. the ---*/
1469  /*--- parametric coordinates in the integration points. ---*/
1470  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1471 
1472  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*nDim, NPad, nDOFs, matDerBasisInt, fluxXDOF, gradFluxXInt, config);
1473  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*nDim, NPad, nDOFs, matDerBasisInt, fluxYDOF, gradFluxYInt, config);
1474 
1475  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1476  /*--- Compute the divergence of the fluxes in the integration points, ---*/
1477  /*--- multiplied by the integration weight. ---*/
1478  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1479 
1480  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
1481  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
1482 
1483  /*--- Loop over the integration points of the element. ---*/
1484  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
1485 
1486  /* Set the pointers for this integration point. */
1487  const unsigned short offInt = i*NPad + simul*nVar;
1488  const su2double *gradFluxXDr = gradFluxXInt + offInt;
1489  const su2double *gradFluxXDs = gradFluxXDr + offDerivFluxes;
1490  const su2double *gradFluxYDr = gradFluxYInt + offInt;
1491  const su2double *gradFluxYDs = gradFluxYDr + offDerivFluxes;
1492  su2double *divFluxInt = divFlux + offInt;
1493 
1494  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point.
1495  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
1496  THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST
1497  BE TAKEN. */
1498  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTerms.data() + i*nMetricPerPoint;
1499 
1500  /* Compute the metric terms multiplied by the integration weight. Note that the
1501  first term in the metric terms is the Jacobian. */
1502  const su2double wDrdx = weights[i]*metricTerms[1];
1503  const su2double wDrdy = weights[i]*metricTerms[2];
1504 
1505  const su2double wDsdx = weights[i]*metricTerms[3];
1506  const su2double wDsdy = weights[i]*metricTerms[4];
1507 
1508  /* Compute the divergence of the fluxes, multiplied by the
1509  integration weight. */
1510  divFluxInt[0] = gradFluxXDr[0]*wDrdx + gradFluxXDs[0]*wDsdx
1511  + gradFluxYDr[0]*wDrdy + gradFluxYDs[0]*wDsdy;
1512  divFluxInt[1] = gradFluxXDr[1]*wDrdx + gradFluxXDs[1]*wDsdx
1513  + gradFluxYDr[1]*wDrdy + gradFluxYDs[1]*wDsdy;
1514  divFluxInt[2] = gradFluxXDr[2]*wDrdx + gradFluxXDs[2]*wDsdx
1515  + gradFluxYDr[2]*wDrdy + gradFluxYDs[2]*wDsdy;
1516  divFluxInt[3] = gradFluxXDr[3]*wDrdx + gradFluxXDs[3]*wDsdx
1517  + gradFluxYDr[3]*wDrdy + gradFluxYDs[3]*wDsdy;
1518  }
1519  }
1520 
1521  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1522  /*--- Add the body force to the divergence of the fluxes, if such a ---*/
1523  /*--- force is present. ---*/
1524  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1525 
1526  if( config->GetBody_Force() ) {
1527 
1528  /* Easier storage of the body force. */
1529  const su2double *body_force_vector = config->GetBody_Force_Vector();
1530 
1531  /* Compute the solution in the integration points of the element.
1532  Use gradFluxYInt to store this solution. */
1533  su2double *solInt = gradFluxYInt;
1534 
1535  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt, NPad, nDOFs, matBasisInt, sol, solInt, config);
1536 
1537  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
1538  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
1539 
1540  /*--- Loop over the integration points of the element. ---*/
1541  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
1542 
1543  /* Set the pointers for this integration point. */
1544  const unsigned short offInt = i*NPad + simul*nVar;
1545  const su2double *solThisInt = solInt + offInt;
1546  su2double *divFluxInt = divFlux + offInt;
1547 
1548  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point.
1549  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
1550  THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST
1551  BE TAKEN. */
1552  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTerms.data() + i*nMetricPerPoint;
1553 
1554  /* Compute the velocities. */
1555  const su2double rhoInv = 1.0/solThisInt[0];
1556  const su2double u = solThisInt[1]*rhoInv;
1557  const su2double v = solThisInt[2]*rhoInv;
1558 
1559  /* Add the body force to the flux divergence for the momentum and energy
1560  equation. Note that the source terms are multiplied with minus the
1561  integration weight in order to be consistent with the formulation of
1562  the residual. Also note that for the energy source term the absolute
1563  velocity must be taken and not the relative. */
1564  const su2double weightJac = weights[i]*metricTerms[0];
1565 
1566  divFluxInt[1] -= weightJac*body_force_vector[0];
1567  divFluxInt[2] -= weightJac*body_force_vector[1];
1568  divFluxInt[3] -= weightJac*(u*body_force_vector[0] + v*body_force_vector[1]);
1569  }
1570  }
1571  }
1572 
1573  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1574  /*--- Add the source terms of the manufactured solution to the divergence---*/
1575  /*--- of the fluxes, if a manufactured solution is used. ---*/
1576  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1577 
1578  if( VerificationSolution ) {
1579  if( VerificationSolution->IsManufacturedSolution() ) {
1580 
1581  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
1582  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
1583 
1584  /*--- Loop over the integration points of the element. ---*/
1585  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
1586 
1587  /* Set the pointers for this integration point. */
1588  const unsigned short offInt = i*NPad + simul*nVar;
1589  su2double *divFluxInt = divFlux + offInt;
1590 
1591  /* Set the pointer to the coordinates in this integration point.
1592  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
1593  THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST
1594  BE TAKEN. */
1595  const su2double *coor = elem->coorIntegrationPoints.data() + i*nDim;
1596 
1597  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point.
1598  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
1599  THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST
1600  BE TAKEN. */
1601  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTerms.data() + i*nMetricPerPoint;
1602  const su2double weightJac = weights[i]*metricTerms[0];
1603 
1604  /* Compute the source terms of the manufactured solution.
1605  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. FOR AN ACTUAL TIME ACCURATE
1606  SIMULATION THE CORRECT TIME MUST BE GIVEN TO THIS FUNCTION. */
1607  su2double sourceMan[4];
1608  VerificationSolution->GetMMSSourceTerm(coor, 0.0, sourceMan);
1609 
1610  /* Add the source terms to the flux divergence. Note that the source
1611  terms are multiplied with minus the integration weight in order
1612  to be consistent with the formulation of the residual. */
1613  divFluxInt[0] -= weightJac*sourceMan[0];
1614  divFluxInt[1] -= weightJac*sourceMan[1];
1615  divFluxInt[2] -= weightJac*sourceMan[2];
1616  divFluxInt[3] -= weightJac*sourceMan[3];
1617  }
1618  }
1619  }
1620  }
1621 
1622  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1623  /*--- Compute the residual in the DOFs, which is the matrix product of ---*/
1624  /*--- basisFunctionsIntTrans and divFlux. ---*/
1625  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1626 
1627  blasFunctions->gemm(nDOFs, NPad, nInt, basisFunctionsIntTrans, divFlux, res, config);
1628 }
1629 
1630 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::ADER_DG_AliasedPredictorResidual_3D(CConfig *config,
1631  CVolumeElementFEM *elem,
1632  const su2double *sol,
1633  const unsigned short nSimul,
1634  const unsigned short NPad,
1635  su2double *res,
1636  su2double *work) {
1637  /* Constant factor present in the heat flux vector. */
1638  const su2double factHeatFlux_Lam = Gamma/Prandtl_Lam;
1639  const su2double factHeatFlux_Turb = Gamma/Prandtl_Turb;
1640 
1641  /*--- Get the necessary information from the standard element. ---*/
1642  const unsigned short ind = elem->indStandardElement;
1643  const unsigned short nInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
1644  const unsigned short nDOFs = elem->nDOFsSol;
1645  const su2double *matBasisInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetMatBasisFunctionsIntegration();
1646  const su2double *matDerBasisInt = matBasisInt + nDOFs*nInt;
1647  const su2double *matDerBasisSolDOFs = standardElementsSol[ind].GetMatDerBasisFunctionsSolDOFs();
1648  const su2double *basisFunctionsIntTrans = standardElementsSol[ind].GetBasisFunctionsIntegrationTrans();
1649  const su2double *weights = standardElementsSol[ind].GetWeightsIntegration();
1650 
1651  unsigned short nPoly = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNPoly();
1652  if(nPoly == 0) nPoly = 1;
1653 
1654  /* Compute the length scale of the current element for the LES. */
1655  const su2double lenScale = elem->lenScale/nPoly;
1656 
1657  /* Set the pointers for fluxes in the DOFs, the gradient of the fluxes in
1658  the integration points, the gradient of the solution in the DOFs and the
1659  divergence of the fluxes in the integration points. Note that some pointers
1660  point to the same physical location. This is because this memory can be
1661  used for different purposes. */
1662  su2double *fluxXDOF = work;
1663  su2double *fluxYDOF = fluxXDOF + NPad*nDOFs;
1664  su2double *fluxZDOF = fluxYDOF + NPad*nDOFs;
1665  su2double *gradFluxXInt = fluxZDOF + NPad*nDOFs;
1666  su2double *gradFluxYInt = gradFluxXInt + nDim*NPad*nInt;
1667  su2double *gradFluxZInt = gradFluxYInt + nDim*NPad*nInt;
1668  su2double *gradSolDOFs = gradFluxXInt;
1669  su2double *divFlux = work;
1670 
1671  /* Determine the offset between the r-derivatives and s-derivatives of the
1672  fluxes in the integration points and the offset between the r-derivatives
1673  and s-derivatives of the solution in the DOFs. */
1674  const unsigned short offDerivSol = NPad*nDOFs;
1675  const unsigned short offDerivFluxes = NPad*nInt;
1676 
1677  /* Store the number of metric points per integration point/DOF for readability. */
1678  const unsigned short nMetricPerPoint = 10; /* nDim*nDim + 1. */
1679 
1680  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1681  /*--- Construct the Cartesian fluxes in the DOFs. ---*/
1682  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1683 
1684  /* Compute the derivatives of the solution variables w.r.t. the parametric
1685  coordinates in the DOFs. */
1686  blasFunctions->gemm(nDOFs*nDim, NPad, nDOFs, matDerBasisSolDOFs, sol, gradSolDOFs, config);
1687 
1688  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
1689  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
1690 
1691  /*--- Loop over the DOFs to compute the Cartesian fluxes in the DOFs. ---*/
1692  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFs; ++i) {
1693 
1694  /* Set the pointers for the solution, its gradients and the fluxes
1695  for this DOF. */
1696  const unsigned short offDOF = i*NPad + simul*nVar;
1697  const su2double *solDOF = sol + offDOF;
1698  const su2double *solDOFDr = gradSolDOFs + offDOF;
1699  const su2double *solDOFDs = solDOFDr + offDerivSol;
1700  const su2double *solDOFDt = solDOFDs + offDerivSol;
1701  su2double *fluxX = fluxXDOF + offDOF;
1702  su2double *fluxY = fluxYDOF + offDOF;
1703  su2double *fluxZ = fluxZDOF + offDOF;
1704 
1705  /* Set the pointer to the grid velocities at the location of the
1706  solution DOFS. THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL
1707  MOTION IS SPECIFIED, THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME
1708  INTEGRATION POINT MUST BE TAKEN. */
1709  const su2double *gridVel = elem->gridVelocitiesSolDOFs.data() + 3*i; /* nDim*i. */
1710 
1711  /* Compute the true value of the metric terms in this DOF. Note that in
1712  metricTerms the metric terms scaled by the Jacobian are stored. THIS
1713  IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED, THE
1714  DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST BE TAKEN. */
1715  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTermsSolDOFs.data()
1716  + i*nMetricPerPoint;
1717  const su2double JacInv = 1.0/metricTerms[0];
1718 
1719  const su2double drdx = JacInv*metricTerms[1];
1720  const su2double drdy = JacInv*metricTerms[2];
1721  const su2double drdz = JacInv*metricTerms[3];
1722 
1723  const su2double dsdx = JacInv*metricTerms[4];
1724  const su2double dsdy = JacInv*metricTerms[5];
1725  const su2double dsdz = JacInv*metricTerms[6];
1726 
1727  const su2double dtdx = JacInv*metricTerms[7];
1728  const su2double dtdy = JacInv*metricTerms[8];
1729  const su2double dtdz = JacInv*metricTerms[9];
1730 
1731  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the independent solution variables
1732  from the gradients in parametric coordinates and the metric terms. */
1733  const su2double drhodx = solDOFDr[0]*drdx + solDOFDs[0]*dsdx + solDOFDt[0]*dtdx;
1734  const su2double drudx = solDOFDr[1]*drdx + solDOFDs[1]*dsdx + solDOFDt[1]*dtdx;
1735  const su2double drvdx = solDOFDr[2]*drdx + solDOFDs[2]*dsdx + solDOFDt[2]*dtdx;
1736  const su2double drwdx = solDOFDr[3]*drdx + solDOFDs[3]*dsdx + solDOFDt[3]*dtdx;
1737  const su2double drEdx = solDOFDr[4]*drdx + solDOFDs[4]*dsdx + solDOFDt[4]*dtdx;
1738 
1739  const su2double drhody = solDOFDr[0]*drdy + solDOFDs[0]*dsdy + solDOFDt[0]*dtdy;
1740  const su2double drudy = solDOFDr[1]*drdy + solDOFDs[1]*dsdy + solDOFDt[1]*dtdy;
1741  const su2double drvdy = solDOFDr[2]*drdy + solDOFDs[2]*dsdy + solDOFDt[2]*dtdy;
1742  const su2double drwdy = solDOFDr[3]*drdy + solDOFDs[3]*dsdy + solDOFDt[3]*dtdy;
1743  const su2double drEdy = solDOFDr[4]*drdy + solDOFDs[4]*dsdy + solDOFDt[4]*dtdy;
1744 
1745  const su2double drhodz = solDOFDr[0]*drdz + solDOFDs[0]*dsdz + solDOFDt[0]*dtdz;
1746  const su2double drudz = solDOFDr[1]*drdz + solDOFDs[1]*dsdz + solDOFDt[1]*dtdz;
1747  const su2double drvdz = solDOFDr[2]*drdz + solDOFDs[2]*dsdz + solDOFDt[2]*dtdz;
1748  const su2double drwdz = solDOFDr[3]*drdz + solDOFDs[3]*dsdz + solDOFDt[3]*dtdz;
1749  const su2double drEdz = solDOFDr[4]*drdz + solDOFDs[4]*dsdz + solDOFDt[4]*dtdz;
1750 
1751  /* Compute the velocities, pressure and laminar viscosity in this DOF. */
1752  const su2double DensityInv = 1.0/solDOF[0];
1753  const su2double u = DensityInv*solDOF[1];
1754  const su2double v = DensityInv*solDOF[2];
1755  const su2double w = DensityInv*solDOF[3];
1756  const su2double TotalEnergy = DensityInv*solDOF[4];
1757  const su2double StaticEnergy = TotalEnergy - 0.5*(u*u + v*v + w*w);
1758 
1759  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(solDOF[0], StaticEnergy);
