1760  const su2double Pressure = FluidModel->GetPressure();
1761  const su2double ViscosityLam = FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
1762 
1763  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the velocities and static energy. */
1764  const su2double dudx = DensityInv*(drudx - u*drhodx);
1765  const su2double dudy = DensityInv*(drudy - u*drhody);
1766  const su2double dudz = DensityInv*(drudz - u*drhodz);
1767 
1768  const su2double dvdx = DensityInv*(drvdx - v*drhodx);
1769  const su2double dvdy = DensityInv*(drvdy - v*drhody);
1770  const su2double dvdz = DensityInv*(drvdz - v*drhodz);
1771 
1772  const su2double dwdx = DensityInv*(drwdx - w*drhodx);
1773  const su2double dwdy = DensityInv*(drwdy - w*drhody);
1774  const su2double dwdz = DensityInv*(drwdz - w*drhodz);
1775 
1776  const su2double dedx = DensityInv*(drEdx - TotalEnergy*drhodx) - u*dudx - v*dvdx - w*dwdx;
1777  const su2double dedy = DensityInv*(drEdy - TotalEnergy*drhody) - u*dudy - v*dvdy - w*dwdy;
1778  const su2double dedz = DensityInv*(drEdz - TotalEnergy*drhodz) - u*dudz - v*dvdz - w*dwdz;
1779 
1780  /* Compute the eddy viscosity, if needed, and the total viscosity. */
1781  su2double ViscosityTurb = 0.0;
1782  if( SGSModelUsed )
1783  ViscosityTurb = SGSModel->ComputeEddyViscosity_3D(solDOF[0], dudx, dudy, dudz,
1784  dvdx, dvdy, dvdz, dwdx,
1785  dwdy, dwdz, lenScale,
1786  elem->wallDistanceSolDOFs[i]);
1787  const su2double Viscosity = ViscosityLam + ViscosityTurb;
1788 
1789  /* Compute the total thermal conductivity divided by Cv. */
1790  const su2double kOverCv = ViscosityLam *factHeatFlux_Lam
1791  + ViscosityTurb*factHeatFlux_Turb;
1792 
1793  /* Set the value of the second viscosity and compute the divergence
1794  term in the viscous normal stresses. */
1795  const su2double lambda = -TWO3*Viscosity;
1796  const su2double lamDivTerm = lambda*(dudx + dvdy + dwdz);
1797 
1798  /* Compute the viscous stress tensor. */
1799  const su2double tauxx = 2.0*Viscosity*dudx + lamDivTerm;
1800  const su2double tauyy = 2.0*Viscosity*dvdy + lamDivTerm;
1801  const su2double tauzz = 2.0*Viscosity*dwdz + lamDivTerm;
1802 
1803  const su2double tauxy = Viscosity*(dudy + dvdx);
1804  const su2double tauxz = Viscosity*(dudz + dwdx);
1805  const su2double tauyz = Viscosity*(dvdz + dwdy);
1806 
1807  /* The Cartesian fluxes in the x-direction. */
1808  const su2double uRel = u - gridVel[0];
1809  fluxX[0] = solDOF[0]*uRel;
1810  fluxX[1] = solDOF[1]*uRel + Pressure - tauxx;
1811  fluxX[2] = solDOF[2]*uRel - tauxy;
1812  fluxX[3] = solDOF[3]*uRel - tauxz;
1813  fluxX[4] = solDOF[4]*uRel + Pressure*u - kOverCv*dedx - u*tauxx - v*tauxy - w*tauxz;
1814 
1815  /* The Cartesian fluxes in the y-direction. */
1816  const su2double vRel = v - gridVel[1];
1817  fluxY[0] = solDOF[0]*vRel;
1818  fluxY[1] = solDOF[1]*vRel - tauxy;
1819  fluxY[2] = solDOF[2]*vRel + Pressure - tauyy;
1820  fluxY[3] = solDOF[3]*vRel - tauyz;
1821  fluxY[4] = solDOF[4]*vRel + Pressure*v - kOverCv*dedy - u*tauxy - v*tauyy - w*tauyz;
1822 
1823  /* The Cartesian fluxes in the z-direction. */
1824  const su2double wRel = w - gridVel[2];
1825  fluxZ[0] = solDOF[0]*wRel;
1826  fluxZ[1] = solDOF[1]*wRel - tauxz;
1827  fluxZ[2] = solDOF[2]*wRel - tauyz;
1828  fluxZ[3] = solDOF[3]*wRel + Pressure - tauzz;
1829  fluxZ[4] = solDOF[4]*wRel + Pressure*w - kOverCv*dedz - u*tauxz - v*tauyz - w*tauzz;
1830  }
1831  }
1832 
1833  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1834  /*--- Compute the derivatives of the Cartesian fluxes w.r.t. the ---*/
1835  /*--- parametric coordinates in the integration points. ---*/
1836  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1837 
1838  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*nDim, NPad, nDOFs, matDerBasisInt, fluxXDOF, gradFluxXInt, config);
1839  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*nDim, NPad, nDOFs, matDerBasisInt, fluxYDOF, gradFluxYInt, config);
1840  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*nDim, NPad, nDOFs, matDerBasisInt, fluxZDOF, gradFluxZInt, config);
1841 
1842  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1843  /*--- Compute the divergence of the fluxes in the integration points, ---*/
1844  /*--- multiplied by the integration weight. ---*/
1845  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1846 
1847  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
1848  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
1849 
1850  /*--- Loop over the integration points of the element. ---*/
1851  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
1852 
1853  /* Set the pointers for this integration point. */
1854  const unsigned short offInt = i*NPad + simul*nVar;
1855  const su2double *gradFluxXDr = gradFluxXInt + offInt;
1856  const su2double *gradFluxXDs = gradFluxXDr + offDerivFluxes;
1857  const su2double *gradFluxXDt = gradFluxXDs + offDerivFluxes;
1858  const su2double *gradFluxYDr = gradFluxYInt + offInt;
1859  const su2double *gradFluxYDs = gradFluxYDr + offDerivFluxes;
1860  const su2double *gradFluxYDt = gradFluxYDs + offDerivFluxes;
1861  const su2double *gradFluxZDr = gradFluxZInt + offInt;
1862  const su2double *gradFluxZDs = gradFluxZDr + offDerivFluxes;
1863  const su2double *gradFluxZDt = gradFluxZDs + offDerivFluxes;
1864  su2double *divFluxInt = divFlux + offInt;
1865 
1866  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point.
1867  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
1868  THE DATA FOR THIS SPATIAL INTEGRATION POINT FOR THE CURRENT TIME
1869  INTEGRATION POINT MUST BE TAKEN. */
1870  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTerms.data() + i*nMetricPerPoint;
1871 
1872  /* Compute the metric terms multiplied by the integration weight. Note that the
1873  first term in the metric terms is the Jacobian. */
1874  const su2double wDrdx = weights[i]*metricTerms[1];
1875  const su2double wDrdy = weights[i]*metricTerms[2];
1876  const su2double wDrdz = weights[i]*metricTerms[3];
1877 
1878  const su2double wDsdx = weights[i]*metricTerms[4];
1879  const su2double wDsdy = weights[i]*metricTerms[5];
1880  const su2double wDsdz = weights[i]*metricTerms[6];
1881 
1882  const su2double wDtdx = weights[i]*metricTerms[7];
1883  const su2double wDtdy = weights[i]*metricTerms[8];
1884  const su2double wDtdz = weights[i]*metricTerms[9];
1885 
1886  /* Compute the divergence of the fluxes, multiplied by the integration weight. */
1887  divFluxInt[0] = gradFluxXDr[0]*wDrdx + gradFluxXDs[0]*wDsdx + gradFluxXDt[0]*wDtdx
1888  + gradFluxYDr[0]*wDrdy + gradFluxYDs[0]*wDsdy + gradFluxYDt[0]*wDtdy
1889  + gradFluxZDr[0]*wDrdz + gradFluxZDs[0]*wDsdz + gradFluxZDt[0]*wDtdz;
1890  divFluxInt[1] = gradFluxXDr[1]*wDrdx + gradFluxXDs[1]*wDsdx + gradFluxXDt[1]*wDtdx
1891  + gradFluxYDr[1]*wDrdy + gradFluxYDs[1]*wDsdy + gradFluxYDt[1]*wDtdy
1892  + gradFluxZDr[1]*wDrdz + gradFluxZDs[1]*wDsdz + gradFluxZDt[1]*wDtdz;
1893  divFluxInt[2] = gradFluxXDr[2]*wDrdx + gradFluxXDs[2]*wDsdx + gradFluxXDt[2]*wDtdx
1894  + gradFluxYDr[2]*wDrdy + gradFluxYDs[2]*wDsdy + gradFluxYDt[2]*wDtdy
1895  + gradFluxZDr[2]*wDrdz + gradFluxZDs[2]*wDsdz + gradFluxZDt[2]*wDtdz;
1896  divFluxInt[3] = gradFluxXDr[3]*wDrdx + gradFluxXDs[3]*wDsdx + gradFluxXDt[3]*wDtdx
1897  + gradFluxYDr[3]*wDrdy + gradFluxYDs[3]*wDsdy + gradFluxYDt[3]*wDtdy
1898  + gradFluxZDr[3]*wDrdz + gradFluxZDs[3]*wDsdz + gradFluxZDt[3]*wDtdz;
1899  divFluxInt[4] = gradFluxXDr[4]*wDrdx + gradFluxXDs[4]*wDsdx + gradFluxXDt[4]*wDtdx
1900  + gradFluxYDr[4]*wDrdy + gradFluxYDs[4]*wDsdy + gradFluxYDt[4]*wDtdy
1901  + gradFluxZDr[4]*wDrdz + gradFluxZDs[4]*wDsdz + gradFluxZDt[4]*wDtdz;
1902  }
1903  }
1904 
1905  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1906  /*--- Add the body force to the divergence of the fluxes, if such a ---*/
1907  /*--- force is present. ---*/
1908  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1909 
1910  if( config->GetBody_Force() ) {
1911 
1912  /* Easier storage of the body force. */
1913  const su2double *body_force_vector = config->GetBody_Force_Vector();
1914 
1915  /* Compute the solution in the integration points of the element.
1916  Use gradFluxYInt to store this solution. */
1917  su2double *solInt = gradFluxYInt;
1918 
1919  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt, NPad, nDOFs, matBasisInt, sol, solInt, config);
1920 
1921  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
1922  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
1923 
1924  /*--- Loop over the integration points of the element. ---*/
1925  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
1926 
1927  /* Set the pointers for this integration point. */
1928  const unsigned short offInt = i*NPad + simul*nVar;
1929  const su2double *solThisInt = solInt + offInt;
1930  su2double *divFluxInt = divFlux + offInt;
1931 
1932  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point.
1933  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
1934  THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST
1935  BE TAKEN. */
1936  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTerms.data() + i*nMetricPerPoint;
1937 
1938  /* Compute the velocities. */
1939  const su2double rhoInv = 1.0/solThisInt[0];
1940  const su2double u = solThisInt[1]*rhoInv;
1941  const su2double v = solThisInt[2]*rhoInv;
1942  const su2double w = solThisInt[3]*rhoInv;
1943 
1944  /* Add the body force to the flux divergence for the momentum and energy
1945  equation. Note that the source terms are multiplied with minus the
1946  integration weight in order to be consistent with the formulation of
1947  the residual. Also note that for the energy source term the absolute
1948  velocity must be taken and not the relative. */
1949  const su2double weightJac = weights[i]*metricTerms[0];
1950 
1951  divFluxInt[1] -= weightJac*body_force_vector[0];
1952  divFluxInt[2] -= weightJac*body_force_vector[1];
1953  divFluxInt[3] -= weightJac*body_force_vector[2];
1954  divFluxInt[4] -= weightJac*(u*body_force_vector[0] + v*body_force_vector[1]
1955  + w*body_force_vector[2]);
1956  }
1957  }
1958  }
1959 
1960  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1961  /*--- Add the source terms of the manufactured solution to the divergence---*/
1962  /*--- of the fluxes, if a manufactured solution is used. ---*/
1963  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1964 
1965  if( VerificationSolution ) {
1966  if( VerificationSolution->IsManufacturedSolution() ) {
1967 
1968  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
1969  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
1970 
1971  /*--- Loop over the integration points of the element. ---*/
1972  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
1973 
1974  /* Set the pointers for this integration point. */
1975  const unsigned short offInt = i*NPad + simul*nVar;
1976  su2double *divFluxInt = divFlux + offInt;
1977 
1978  /* Set the pointer to the coordinates in this integration point.
1979  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
1980  THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST
1981  BE TAKEN. */
1982  const su2double *coor = elem->coorIntegrationPoints.data() + i*nDim;
1983 
1984  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point.
1985  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
1986  THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST
1987  BE TAKEN. */
1988  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTerms.data() + i*nMetricPerPoint;
1989  const su2double weightJac = weights[i]*metricTerms[0];
1990 
1991  /* Compute the source terms of the manufactured solution.
1992  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. FOR AN ACTUAL TIME ACCURATE
1993  SIMULATION THE CORRECT TIME MUST BE GIVEN TO THIS FUNCTION. */
1994  su2double sourceMan[5];
1995  VerificationSolution->GetMMSSourceTerm(coor, 0.0, sourceMan);
1996 
1997  /* Add the source terms to the flux divergence. Note that the source
1998  terms are multiplied with minus the integration weight in order
1999  to be consistent with the formulation of the residual. */
2000  divFluxInt[0] -= weightJac*sourceMan[0];
2001  divFluxInt[1] -= weightJac*sourceMan[1];
2002  divFluxInt[2] -= weightJac*sourceMan[2];
2003  divFluxInt[3] -= weightJac*sourceMan[3];
2004  divFluxInt[4] -= weightJac*sourceMan[4];
2005  }
2006  }
2007  }
2008  }
2009 
2010  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2011  /*--- Compute the residual in the DOFs, which is the matrix product of ---*/
2012  /*--- basisFunctionsIntTrans and divFlux. ---*/
2013  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2014 
2015  blasFunctions->gemm(nDOFs, NPad, nInt, basisFunctionsIntTrans, divFlux, res, config);
2016 }
2017 
2018 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::ADER_DG_NonAliasedPredictorResidual_2D(CConfig *config,
2019  CVolumeElementFEM *elem,
2020  const su2double *sol,
2021  const unsigned short nSimul,
2022  const unsigned short NPad,
2023  su2double *res,
2024  su2double *work) {
2025 
2026  /* Constant factor present in the heat flux vector, the inverse of
2027  the specific heat at constant volume and ratio lambdaOverMu. */
2028  const su2double factHeatFlux_Lam = Gamma/Prandtl_Lam;
2029  const su2double factHeatFlux_Turb = Gamma/Prandtl_Turb;
2030  const su2double Gas_Constant = config->GetGas_ConstantND();
2031  const su2double CvInv = Gamma_Minus_One/Gas_Constant;
2032  const su2double lambdaOverMu = -TWO3;
2033 
2034  /*--- Get the necessary information from the standard element. ---*/
2035  const unsigned short ind = elem->indStandardElement;
2036  const unsigned short nInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
2037  const unsigned short nDOFs = elem->nDOFsSol;
2038  const su2double *matBasisInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetMatBasisFunctionsIntegration();
2039  const su2double *mat2ndDerBasisInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetMat2ndDerBasisFunctionsInt();
2040  const su2double *basisFunctionsIntTrans = standardElementsSol[ind].GetBasisFunctionsIntegrationTrans();
2041  const su2double *weights = standardElementsSol[ind].GetWeightsIntegration();
2042 
2043  unsigned short nPoly = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNPoly();
2044  if(nPoly == 0) nPoly = 1;
2045 
2046  /* Check if a body force is present and set it accordingly. */
2047  su2double bodyForceX = 0.0, bodyForceY = 0.0;
2048  if( config->GetBody_Force() ) {
2049  const su2double *body_force_vector = config->GetBody_Force_Vector();
2050  bodyForceX = body_force_vector[0];
2051  bodyForceY = body_force_vector[1];
2052  }
2053 
2054  /* Compute the length scale of the current element for the LES. */
2055  const su2double lenScale = elem->lenScale/nPoly;
2056 
2057  /* Set the pointers for solAndGradInt and divFlux to work. The same array
2058  can be used for both help arrays. */
2059  su2double *solAndGradInt = work;
2060  su2double *divFlux = work;
2061 
2062  /* Determine the offset between the solution variables and the r-derivatives,
2063  which is also the offset between the r- and s-derivatives in the
2064  integration points. */
2065  const unsigned short offDerivInt = NPad*nInt;
2066 
2067  /* Set the pointer for the second derivatives such that they are stored
2068  after the first derivatives. */
2069  su2double *secDerSol = solAndGradInt + 3*NPad*nInt; /*(nDim+1)*NPad*nInt. */
2070 
2071  /* Store the number of metric points per integration point for readability. */
2072  const unsigned short nMetricPerPoint = 5; /* nDim*nDim + 1. */
2073 
2074  /* Store the number of additional metric points per integration point, which
2075  are needed to compute the second derivatives. These terms take the
2076  non-constant metric into account. */
2077  const unsigned short nMetric2ndDerPerPoint = 6; /*nDim*(nDim + nDim*(nDim-1)/2). */
2078 
2079  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2080  /*--- Interpolate the solution variables to the integration points and ---*/
2081  /*--- also determine the first and second derivatives of these variables ---*/
2082  /*--- in the integration points. All derivatives are w.r.t. the ---*/
2083  /*--- parametric coordinates. ---*/
2084  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2085 
2086  /* Compute the solution and the derivatives w.r.t. the parametric coordinates
2087  in the integration points. The first argument is nInt*(nDim+1). */
2088  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*3, NPad, nDOFs, matBasisInt, sol, solAndGradInt, config);
2089 
2090  /* Compute the second derivatives w.r.t. the parametric coordinates
2091  in the integration points. */
2092  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*3, NPad, nDOFs, mat2ndDerBasisInt, sol, secDerSol, config);
2093 
2094  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2095  /*--- Compute the divergence of viscous fluxes, multiplied by the ---*/
2096  /*--- integration weight in the integration points of the element. ---*/
2097  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2098 
2099  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
2100  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
2101 
2102  /*--- Loop over the integration points. ---*/
2103  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
2104 
2105  /* Easier storage of the locations where the solution and the gradient
2106  data of this integration point start. */
2107  const unsigned short offInt = NPad*i + simul*nVar;
2108  const su2double *sol = solAndGradInt + offInt;
2109  const su2double *solDr = sol + offDerivInt;
2110  const su2double *solDs = solDr + offDerivInt;
2111 
2112  /* Easier storage of the locations where the second derivatives are
2113  stored for this integration point. */
2114  const su2double *solDrDr = secDerSol + offInt;
2115  const su2double *solDrDs = solDrDr + offDerivInt;
2116  const su2double *solDsDs = solDrDs + offDerivInt;
2117 
2118  /* Compute the velocities, pressure and total enthalpy
2119  in this integration point. */
2120  const su2double rho = sol[0];
2121  const su2double ru = sol[1];
2122  const su2double rv = sol[2];
2123  const su2double rE = sol[3];
2124 
2125  const su2double rhoInv = 1.0/rho;
2126  const su2double u = rhoInv*ru;
2127  const su2double v = rhoInv*rv;
2128  const su2double kinEnergy = 0.5*(u*u + v*v);
2129  const su2double TotalEnergy = rhoInv*rE;
2130  const su2double StaticEnergy = TotalEnergy - kinEnergy;
2131 
2132  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(rho, StaticEnergy);
2133  const su2double Pressure = FluidModel->GetPressure();
2134  const su2double Htot = rhoInv*(rE + Pressure);
2135 
2136  /* Compute the laminar viscosity and its derivative w.r.t. temperature. */
2137  const su2double ViscosityLam = FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
2138  const su2double dViscLamdT = FluidModel->GetdmudT_rho();
2139 
2140  /* Set the pointer to the grid velocities in this integration point.
2141  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
2142  THE DATA FOR THIS SPATIAL INTEGRATION POINT FOR THE CURRENT TIME
2143  INTEGRATION POINT MUST BE TAKEN. */
2144  const su2double *gridVel = elem->gridVelocities.data() + 2*i; /* nDim*i. */
2145 
2146  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point.
2147  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
2148  THE DATA FOR THIS SPATIAL INTEGRATION POINT FOR THE CURRENT TIME
2149  INTEGRATION POINT MUST BE TAKEN. */
2150  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTerms.data() + i*nMetricPerPoint;
2151 
2152  /* Compute the true metric terms. Note in metricTerms the actual metric
2153  terms multiplied by the Jacobian are stored. */
2154  const su2double Jac = metricTerms[0];
2155  const su2double JacInv = 1.0/Jac;
2156 
2157  const su2double drdx = JacInv*metricTerms[1];
2158  const su2double drdy = JacInv*metricTerms[2];
2159  const su2double dsdx = JacInv*metricTerms[3];
2160  const su2double dsdy = JacInv*metricTerms[4];
2161 
2162  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the independent solution
2163  variables from the gradients in parametric coordinates and the
2164  metric terms in this integration point. */
2165  const su2double drhodx = solDr[0]*drdx + solDs[0]*dsdx;
2166  const su2double drudx = solDr[1]*drdx + solDs[1]*dsdx;
2167  const su2double drvdx = solDr[2]*drdx + solDs[2]*dsdx;
2168  const su2double drEdx = solDr[3]*drdx + solDs[3]*dsdx;
2169 
2170  const su2double drhody = solDr[0]*drdy + solDs[0]*dsdy;
2171  const su2double drudy = solDr[1]*drdy + solDs[1]*dsdy;
2172  const su2double drvdy = solDr[2]*drdy + solDs[2]*dsdy;
2173  const su2double drEdy = solDr[3]*drdy + solDs[3]*dsdy;
2174 
2175  /* Pointer to the necessary additional metric terms needed to compute
2176  the Cartesian second derivatives for this integration point.
2177  HIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
2178  THE DATA FOR THIS SPATIAL INTEGRATION POINT FOR THE CURRENT TIME
2179  INTEGRATION POINT MUST BE TAKEN. */
2180  const su2double *metricTerms2ndDer = elem->metricTerms2ndDer.data()
2181  + i*nMetric2ndDerPerPoint;
2182 
2183  /* Compute the Cartesian second derivatives of the independent solution
2184  variables from the gradients and second derivatives in parametric
2185  coordinates and the metric terms and its derivatives w.r.t. the
2186  parametric coordinates. */
2187  const su2double d2rhodxdx = solDrDr[0]*drdx*drdx + solDsDs[0]*dsdx*dsdx
2188  + 2.0*solDrDs[0]*drdx*dsdx
2189  + solDr[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[0] + solDs[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[1];
2190  const su2double d2rudxdx = solDrDr[1]*drdx*drdx + solDsDs[1]*dsdx*dsdx
2191  + 2.0*solDrDs[1]*drdx*dsdx
2192  + solDr[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[0] + solDs[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[1];
2193  const su2double d2rvdxdx = solDrDr[2]*drdx*drdx + solDsDs[2]*dsdx*dsdx
2194  + 2.0*solDrDs[2]*drdx*dsdx
2195  + solDr[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[0] + solDs[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[1];
2196  const su2double d2rEdxdx = solDrDr[3]*drdx*drdx + solDsDs[3]*dsdx*dsdx
2197  + 2.0*solDrDs[3]*drdx*dsdx
2198  + solDr[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[0] + solDs[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[1];
2199 
2200  const su2double d2rhodydy = solDrDr[0]*drdy*drdy + solDsDs[0]*dsdy*dsdy
2201  + 2.0*solDrDs[0]*drdy*dsdy
2202  + solDr[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[4] + solDs[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[5];
2203  const su2double d2rudydy = solDrDr[1]*drdy*drdy + solDsDs[1]*dsdy*dsdy
2204  + 2.0*solDrDs[1]*drdy*dsdy
2205  + solDr[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[4] + solDs[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[5];
2206  const su2double d2rvdydy = solDrDr[2]*drdy*drdy + solDsDs[2]*dsdy*dsdy
2207  + 2.0*solDrDs[2]*drdy*dsdy
2208  + solDr[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[4] + solDs[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[5];
2209  const su2double d2rEdydy = solDrDr[3]*drdy*drdy + solDsDs[3]*dsdy*dsdy
2210  + 2.0*solDrDs[3]*drdy*dsdy
2211  + solDr[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[4] + solDs[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[5];
2212 
2213  const su2double d2rhodxdy = solDrDr[0]*drdx*drdy + solDsDs[0]*dsdx*dsdy
2214  + solDrDs[0]*(drdx*dsdy + dsdx*drdy)
2215  + solDr[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[2] + solDs[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[3];
2216  const su2double d2rudxdy = solDrDr[1]*drdx*drdy + solDsDs[1]*dsdx*dsdy
2217  + solDrDs[1]*(drdx*dsdy + dsdx*drdy)
2218  + solDr[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[2] + solDs[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[3];
2219  const su2double d2rvdxdy = solDrDr[2]*drdx*drdy + solDsDs[2]*dsdx*dsdy
2220  + solDrDs[2]*(drdx*dsdy + dsdx*drdy)
2221  + solDr[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[2] + solDs[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[3];
2222 
2223  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the pressure, velocity components,
2224  static energy and dynamic viscosity. */
2225  const su2double dpdx = Gamma_Minus_One*(drEdx + kinEnergy*drhodx
2226  - u*drudx - v*drvdx);
2227  const su2double dpdy = Gamma_Minus_One*(drEdy + kinEnergy*drhody
2228  - u*drudy - v*drvdy);
2229 
2230  const su2double dudx = rhoInv*(drudx - u*drhodx);
2231  const su2double dudy = rhoInv*(drudy - u*drhody);
2232  const su2double dvdx = rhoInv*(drvdx - v*drhodx);
2233  const su2double dvdy = rhoInv*(drvdy - v*drhody);
2234 
2235  const su2double dedx = rhoInv*(drEdx - TotalEnergy*drhodx) - u*dudx - v*dvdx;
2236  const su2double dedy = rhoInv*(drEdy - TotalEnergy*drhody) - u*dudy - v*dvdy;
2237 
2238  const su2double dViscLamdx = CvInv*dedx*dViscLamdT;
2239  const su2double dViscLamdy = CvInv*dedy*dViscLamdT;
2240 
2241  /* Compute the second derivatives of the velocity components. */
2242  const su2double d2udxdx = rhoInv*(d2rudxdx - u*d2rhodxdx
2243  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhodx*(u*drhodx - drudx));
2244  const su2double d2udydy = rhoInv*(d2rudydy - u*d2rhodydy
2245  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhody*(u*drhody - drudy));
2246  const su2double d2udxdy = rhoInv*(d2rudxdy - u*d2rhodxdy
2247  + rhoInv*(drhodx*(u*drhody - drudy)
2248  + drhody*(u*drhodx - drudx)));
2249 
2250  const su2double d2vdxdx = rhoInv*(d2rvdxdx - v*d2rhodxdx
2251  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhodx*(v*drhodx - drvdx));
2252  const su2double d2vdydy = rhoInv*(d2rvdydy - v*d2rhodydy
2253  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhody*(v*drhody - drvdy));
2254  const su2double d2vdxdy = rhoInv*(d2rvdxdy - v*d2rhodxdy
2255  + rhoInv*(drhodx*(v*drhody - drvdy)
2256  + drhody*(v*drhodx - drvdx)));
2257 
2258  /* Compute the second derivatives of the static energy. Note that this
2259  term appears in the heat flux and therefore only the pure second
2260  derivatives are needed. Hence, the cross-derivatives are omitted. */
2261  const su2double d2edxdx = rhoInv*(d2rEdxdx - TotalEnergy*d2rhodxdx
2262  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhodx*(TotalEnergy*drhodx - drEdx))
2263  - u*d2udxdx - dudx*dudx - v*d2vdxdx - dvdx*dvdx;
2264  const su2double d2edydy = rhoInv*(d2rEdydy - TotalEnergy*d2rhodydy
2265  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhody*(TotalEnergy*drhody - drEdy))
2266  - u*d2udydy - dudy*dudy - v*d2vdydy - dvdy*dvdy;
2267 
2268  /* If an SGS model is used the eddy viscosity and its spatial
2269  derivatives must be computed. */
2270  su2double ViscosityTurb = 0.0;
2271  su2double dViscTurbdx = 0.0, dViscTurbdy = 0.0;
2272 
2273  if( SGSModelUsed ) {
2274  const su2double dist = elem->wallDistance[i];
2275  ViscosityTurb = SGSModel->ComputeEddyViscosity_2D(rho, dudx, dudy, dvdx,
2276  dvdy, lenScale, dist);
2277 
2278  SGSModel->ComputeGradEddyViscosity_2D(rho, drhodx, drhody, dudx, dudy,
2279  dvdx, dvdy, d2udxdx, d2udydy, d2udxdy,
2280  d2vdxdx, d2vdydy, d2vdxdy, lenScale,
2281  dist, dViscTurbdx, dViscTurbdy);
2282  }
2283 
2284  /* Compute the total viscosity, the total heat conductivity and their
2285  gradients. Note that the heat conductivity is divided by the Cv,
2286  because gradients of internal energy are computed and not temperature. */
2287  const su2double Viscosity = ViscosityLam + ViscosityTurb;
2288  const su2double kOverCv = ViscosityLam *factHeatFlux_Lam
2289  + ViscosityTurb*factHeatFlux_Turb;
2290 
2291  const su2double dViscDx = dViscLamdx + dViscTurbdx;
2292  const su2double dViscDy = dViscLamdy + dViscTurbdy;
2293 
2294  const su2double dkOverCvdx = dViscLamdx *factHeatFlux_Lam
2295  + dViscTurbdx*factHeatFlux_Turb;
2296  const su2double dkOverCvdy = dViscLamdy *factHeatFlux_Lam
2297  + dViscTurbdy*factHeatFlux_Turb;
2298 
2299  /* Abbreviations, which make it easier to compute the divergence term. */
2300  const su2double abv1 = drudx + drvdy;
2301  const su2double abv2 = u*drhodx + v*drhody;
2302  const su2double abv3 = u*(drEdx + dpdx) + v*(drEdy + dpdy);
2303  const su2double abv4 = dudx + dvdy;
2304 
2305  /* Compute the divergence of the grid velocity.
2306  SET TO ZERO FOR NOW. THIS IS NOT CORRECT!!!!. */
2307  const su2double divGridVel = 0.0;
2308 
2309  /* Set the pointer to store the divergence terms for this integration
2310  point and compute these terms, multiplied by the integration weight
2311  and Jacobian. */
2312  const su2double weightJac = weights[i]*Jac;
2313  su2double *divFluxInt = divFlux + offInt;
2314 
2315  divFluxInt[0] = weightJac*(abv1 - rho*divGridVel
2316  - gridVel[0]*drhodx - gridVel[1]*drhody);
2317  divFluxInt[1] = weightJac*(dpdx + u*(abv1-abv2) - lambdaOverMu*abv4*dViscDx
2318  + u*drudx + v*drudy
2319  - lambdaOverMu*Viscosity*(d2udxdx + d2vdxdy)
2320  - Viscosity*(2.0*d2udxdx + d2udydy + d2vdxdy)
2321  - 2.0*dViscDx*dudx - dViscDy*(dudy+dvdx)
2322  - ru*divGridVel
2323  - gridVel[0]*drudx - gridVel[1]*drudy);
2324  divFluxInt[2] = weightJac*(dpdy + v*(abv1-abv2) - lambdaOverMu*abv4*dViscDy
2325  + u*drvdx + v*drvdy
2326  - lambdaOverMu*Viscosity*(d2udxdy + d2vdydy)
2327  - Viscosity*(2.0*d2vdydy + d2vdxdx + d2udxdy)
2328  - dViscDx*(dudy + dvdx) - 2.0*dViscDy*dvdy
2329  - rv*divGridVel
2330  - gridVel[0]*drvdx - gridVel[1]*drvdy);
2331  divFluxInt[3] = weightJac*(abv3 + Htot*(abv1 - abv2)
2332  - abv4*lambdaOverMu*(Viscosity*abv4 + u*dViscDx + v*dViscDy)
2333  - dkOverCvdx*dedx - dkOverCvdy*dedy - kOverCv*(d2edxdx + d2edydy)
2334  - (Viscosity*dudx + u*dViscDx)*2.0*dudx
2335  - (Viscosity*dvdy + v*dViscDy)*2.0*dvdy
2336  - (Viscosity*dudy + u*dViscDy + Viscosity*dvdx + v*dViscDx)*(dudy + dvdx)
2337  - Viscosity*u*(d2udxdx+d2udydy + (1.0+lambdaOverMu)*(d2udxdx+d2vdxdy))
2338  - Viscosity*v*(d2vdxdx+d2vdydy + (1.0+lambdaOverMu)*(d2udxdy+d2vdydy))
2339  - rE*divGridVel
2340  - gridVel[0]*drEdx - gridVel[1]*drEdy);
2341 
2342  /* Add the body force to the flux divergence for the momentum and energy
2343  equation. Note that the source terms are multiplied with minus the
2344  integration weight in order to be consistent with the formulation of
2345  the residual. Also note that for the energy source term the absolute
2346  velocity must be taken and not the relative. */
2347  divFluxInt[1] -= weightJac*bodyForceX;
2348  divFluxInt[2] -= weightJac*bodyForceY;
2349  divFluxInt[3] -= weightJac*(u*bodyForceX + v*bodyForceY);
2350  }
2351  }
2352 
2353  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2354  /*--- Add the source terms of the manufactured solution to the divergence---*/
2355  /*--- of the fluxes, if a manufactured solution is used. ---*/
2356  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2357 
2358  if( VerificationSolution ) {
2359  if( VerificationSolution->IsManufacturedSolution() ) {
2360 
2361  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
2362  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
2363 
2364  /*--- Loop over the integration points of the element. ---*/
2365  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
2366 
2367  /* Set the pointers for this integration point. */
2368  const unsigned short offInt = i*NPad + simul*nVar;
2369  su2double *divFluxInt = divFlux + offInt;
2370 
2371  /* Set the pointer to the coordinates in this integration point.
2372  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
2373  THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST
2374  BE TAKEN. */
2375  const su2double *coor = elem->coorIntegrationPoints.data() + i*nDim;
2376 
2377  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point.
2378  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
2379  THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST
2380  BE TAKEN. */
2381  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTerms.data() + i*nMetricPerPoint;
2382  const su2double weightJac = weights[i]*metricTerms[0];
2383 
2384  /* Compute the source terms of the manufactured solution.
2385  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. FOR AN ACTUAL TIME ACCURATE
2386  SIMULATION THE CORRECT TIME MUST BE GIVEN TO THIS FUNCTION. */
2387  su2double sourceMan[4];
2388  VerificationSolution->GetMMSSourceTerm(coor, 0.0, sourceMan);
2389 
2390  /* Add the source terms to the flux divergence. Note that the source
2391  terms are multiplied with minus the integration weight in order
2392  to be consistent with the formulation of the residual. */
2393  divFluxInt[0] -= weightJac*sourceMan[0];
2394  divFluxInt[1] -= weightJac*sourceMan[1];
2395  divFluxInt[2] -= weightJac*sourceMan[2];
2396  divFluxInt[3] -= weightJac*sourceMan[3];
2397  }
2398  }
2399  }
2400  }
2401 
2402  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2403  /*--- Compute the residual in the DOFs, which is the matrix product of ---*/
2404  /*--- basisFunctionsIntTrans and divFlux. ---*/
2405  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2406 
2407  blasFunctions->gemm(nDOFs, NPad, nInt, basisFunctionsIntTrans, divFlux, res, config);
2408 }
2409 
2410 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::ADER_DG_NonAliasedPredictorResidual_3D(CConfig *config,
2411  CVolumeElementFEM *elem,
2412  const su2double *sol,
2413  const unsigned short nSimul,
2414  const unsigned short NPad,
2415  su2double *res,
2416  su2double *work) {
2417 
2418  /* Constant factor present in the heat flux vector, the inverse of
2419  the specific heat at constant volume and ratio lambdaOverMu. */
2420  const su2double factHeatFlux_Lam = Gamma/Prandtl_Lam;
2421  const su2double factHeatFlux_Turb = Gamma/Prandtl_Turb;
2422  const su2double Gas_Constant = config->GetGas_ConstantND();
2423  const su2double CvInv = Gamma_Minus_One/Gas_Constant;
2424  const su2double lambdaOverMu = -TWO3;
2425 
2426  /*--- Get the necessary information from the standard element. ---*/
2427  const unsigned short ind = elem->indStandardElement;
2428  const unsigned short nInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
2429  const unsigned short nDOFs = elem->nDOFsSol;
2430  const su2double *matBasisInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetMatBasisFunctionsIntegration();
2431  const su2double *mat2ndDerBasisInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetMat2ndDerBasisFunctionsInt();
2432  const su2double *basisFunctionsIntTrans = standardElementsSol[ind].GetBasisFunctionsIntegrationTrans();
2433  const su2double *weights = standardElementsSol[ind].GetWeightsIntegration();
2434 
2435  unsigned short nPoly = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNPoly();
2436  if(nPoly == 0) nPoly = 1;
2437 
2438  /* Check if a body force is present and set it accordingly. */
2439  su2double bodyForceX = 0.0, bodyForceY = 0.0, bodyForceZ = 0.0;
2440  if( config->GetBody_Force() ) {
2441  const su2double *body_force_vector = config->GetBody_Force_Vector();
2442  bodyForceX = body_force_vector[0];
2443  bodyForceY = body_force_vector[1];
2444  bodyForceZ = body_force_vector[2];
2445  }
2446 
2447  /* Compute the length scale of the current element for the LES. */
2448  const su2double lenScale = elem->lenScale/nPoly;
2449 
2450  /* Set the pointers for solAndGradInt and divFlux to work. The same array
2451  can be used for both help arrays. */
2452  su2double *solAndGradInt = work;
2453  su2double *divFlux = work;
2454 
2455  /* Determine the offset between the solution variables and the r-derivatives,
2456  which is also the offset between the r- and s-derivatives in the
2457  integration points. */
2458  const unsigned short offDerivInt = NPad*nInt;
2459 
2460  /* Set the pointer for the second derivatives such that they are stored
2461  after the first derivatives. */
2462  su2double *secDerSol = solAndGradInt + 4*NPad*nInt; /*(nDim+1)*NPad*nInt. */
2463 
2464  /* Store the number of metric points per integration point for readability. */
2465  const unsigned short nMetricPerPoint = 10; /* nDim*nDim + 1. */
2466 
2467  /* Store the number of additional metric points per integration point, which
2468  are needed to compute the second derivatives. These terms take the
2469  non-constant metric into account. */
2470  const unsigned short nMetric2ndDerPerPoint = 18; /*nDim*(nDim + nDim*(nDim-1)/2). */
2471 
2472  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2473  /*--- Interpolate the solution variables to the integration points and ---*/
2474  /*--- also determine the first and second derivatives of these variables ---*/
2475  /*--- in the integration points. All derivatives are w.r.t. the ---*/
2476  /*--- parametric coordinates. ---*/
2477  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2478 
2479  /* Compute the solution and the derivatives w.r.t. the parametric coordinates
2480  in the integration points. The first argument is nInt*(nDim+1). */
2481  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*4, NPad, nDOFs, matBasisInt, sol, solAndGradInt, config);
2482 
2483  /* Compute the second derivatives w.r.t. the parametric coordinates
2484  in the integration points. */
2485  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*6, NPad, nDOFs, mat2ndDerBasisInt, sol, secDerSol, config);
2486 
2487  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2488  /*--- Compute the divergence of viscous fluxes, multiplied by the ---*/
2489  /*--- integration weight in the integration points of the element. ---*/
2490  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2491 
2492  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
2493  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
2494 
2495  /*--- Loop over the integration points. ---*/
2496  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
2497 
2498  /* Easier storage of the locations where the solution and the gradient
2499  data of this integration point start. */
2500  const unsigned short offInt = NPad*i + simul*nVar;
2501  const su2double *sol = solAndGradInt + offInt;
2502  const su2double *solDr = sol + offDerivInt;
2503  const su2double *solDs = solDr + offDerivInt;
2504  const su2double *solDt = solDs + offDerivInt;
2505 
2506  /* Easier storage of the locations where the second derivatives are
2507  stored for this integration point. */
2508  const su2double *solDrDr = secDerSol + offInt;
2509  const su2double *solDrDs = solDrDr + offDerivInt;
2510  const su2double *solDsDs = solDrDs + offDerivInt;
2511  const su2double *solDrDt = solDsDs + offDerivInt;
2512  const su2double *solDsDt = solDrDt + offDerivInt;
2513  const su2double *solDtDt = solDsDt + offDerivInt;
2514 
2515  /* Compute the velocities, pressure and total enthalpy
2516  in this integration point. */
2517  const su2double rho = sol[0];
2518  const su2double ru = sol[1];
2519  const su2double rv = sol[2];
2520  const su2double rw = sol[3];
2521  const su2double rE = sol[4];
2522 
2523  const su2double rhoInv = 1.0/rho;
2524  const su2double u = rhoInv*ru;
2525  const su2double v = rhoInv*rv;
2526  const su2double w = rhoInv*rw;
2527  const su2double kinEnergy = 0.5*(u*u + v*v + w*w);
2528  const su2double TotalEnergy = rhoInv*rE;
2529  const su2double StaticEnergy = TotalEnergy - kinEnergy;
2530 
2531  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(rho, StaticEnergy);
2532  const su2double Pressure = FluidModel->GetPressure();
2533  const su2double Htot = rhoInv*(rE + Pressure);
2534 
2535  /* Compute the laminar viscosity and its derivative w.r.t. temperature. */
2536  const su2double ViscosityLam = FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
2537  const su2double dViscLamdT = FluidModel->GetdmudT_rho();
2538 
2539  /* Set the pointer to the grid velocities in this integration point.
2540  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
2541  THE DATA FOR THIS SPATIAL INTEGRATION POINT FOR THE CURRENT TIME
2542  INTEGRATION POINT MUST BE TAKEN. */
2543  const su2double *gridVel = elem->gridVelocities.data() + 3*i; /* nDim*i. */
2544 
2545  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point.
2546  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
2547  THE DATA FOR THIS SPATIAL INTEGRATION POINT FOR THE CURRENT TIME
2548  INTEGRATION POINT MUST BE TAKEN. */
2549  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTerms.data() + i*nMetricPerPoint;
2550 
2551  /* Compute the true metric terms. Note in metricTerms the actual metric
2552  terms multiplied by the Jacobian are stored. */
2553  const su2double Jac = metricTerms[0];
2554  const su2double JacInv = 1.0/Jac;
2555 
2556  const su2double drdx = JacInv*metricTerms[1];
2557  const su2double drdy = JacInv*metricTerms[2];
2558  const su2double drdz = JacInv*metricTerms[3];
2559 
2560  const su2double dsdx = JacInv*metricTerms[4];
2561  const su2double dsdy = JacInv*metricTerms[5];
2562  const su2double dsdz = JacInv*metricTerms[6];
2563 
2564  const su2double dtdx = JacInv*metricTerms[7];
2565  const su2double dtdy = JacInv*metricTerms[8];
2566  const su2double dtdz = JacInv*metricTerms[9];
2567 
2568  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the independent solution
2569  variables from the gradients in parametric coordinates and the
2570  metric terms in this integration point. */
2571  const su2double drhodx = solDr[0]*drdx + solDs[0]*dsdx + solDt[0]*dtdx;
2572  const su2double drudx = solDr[1]*drdx + solDs[1]*dsdx + solDt[1]*dtdx;
2573  const su2double drvdx = solDr[2]*drdx + solDs[2]*dsdx + solDt[2]*dtdx;
2574  const su2double drwdx = solDr[3]*drdx + solDs[3]*dsdx + solDt[3]*dtdx;
2575  const su2double drEdx = solDr[4]*drdx + solDs[4]*dsdx + solDt[4]*dtdx;
2576 
2577  const su2double drhody = solDr[0]*drdy + solDs[0]*dsdy + solDt[0]*dtdy;
2578  const su2double drudy = solDr[1]*drdy + solDs[1]*dsdy + solDt[1]*dtdy;
2579  const su2double drvdy = solDr[2]*drdy + solDs[2]*dsdy + solDt[2]*dtdy;
2580  const su2double drwdy = solDr[3]*drdy + solDs[3]*dsdy + solDt[3]*dtdy;
2581  const su2double drEdy = solDr[4]*drdy + solDs[4]*dsdy + solDt[4]*dtdy;
2582 
2583  const su2double drhodz = solDr[0]*drdz + solDs[0]*dsdz + solDt[0]*dtdz;
2584  const su2double drudz = solDr[1]*drdz + solDs[1]*dsdz + solDt[1]*dtdz;
2585  const su2double drvdz = solDr[2]*drdz + solDs[2]*dsdz + solDt[2]*dtdz;
2586  const su2double drwdz = solDr[3]*drdz + solDs[3]*dsdz + solDt[3]*dtdz;
2587  const su2double drEdz = solDr[4]*drdz + solDs[4]*dsdz + solDt[4]*dtdz;
2588 
2589  /* Pointer to the necessary additional metric terms needed to compute
2590  the Cartesian second derivatives for this integration point.
2591  HIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
2592  THE DATA FOR THIS SPATIAL INTEGRATION POINT FOR THE CURRENT TIME
2593  INTEGRATION POINT MUST BE TAKEN. */
2594  const su2double *metricTerms2ndDer = elem->metricTerms2ndDer.data()
2595  + i*nMetric2ndDerPerPoint;
2596 
2597  /* Compute the Cartesian second derivatives of the independent solution
2598  variables from the gradients and second derivatives in parametric
2599  coordinates and the metric terms and its derivatives w.r.t. the
2600  parametric coordinates. */
2601  const su2double d2rhodxdx = solDrDr[0]*drdx*drdx + solDsDs[0]*dsdx*dsdx + solDtDt[0]*dtdx*dtdx
2602  + 2.0*(solDrDs[0]*drdx*dsdx + solDrDt[0]*drdx*dtdx + solDsDt[0]*dsdx*dtdx)
2603  + solDr[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[0] + solDs[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[1]
2604  + solDt[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[2];
2605  const su2double d2rudxdx = solDrDr[1]*drdx*drdx + solDsDs[1]*dsdx*dsdx + solDtDt[1]*dtdx*dtdx
2606  + 2.0*(solDrDs[1]*drdx*dsdx + solDrDt[1]*drdx*dtdx + solDsDt[1]*dsdx*dtdx)
2607  + solDr[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[0] + solDs[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[1]
2608  + solDt[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[2];
2609  const su2double d2rvdxdx = solDrDr[2]*drdx*drdx + solDsDs[2]*dsdx*dsdx + solDtDt[2]*dtdx*dtdx
2610  + 2.0*(solDrDs[2]*drdx*dsdx + solDrDt[2]*drdx*dtdx + solDsDt[2]*dsdx*dtdx)
2611  + solDr[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[0] + solDs[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[1]
2612  + solDt[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[2];
2613  const su2double d2rwdxdx = solDrDr[3]*drdx*drdx + solDsDs[3]*dsdx*dsdx + solDtDt[3]*dtdx*dtdx
2614  + 2.0*(solDrDs[3]*drdx*dsdx + solDrDt[3]*drdx*dtdx + solDsDt[3]*dsdx*dtdx)
2615  + solDr[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[0] + solDs[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[1]
2616  + solDt[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[2];
2617  const su2double d2rEdxdx = solDrDr[4]*drdx*drdx + solDsDs[4]*dsdx*dsdx + solDtDt[4]*dtdx*dtdx
2618  + 2.0*(solDrDs[4]*drdx*dsdx + solDrDt[4]*drdx*dtdx + solDsDt[4]*dsdx*dtdx)
2619  + solDr[4]*metricTerms2ndDer[0] + solDs[4]*metricTerms2ndDer[1]
2620  + solDt[4]*metricTerms2ndDer[2];
2621 
2622  const su2double d2rhodydy = solDrDr[0]*drdy*drdy + solDsDs[0]*dsdy*dsdy + solDtDt[0]*dtdy*dtdy
2623  + 2.0*(solDrDs[0]*drdy*dsdy + solDrDt[0]*drdy*dtdy + solDsDt[0]*dsdy*dtdy)
2624  + solDr[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[6] + solDs[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[7]
2625  + solDt[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[8];
2626  const su2double d2rudydy = solDrDr[1]*drdy*drdy + solDsDs[1]*dsdy*dsdy + solDtDt[1]*dtdy*dtdy
2627  + 2.0*(solDrDs[1]*drdy*dsdy + solDrDt[1]*drdy*dtdy + solDsDt[1]*dsdy*dtdy)
2628  + solDr[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[6] + solDs[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[7]
2629  + solDt[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[8];
2630  const su2double d2rvdydy = solDrDr[2]*drdy*drdy + solDsDs[2]*dsdy*dsdy + solDtDt[2]*dtdy*dtdy
2631  + 2.0*(solDrDs[2]*drdy*dsdy + solDrDt[2]*drdy*dtdy + solDsDt[2]*dsdy*dtdy)
2632  + solDr[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[6] + solDs[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[7]
2633  + solDt[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[8];
2634  const su2double d2rwdydy = solDrDr[3]*drdy*drdy + solDsDs[3]*dsdy*dsdy + solDtDt[3]*dtdy*dtdy
2635  + 2.0*(solDrDs[3]*drdy*dsdy + solDrDt[3]*drdy*dtdy + solDsDt[3]*dsdy*dtdy)
2636  + solDr[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[6] + solDs[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[7]
2637  + solDt[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[8];
2638  const su2double d2rEdydy = solDrDr[4]*drdy*drdy + solDsDs[4]*dsdy*dsdy + solDtDt[4]*dtdy*dtdy
2639  + 2.0*(solDrDs[4]*drdy*dsdy + solDrDt[4]*drdy*dtdy + solDsDt[4]*dsdy*dtdy)
2640  + solDr[4]*metricTerms2ndDer[6] + solDs[4]*metricTerms2ndDer[7]
2641  + solDt[4]*metricTerms2ndDer[8];
2642 
2643  const su2double d2rhodzdz = solDrDr[0]*drdz*drdz + solDsDs[0]*dsdz*dsdz + solDtDt[0]*dtdz*dtdz
2644  + 2.0*(solDrDs[0]*drdz*dsdz + solDrDt[0]*drdz*dtdz + solDsDt[0]*dsdz*dtdz)
2645  + solDr[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[15] + solDs[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[16]
2646  + solDt[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[17];
2647  const su2double d2rudzdz = solDrDr[1]*drdz*drdz + solDsDs[1]*dsdz*dsdz + solDtDt[1]*dtdz*dtdz
2648  + 2.0*(solDrDs[1]*drdz*dsdz + solDrDt[1]*drdz*dtdz + solDsDt[1]*dsdz*dtdz)
2649  + solDr[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[15] + solDs[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[16]
2650  + solDt[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[17];
2651  const su2double d2rvdzdz = solDrDr[2]*drdz*drdz + solDsDs[2]*dsdz*dsdz + solDtDt[2]*dtdz*dtdz
2652  + 2.0*(solDrDs[2]*drdz*dsdz + solDrDt[2]*drdz*dtdz + solDsDt[2]*dsdz*dtdz)
2653  + solDr[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[15] + solDs[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[16]
2654  + solDt[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[17];
2655  const su2double d2rwdzdz = solDrDr[3]*drdz*drdz + solDsDs[3]*dsdz*dsdz + solDtDt[3]*dtdz*dtdz
2656  + 2.0*(solDrDs[3]*drdz*dsdz + solDrDt[3]*drdz*dtdz + solDsDt[3]*dsdz*dtdz)
2657  + solDr[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[15] + solDs[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[16]
2658  + solDt[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[17];
2659  const su2double d2rEdzdz = solDrDr[4]*drdz*drdz + solDsDs[4]*dsdz*dsdz + solDtDt[4]*dtdz*dtdz
2660  + 2.0*(solDrDs[4]*drdz*dsdz + solDrDt[4]*drdz*dtdz + solDsDt[4]*dsdz*dtdz)
2661  + solDr[4]*metricTerms2ndDer[15] + solDs[4]*metricTerms2ndDer[16]
2662  + solDt[4]*metricTerms2ndDer[17];
2663 
2664  const su2double d2rhodxdy = solDrDr[0]*drdx*drdy + solDsDs[0]*dsdx*dsdy + solDtDt[0]*dtdx*dtdy
2665  + solDrDs[0]*(drdx*dsdy + dsdx*drdy) + solDrDt[0]*(drdx*dtdy + dtdx*drdy)
2666  + solDsDt[0]*(dsdx*dtdy + dtdx*dsdy) + solDr[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[3]
2667  + solDs[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[4] + solDt[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[5];
2668  const su2double d2rudxdy = solDrDr[1]*drdx*drdy + solDsDs[1]*dsdx*dsdy + solDtDt[1]*dtdx*dtdy
2669  + solDrDs[1]*(drdx*dsdy + dsdx*drdy) + solDrDt[1]*(drdx*dtdy + dtdx*drdy)
2670  + solDsDt[1]*(dsdx*dtdy + dtdx*dsdy) + solDr[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[3]
2671  + solDs[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[4] + solDt[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[5];
2672  const su2double d2rvdxdy = solDrDr[2]*drdx*drdy + solDsDs[2]*dsdx*dsdy + solDtDt[2]*dtdx*dtdy
2673  + solDrDs[2]*(drdx*dsdy + dsdx*drdy) + solDrDt[2]*(drdx*dtdy + dtdx*drdy)
2674  + solDsDt[2]*(dsdx*dtdy + dtdx*dsdy) + solDr[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[3]
2675  + solDs[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[4] + solDt[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[5];
2676  const su2double d2rwdxdy = solDrDr[3]*drdx*drdy + solDsDs[3]*dsdx*dsdy + solDtDt[3]*dtdx*dtdy
2677  + solDrDs[3]*(drdx*dsdy + dsdx*drdy) + solDrDt[3]*(drdx*dtdy + dtdx*drdy)
2678  + solDsDt[3]*(dsdx*dtdy + dtdx*dsdy) + solDr[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[3]
2679  + solDs[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[4] + solDt[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[5];
2680 
2681  const su2double d2rhodxdz = solDrDr[0]*drdx*drdz + solDsDs[0]*dsdx*dsdz + solDtDt[0]*dtdx*dtdz
2682  + solDrDs[0]*(drdx*dsdz + dsdx*drdz) + solDrDt[0]*(drdx*dtdz + dtdx*drdz)
2683  + solDsDt[0]*(dsdx*dtdz + dtdx*dsdz) + solDr[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[9]
2684  + solDs[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[10] + solDt[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[11];
2685  const su2double d2rudxdz = solDrDr[1]*drdx*drdz + solDsDs[1]*dsdx*dsdz + solDtDt[1]*dtdx*dtdz
2686  + solDrDs[1]*(drdx*dsdz + dsdx*drdz) + solDrDt[1]*(drdx*dtdz + dtdx*drdz)
2687  + solDsDt[1]*(dsdx*dtdz + dtdx*dsdz) + solDr[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[9]
2688  + solDs[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[10] + solDt[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[11];
2689  const su2double d2rvdxdz = solDrDr[2]*drdx*drdz + solDsDs[2]*dsdx*dsdz + solDtDt[2]*dtdx*dtdz
2690  + solDrDs[2]*(drdx*dsdz + dsdx*drdz) + solDrDt[2]*(drdx*dtdz + dtdx*drdz)
2691  + solDsDt[2]*(dsdx*dtdz + dtdx*dsdz) + solDr[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[9]
2692  + solDs[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[10] + solDt[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[11];
2693  const su2double d2rwdxdz = solDrDr[3]*drdx*drdz + solDsDs[3]*dsdx*dsdz + solDtDt[3]*dtdx*dtdz
2694  + solDrDs[3]*(drdx*dsdz + dsdx*drdz) + solDrDt[3]*(drdx*dtdz + dtdx*drdz)
2695  + solDsDt[3]*(dsdx*dtdz + dtdx*dsdz) + solDr[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[9]
2696  + solDs[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[10] + solDt[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[11];
2697 
2698  const su2double d2rhodydz = solDrDr[0]*drdy*drdz + solDsDs[0]*dsdy*dsdz + solDtDt[0]*dtdy*dtdz
2699  + solDrDs[0]*(drdy*dsdz + dsdy*drdz) + solDrDt[0]*(drdy*dtdz + dtdy*drdz)
2700  + solDsDt[0]*(dsdy*dtdz + dtdy*dsdz) + solDr[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[12]
2701  + solDs[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[13] + solDt[0]*metricTerms2ndDer[14];
2702  const su2double d2rudydz = solDrDr[1]*drdy*drdz + solDsDs[1]*dsdy*dsdz + solDtDt[1]*dtdy*dtdz
2703  + solDrDs[1]*(drdy*dsdz + dsdy*drdz) + solDrDt[1]*(drdy*dtdz + dtdy*drdz)
2704  + solDsDt[1]*(dsdy*dtdz + dtdy*dsdz) + solDr[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[12]
2705  + solDs[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[13] + solDt[1]*metricTerms2ndDer[14];
2706  const su2double d2rvdydz = solDrDr[2]*drdy*drdz + solDsDs[2]*dsdy*dsdz + solDtDt[2]*dtdy*dtdz
2707  + solDrDs[2]*(drdy*dsdz + dsdy*drdz) + solDrDt[2]*(drdy*dtdz + dtdy*drdz)
2708  + solDsDt[2]*(dsdy*dtdz + dtdy*dsdz) + solDr[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[12]
2709  + solDs[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[13] + solDt[2]*metricTerms2ndDer[14];
2710  const su2double d2rwdydz = solDrDr[3]*drdy*drdz + solDsDs[3]*dsdy*dsdz + solDtDt[3]*dtdy*dtdz
2711  + solDrDs[3]*(drdy*dsdz + dsdy*drdz) + solDrDt[3]*(drdy*dtdz + dtdy*drdz)
2712  + solDsDt[3]*(dsdy*dtdz + dtdy*dsdz) + solDr[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[12]
2713  + solDs[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[13] + solDt[3]*metricTerms2ndDer[14];
2714 
2715  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the pressure, velocity components,
2716  static energy and dynamic viscosity. */
2717  const su2double dpdx = Gamma_Minus_One*(drEdx + kinEnergy*drhodx
2718  - u*drudx - v*drvdx - w*drwdx);
2719  const su2double dpdy = Gamma_Minus_One*(drEdy + kinEnergy*drhody
2720  - u*drudy - v*drvdy - w*drwdy);
2721  const su2double dpdz = Gamma_Minus_One*(drEdz + kinEnergy*drhodz
2722  - u*drudz - v*drvdz - w*drwdz);
2723 
2724  const su2double dudx = rhoInv*(drudx - u*drhodx);
2725  const su2double dudy = rhoInv*(drudy - u*drhody);
2726  const su2double dudz = rhoInv*(drudz - u*drhodz);
2727 
2728  const su2double dvdx = rhoInv*(drvdx - v*drhodx);
2729  const su2double dvdy = rhoInv*(drvdy - v*drhody);
2730  const su2double dvdz = rhoInv*(drvdz - v*drhodz);
2731 
2732  const su2double dwdx = rhoInv*(drwdx - w*drhodx);
2733  const su2double dwdy = rhoInv*(drwdy - w*drhody);
2734  const su2double dwdz = rhoInv*(drwdz - w*drhodz);
2735 
2736  const su2double dedx = rhoInv*(drEdx - TotalEnergy*drhodx) - u*dudx - v*dvdx - w*dwdx;
2737  const su2double dedy = rhoInv*(drEdy - TotalEnergy*drhody) - u*dudy - v*dvdy - w*dwdy;
2738  const su2double dedz = rhoInv*(drEdz - TotalEnergy*drhodz) - u*dudz - v*dvdz - w*dwdz;
2739 
2740  const su2double dViscLamdx = CvInv*dedx*dViscLamdT;
2741  const su2double dViscLamdy = CvInv*dedy*dViscLamdT;
2742  const su2double dViscLamdz = CvInv*dedz*dViscLamdT;
2743 
2744  /*--- Compute the second derivatives of the velocity components. ---*/
2745  const su2double d2udxdx = rhoInv*(d2rudxdx - u*d2rhodxdx
2746  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhodx*(u*drhodx - drudx));
2747  const su2double d2udydy = rhoInv*(d2rudydy - u*d2rhodydy
2748  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhody*(u*drhody - drudy));
2749  const su2double d2udzdz = rhoInv*(d2rudzdz - u*d2rhodzdz
2750  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhodz*(u*drhodz - drudz));
2751  const su2double d2udxdy = rhoInv*(d2rudxdy - u*d2rhodxdy
2752  + rhoInv*(drhodx*(u*drhody - drudy)
2753  + drhody*(u*drhodx - drudx)));
2754  const su2double d2udxdz = rhoInv*(d2rudxdz - u*d2rhodxdz
2755  + rhoInv*(drhodx*(u*drhodz - drudz)
2756  + drhodz*(u*drhodx - drudx)));
2757  const su2double d2udydz = rhoInv*(d2rudydz - u*d2rhodydz
2758  + rhoInv*(drhody*(u*drhodz - drudz)
2759  + drhodz*(u*drhody - drudy)));
2760 
2761  const su2double d2vdxdx = rhoInv*(d2rvdxdx - v*d2rhodxdx
2762  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhodx*(v*drhodx - drvdx));
2763  const su2double d2vdydy = rhoInv*(d2rvdydy - v*d2rhodydy
2764  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhody*(v*drhody - drvdy));
2765  const su2double d2vdzdz = rhoInv*(d2rvdzdz - v*d2rhodzdz
2766  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhodz*(v*drhodz - drvdz));
2767  const su2double d2vdxdy = rhoInv*(d2rvdxdy - v*d2rhodxdy
2768  + rhoInv*(drhodx*(v*drhody - drvdy)
2769  + drhody*(v*drhodx - drvdx)));
2770  const su2double d2vdxdz = rhoInv*(d2rvdxdz - v*d2rhodxdz
2771  + rhoInv*(drhodx*(v*drhodz - drvdz)
2772  + drhodz*(v*drhodx - drvdx)));
2773  const su2double d2vdydz = rhoInv*(d2rvdydz - v*d2rhodydz
2774  + rhoInv*(drhody*(v*drhodz - drvdz)
2775  + drhodz*(v*drhody - drvdy)));
2776 
2777  const su2double d2wdxdx = rhoInv*(d2rwdxdx - w*d2rhodxdx
2778  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhodx*(w*drhodx - drwdx));
2779  const su2double d2wdydy = rhoInv*(d2rwdydy - w*d2rhodydy
2780  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhody*(w*drhody - drwdy));
2781  const su2double d2wdzdz = rhoInv*(d2rwdzdz - w*d2rhodzdz
2782  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhodz*(w*drhodz - drwdz));
2783  const su2double d2wdxdy = rhoInv*(d2rwdxdy - w*d2rhodxdy
2784  + rhoInv*(drhodx*(w*drhody - drwdy)
2785  + drhody*(w*drhodx - drwdx)));
2786  const su2double d2wdxdz = rhoInv*(d2rwdxdz - w*d2rhodxdz
2787  + rhoInv*(drhodx*(w*drhodz - drwdz)
2788  + drhodz*(w*drhodx - drwdx)));
2789  const su2double d2wdydz = rhoInv*(d2rwdydz - w*d2rhodydz
2790  + rhoInv*(drhody*(w*drhodz - drwdz)
2791  + drhodz*(w*drhody - drwdy)));
2792 
2793  /* Compute the second derivatives of the static energy. Note that this
2794  term appears in the heat flux and therefore only the pure second
2795  derivatives are needed. Hence, the cross-derivatives are omitted. */
2796  const su2double d2edxdx = rhoInv*(d2rEdxdx - TotalEnergy*d2rhodxdx
2797  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhodx*(TotalEnergy*drhodx - drEdx))
2798  - u*d2udxdx - dudx*dudx - v*d2vdxdx - dvdx*dvdx
2799  - w*d2wdxdx - dwdx*dwdx;
2800  const su2double d2edydy = rhoInv*(d2rEdydy - TotalEnergy*d2rhodydy
2801  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhody*(TotalEnergy*drhody - drEdy))
2802  - u*d2udydy - dudy*dudy - v*d2vdydy - dvdy*dvdy
2803  - w*d2wdydy - dwdy*dwdy;
2804  const su2double d2edzdz = rhoInv*(d2rEdzdz - TotalEnergy*d2rhodzdz
2805  + 2.0*rhoInv*drhodz*(TotalEnergy*drhodz - drEdz))
2806  - u*d2udzdz - dudz*dudz - v*d2vdzdz - dvdz*dvdz
2807  - w*d2wdzdz - dwdz*dwdz;
2808 
2809  /*--- If an SGS model is used the eddy viscosity and its spatial
2810  derivatives must be computed. ---*/
2811  su2double ViscosityTurb = 0.0;
2812  su2double dViscTurbdx = 0.0, dViscTurbdy = 0.0, dViscTurbdz = 0.0;
2813 
2814  if( SGSModelUsed ) {
2815  const su2double dist = elem->wallDistance[i];
2816  ViscosityTurb = SGSModel->ComputeEddyViscosity_3D(rho, dudx, dudy, dudz,
2817  dvdx, dvdy, dvdz, dwdx,
2818  dwdy, dwdz, lenScale, dist);
2819 
2820  SGSModel->ComputeGradEddyViscosity_3D(rho, drhodx, drhody, drhodz, dudx, dudy,
2821  dudz, dvdx, dvdy, dvdz, dwdx, dwdy, dwdz,
2822  d2udxdx, d2udydy, d2udzdz, d2udxdy,
2823  d2udxdz, d2udydz, d2vdxdx, d2vdydy,
2824  d2vdzdz, d2vdxdy, d2vdxdz, d2vdydz,
2825  d2wdxdx, d2wdydy, d2wdzdz, d2wdxdy,
2826  d2wdxdz, d2wdydz, lenScale, dist,
2827  dViscTurbdx, dViscTurbdy, dViscTurbdz);
2828  }
2829 
2830  /*--- Compute the total viscosity, the total heat conductivity and their
2831  gradients. Note that the heat conductivity is divided by the Cv,
2832  because gradients of internal energy are computed and not temperature. ---*/
2833  const su2double Viscosity = ViscosityLam + ViscosityTurb;
2834  const su2double kOverCv = ViscosityLam *factHeatFlux_Lam
2835  + ViscosityTurb*factHeatFlux_Turb;
2836 
2837  const su2double dViscDx = dViscLamdx + dViscTurbdx;
2838  const su2double dViscDy = dViscLamdy + dViscTurbdy;
2839  const su2double dViscDz = dViscLamdz + dViscTurbdz;
2840 
2841  const su2double dkOverCvdx = dViscLamdx *factHeatFlux_Lam
2842  + dViscTurbdx*factHeatFlux_Turb;
2843  const su2double dkOverCvdy = dViscLamdy *factHeatFlux_Lam
2844  + dViscTurbdy*factHeatFlux_Turb;
2845  const su2double dkOverCvdz = dViscLamdz *factHeatFlux_Lam
2846  + dViscTurbdz*factHeatFlux_Turb;
2847 
2848  /* Abbreviations, which make it easier to compute the divergence term. */
2849  const su2double abv1 = drudx + drvdy + drwdz;
2850  const su2double abv2 = u*drhodx + v*drhody + w*drhodz;
2851  const su2double abv3 = u*(drEdx + dpdx) + v*(drEdy + dpdy) + w*(drEdz + dpdz);
2852  const su2double abv4 = dudx + dvdy + dwdz;
2853 
2854  /*--- Compute the divergence of the grid velocity.
2855  SET TO ZERO FOR NOW. THIS IS NOT CORRECT!!!!. ---*/
2856  const su2double divGridVel = 0.0;
2857 
2858  /* Set the pointer to store the divergence terms for this integration
2859  point and compute these terms, multiplied by the integration weight
2860  and Jacobian. */
2861  const su2double weightJac = weights[i]*Jac;
2862  su2double *divFluxInt = divFlux + offInt;
2863 
2864  divFluxInt[0] = weightJac*(abv1 - rho*divGridVel - gridVel[0]*drhodx
2865  - gridVel[1]*drhody - gridVel[2]*drhodz);
2866  divFluxInt[1] = weightJac*(dpdx + u*(abv1-abv2) - lambdaOverMu*abv4*dViscDx
2867  + u*drudx + v*drudy + w*drudz
2868  - lambdaOverMu*Viscosity*(d2udxdx + d2vdxdy + d2wdxdz)
2869  - Viscosity*(2.0*d2udxdx + d2udydy + d2vdxdy + d2udzdz + d2wdxdz)
2870  - 2.0*dViscDx*dudx - dViscDy*(dudy+dvdx) - dViscDz*(dudz+dwdx)
2871  - ru*divGridVel
2872  - gridVel[0]*drudx - gridVel[1]*drudy - gridVel[2]*drudz);
2873  divFluxInt[2] = weightJac*(dpdy + v*(abv1-abv2) - lambdaOverMu*abv4*dViscDy
2874  + u*drvdx + v*drvdy + w*drvdz
2875  - lambdaOverMu*Viscosity*(d2udxdy + d2vdydy + d2wdydz)
2876  - Viscosity*(d2udxdy + d2vdxdx + 2.0*d2vdydy + d2vdzdz + d2wdydz)
2877  - dViscDx*(dudy + dvdx) - 2.0*dViscDy*dvdy - dViscDz*(dvdz+dwdy)
2878  - rv*divGridVel
2879  - gridVel[0]*drvdx - gridVel[1]*drvdy - gridVel[2]*drvdz);
2880  divFluxInt[3] = weightJac*(dpdz + w*(abv1-abv2) - lambdaOverMu*abv4*dViscDz
2881  + u*drwdx + v*drwdy + w*drwdz
2882  - lambdaOverMu*Viscosity*(d2udxdz + d2vdydz + d2wdzdz)
2883  - Viscosity*(d2udxdz + d2wdxdx + d2vdydz + d2wdydy + 2.0*d2wdzdz)
2884  - dViscDx*(dudz+dwdx) - dViscDy*(dvdz+dwdy) - 2.0*dViscDz*dwdz
2885  - rw*divGridVel
2886  - gridVel[0]*drwdx - gridVel[1]*drwdy - gridVel[2]*drwdz);
2887  divFluxInt[4] = weightJac*(abv3 + Htot*(abv1 - abv2)
2888  - abv4*lambdaOverMu*(Viscosity*abv4 + u*dViscDx + v*dViscDy + w*dViscDz)
2889  - dkOverCvdx*dedx - dkOverCvdy*dedy - dkOverCvdz*dedz
2890  - kOverCv*(d2edxdx + d2edydy + d2edzdz)
2891  - (Viscosity*dudx + u*dViscDx)*2.0*dudx
2892  - (Viscosity*dvdy + v*dViscDy)*2.0*dvdy
2893  - (Viscosity*dwdz + w*dViscDz)*2.0*dwdz
2894  - (Viscosity*dudy + u*dViscDy + Viscosity*dvdx + v*dViscDx)*(dudy + dvdx)
2895  - (Viscosity*dudz + u*dViscDz + Viscosity*dwdx + w*dViscDx)*(dudz + dwdx)
2896  - (Viscosity*dvdz + v*dViscDz + Viscosity*dwdy + w*dViscDy)*(dvdz + dwdy)
2897  - Viscosity*u*(d2udxdx+d2udydy+d2udzdz + (1.0+lambdaOverMu)*(d2udxdx+d2vdxdy+d2wdxdz))
2898  - Viscosity*v*(d2vdxdx+d2vdydy+d2vdzdz + (1.0+lambdaOverMu)*(d2udxdy+d2vdydy+d2wdydz))
2899  - Viscosity*w*(d2wdxdx+d2wdydy+d2wdzdz + (1.0+lambdaOverMu)*(d2udxdz+d2vdydz+d2wdzdz))
2900  - rE*divGridVel
2901  - gridVel[0]*drEdx - gridVel[1]*drEdy - gridVel[2]*drEdz);
2902 
2903  /* Add the body force to the flux divergence for the momentum and energy
2904  equation. Note that the source terms are multiplied with minus the
2905  integration weight in order to be consistent with the formulation of
2906  the residual. Also note that for the energy source term the absolute
2907  velocity must be taken and not the relative. */
2908  divFluxInt[1] -= weightJac*bodyForceX;
2909  divFluxInt[2] -= weightJac*bodyForceY;
2910  divFluxInt[3] -= weightJac*bodyForceZ;
2911  divFluxInt[4] -= weightJac*(u*bodyForceX + v*bodyForceY + w*bodyForceZ);
2912  }
2913  }
2914 
2915  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2916  /*--- Add the source terms of the manufactured solution to the divergence---*/
2917  /*--- of the fluxes, if a manufactured solution is used. ---*/
2918  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2919 
2920  if( VerificationSolution ) {
2921  if( VerificationSolution->IsManufacturedSolution() ) {
2922 
2923  /*--- Loop over the number of entities that are treated simultaneously. */
2924  for(unsigned short simul=0; simul<nSimul; ++simul) {
2925 
2926  /*--- Loop over the integration points of the element. ---*/
2927  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
2928 
2929  /* Set the pointers for this integration point. */
2930  const unsigned short offInt = i*NPad + simul*nVar;
2931  su2double *divFluxInt = divFlux + offInt;
2932 
2933  /* Set the pointer to the coordinates in this integration point.
2934  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
2935  THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST
2936  BE TAKEN. */
2937  const su2double *coor = elem->coorIntegrationPoints.data() + i*nDim;
2938 
2939  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point.
2940  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. WHEN AN ACTUAL MOTION IS SPECIFIED,
2941  THE DATA FOR THIS DOF FOR THE CURRENT TIME INTEGRATION POINT MUST
2942  BE TAKEN. */
2943  const su2double *metricTerms = elem->metricTerms.data() + i*nMetricPerPoint;
2944  const su2double weightJac = weights[i]*metricTerms[0];
2945 
2946  /* Compute the source terms of the manufactured solution.
2947  THIS IS A TEMPORARY IMPLEMENTATION. FOR AN ACTUAL TIME ACCURATE
2948  SIMULATION THE CORRECT TIME MUST BE GIVEN TO THIS FUNCTION. */
2949  su2double sourceMan[5];
2950  VerificationSolution->GetMMSSourceTerm(coor, 0.0, sourceMan);
2951 
2952  /* Add the source terms to the flux divergence. Note that the source
2953  terms are multiplied with minus the integration weight in order
2954  to be consistent with the formulation of the residual. */
2955  divFluxInt[0] -= weightJac*sourceMan[0];
2956  divFluxInt[1] -= weightJac*sourceMan[1];
2957  divFluxInt[2] -= weightJac*sourceMan[2];
2958  divFluxInt[3] -= weightJac*sourceMan[3];
2959  divFluxInt[4] -= weightJac*sourceMan[4];
2960  }
2961  }
2962  }
2963  }
2964 
2965  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2966  /*--- Compute the residual in the DOFs, which is the matrix product of ---*/
2967  /*--- basisFunctionsIntTrans and divFlux. ---*/
2968  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2969 
2970  blasFunctions->gemm(nDOFs, NPad, nInt, basisFunctionsIntTrans, divFlux, res, config);
2971 }

2973 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::Shock_Capturing_DG(CConfig *config,
2974  const unsigned long elemBeg,
2975  const unsigned long elemEnd,
2976  su2double *workArray) {
2977 
2978  /*--- Run shock capturing algorithm ---*/
2979  switch( config->GetKind_FEM_DG_Shock() ) {
2980  case FEM_SHOCK_CAPTURING_DG::NONE:
2981  break;
2982  case FEM_SHOCK_CAPTURING_DG::PERSSON:
2983  Shock_Capturing_DG_Persson(elemBeg, elemEnd, workArray);
2984  break;
2985  }
2986 
2987 }
2988 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::Shock_Capturing_DG_Persson(const unsigned long elemBeg,
2989  const unsigned long elemEnd,
2990  su2double *workArray) {
2991 
2992  /*--- Dummy variable for storing shock sensor value temporarily ---*/
2993  su2double sensorVal, sensorLowerBound, machNorm, machMax;
2994  su2double DensityInv, Velocity2, StaticEnergy, SoundSpeed2, Velocity2Rel;
2995 
2996  bool shockExist;
2997  unsigned short nDOFsPm1; // Number of DOFs up to polynomial degree p-1
2998 
2999  /*--- Loop over the given range of elements to sense the shock. If shock exists,
3000  add artificial viscosity for DG FEM formulation to the residual. ---*/
3001  for(unsigned long l=elemBeg; l<elemEnd; ++l) {
3002 
3003  /* Get the data from the corresponding standard element. */
3004  const unsigned short ind = volElem[l].indStandardElement;
3005  const unsigned short nDOFs = volElem[l].nDOFsSol;
3006  const unsigned short VTK_TypeElem = volElem[l].VTK_Type;
3007  const unsigned short nPoly = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNPoly();
3008  const su2double *matVanderInv = standardElementsSol[ind].GetMatVandermondeInv();
3009 
3010  /*----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3011  /*--- Step 1: Calculate the number of DOFs up to polynomial degree p-1. ---*/
3012  /*----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3013 
3014  nDOFsPm1 = 0;
3015  switch( VTK_TypeElem ) {
3016  case TRIANGLE:
3017  nDOFsPm1 = nPoly*(nPoly+1)/2;
3018  break;
3019  case QUADRILATERAL:
3020  nDOFsPm1 = nPoly*nPoly;
3021  break;
3022  case TETRAHEDRON:
3023  nDOFsPm1 = nPoly*(nPoly+1)*(nPoly+2)/6;
3024  break;
3025  case PYRAMID:
3026  nDOFsPm1 = nPoly*(nPoly+1)*(2*nPoly+1)/6;
3027  break;
3028  case PRISM:
3029  nDOFsPm1 = nPoly*nPoly*(nPoly+1)/2;
3030  break;
3031  case HEXAHEDRON:
3032  nDOFsPm1 = nPoly*nPoly*nPoly;
3033  break;
3034  }
3035 
3036  /*---------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3037  /*--- Step 2: Calculate the shock sensor value for this element. ---*/
3038  /*---------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3039 
3040  /* Initialize dummy variable for this volume element */
3041  sensorVal = 0;
3042  machMax = -1;
3043  shockExist = false;
3044  sensorLowerBound = 1.e15;
3045 
3046  /* Easier storage of the solution variables for this element. */
3047  const unsigned short timeLevel = volElem[l].timeLevel;
3048  const su2double *solDOFs = VecWorkSolDOFs[timeLevel].data()
3049  + nVar*volElem[l].offsetDOFsSolThisTimeLevel;
3050 
3051  /* Temporary storage of mach number for DOFs in this element. */
3052  su2double *machSolDOFs = workArray;
3053  su2double *vecTemp = machSolDOFs + nDOFs;
3054 
3055  /* Calculate primitive variables and mach number for DOFs in this element.
3056  Also, track the maximum mach number in this element. */
3057  for(unsigned short iInd=0; iInd<nDOFs; ++iInd) {
3058 
3059  const su2double *sol = solDOFs + iInd*nVar;
3060  const su2double *gridVel = volElem[l].gridVelocitiesSolDOFs.data() + iInd*nDim;
3061  DensityInv = 1.0/sol[0];
3062  Velocity2 = 0.0;
3063  Velocity2Rel = 0.0;
3064  for(unsigned short iDim=1; iDim<=nDim; ++iDim) {
3065  const su2double vel = sol[iDim]*DensityInv;
3066  const su2double velRel = vel - gridVel[iDim-1];
3067  Velocity2 += vel*vel;
3068  Velocity2Rel += velRel*velRel;
3069  }
3070 
3071  StaticEnergy = sol[nDim+1]*DensityInv - 0.5*Velocity2;
3072 
3073  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(sol[0], StaticEnergy);
3074  SoundSpeed2 = FluidModel->GetSoundSpeed2();
3075  machSolDOFs[iInd] = sqrt( Velocity2Rel/SoundSpeed2 );
3076  machMax = max(machSolDOFs[iInd],machMax);
3077  }
3078 
3079  /* Change the solution coefficients to modal form from nodal form */
3080  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFs; ++i) {
3081  vecTemp[i] = 0.0;
3082  for (unsigned short j=0; j<nDOFs; ++j)
3083  vecTemp[i] += matVanderInv[i+j*nDOFs]*machSolDOFs[j];
3084  }
3085 
3086  /* Get the L2 norm of solution coefficients for the highest polynomial order. */
3087  for(unsigned short i=nDOFsPm1; i<nDOFs; ++i) {
3088  sensorVal += vecTemp[i]*vecTemp[i];
3089  }
3090 
3091  /* If the maximum mach number is greater than 1.0, try to calculate the shockSensorValue.
3092  Otherwise, assign default value. */
3093  if ( machMax > 1.0) {
3094  // !!!!!Threshold value for sensorVal should be further investigated
3095  if(sensorVal > 1.e-15) {
3096  machNorm = 0.0;
3097 
3098  /*--- Get L2 norm square of vecTemp ---*/
3099  for (unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFs; ++i) {
3100  machNorm += vecTemp[i]*vecTemp[i];
3101  }
3102  if (machNorm < 1.e-15) {
3103  // This should not happen
3104  volElem[l].shockSensorValue = 1000.0;
3105  }
3106  else {
3107  volElem[l].shockSensorValue = log(sensorVal/machNorm);
3108  shockExist = true;
3109  }
3110  }
3111  else {
3112  // There is no shock in this element
3113  volElem[l].shockSensorValue = -1000.0;
3114  }
3115  }
3116  else {
3117  volElem[l].shockSensorValue = -1000.0;
3118  }
3119 
3120  /*---------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3121  /*--- Step 3: Determine artificial viscosity for this element. ---*/
3122  /*---------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3123  if (shockExist) {
3124  // Following if-else clause is purely empirical from NACA0012 case.
3125  // Need to develop thorough method for general problems.
3126  switch ( nPoly ) {
3127  case 1: sensorLowerBound = -6.0; break;
3128  case 2: sensorLowerBound = -12.0; break;
3129  case 3: sensorLowerBound = -12.0; break;
3130  case 4: sensorLowerBound = -17.0; break;
3131  default: sensorLowerBound = -17.0; break;
3132  }
3133 
3134  // Assign artificial viscosity based on shockSensorValue
3135  if ( volElem[l].shockSensorValue > sensorLowerBound ) {
3136  // Following value is initial guess.
3137  volElem[l].shockArtificialViscosity = 1.e-10;
3138  }
3139  else {
3140  volElem[l].shockArtificialViscosity = 0.0;
3141  }
3142  }
3143  else {
3144  volElem[l].shockArtificialViscosity = 0.0;
3145  }
3146  }
3147 }
3148 
3149 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::Volume_Residual(CConfig *config,
3150  const unsigned long elemBeg,
3151  const unsigned long elemEnd,
3152  su2double *workArray) {
3153 
3154  /*--- Determine whether a body force term is present. ---*/
3155  bool body_force = config->GetBody_Force();
3156  const su2double *body_force_vector = body_force ? config->GetBody_Force_Vector() : nullptr;
3157 
3158  /*--- Get the physical time if necessary. ---*/
3159  su2double time = 0.0;
3160  if (config->GetTime_Marching() != TIME_MARCHING::STEADY) time = config->GetPhysicalTime();
3161 
3162  /* Constant factor present in the heat flux vector. */
3163  const su2double factHeatFlux_Lam = Gamma/Prandtl_Lam;
3164  const su2double factHeatFlux_Turb = Gamma/Prandtl_Turb;
3165 
3166  /* Determine the number of elements that are treated simultaneously
3167  in the matrix products to obtain good gemm performance. */
3168  const unsigned short nPadInput = config->GetSizeMatMulPadding();
3169  const unsigned short nElemSimul = nPadInput/nVar;
3170 
3171  /* Determine the minimum padded size in the matrix multiplications, which
3172  corresponds to 64 byte alignment. */
3173  const unsigned short nPadMin = 64/sizeof(passivedouble);
3174 
3175  /* Store the number of metric points per integration point, which depends
3176  on the number of dimensions. */
3177  const unsigned short nMetricPerPoint = nDim*nDim + 1;
3178 
3179  /*--- Loop over the given element range to compute the contribution of the
3180  volume integral in the DG FEM formulation to the residual. Multiple
3181  elements are treated simultaneously to improve the performance
3182  of the matrix multiplications. As a consequence, the update of the
3183  counter l happens at the end of this loop section. ---*/
3184  for(unsigned long l=elemBeg; l<elemEnd;) {
3185 
3186  /* Determine the end index for this chunk of elements and the padded
3187  N value in the gemm computations. */
3188  unsigned long lEnd;
3189  unsigned short ind, llEnd, NPad;
3190 
3191  MetaDataChunkOfElem(volElem, l, elemEnd, nElemSimul, nPadMin, lEnd, ind, llEnd, NPad);
3192 
3193  /* Get the required data from the corresponding standard element. */
3194  const unsigned short nInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
3195  const unsigned short nDOFs = volElem[l].nDOFsSol;
3196  const su2double *matBasisInt = standardElementsSol[ind].GetMatBasisFunctionsIntegration();
3197  const su2double *matDerBasisIntTrans = standardElementsSol[ind].GetDerMatBasisFunctionsIntTrans();
3198  const su2double *matBasisIntTrans = standardElementsSol[ind].GetBasisFunctionsIntegrationTrans();
3199  const su2double *weights = standardElementsSol[ind].GetWeightsIntegration();
3200 
3201  unsigned short nPoly = standardElementsSol[ind].GetNPoly();
3202  if(nPoly == 0) nPoly = 1;
3203 
3204  /*--- Set the pointers for the local arrays. ---*/
3205  su2double *solDOFs = workArray;
3206  su2double *sources = solDOFs + nDOFs*NPad;
3207  su2double *solAndGradInt = sources + nInt *NPad;
3208  su2double *fluxes = solAndGradInt + nInt *NPad*(nDim+1);
3209 
3210  /*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3211  /*--- Step 1: Determine the solution variables and their gradients ---*/
3212  /*--- w.r.t. the parametric coordinates in the integration ---*/
3213  /*--- points of the element. ---*/
3214  /*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3215 
3216  /* Copy the solution of the DOFs into solDOFs for this chunk of elements. */
3217  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
3218 
3219  /* Easier storage of the solution variables for this element. */
3220  const unsigned long lInd = l + ll;
3221  const unsigned short timeLevel = volElem[lInd].timeLevel;
3222  const su2double *solDOFsElem = VecWorkSolDOFs[timeLevel].data()
3223  + nVar*volElem[lInd].offsetDOFsSolThisTimeLevel;
3224 
3225  /* Loop over the DOFs and copy the data. */
3226  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
3227  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFs; ++i)
3228  for(unsigned short mm=0; mm<nVar; ++mm)
3229  solDOFs[i*NPad+llNVar+mm] = solDOFsElem[i*nVar+mm];
3230  }
3231 
3232  /* Call the general function to carry out the matrix product to determine
3233  the solution and gradients in the integration points of the chunk
3234  of elements. */
3235  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*(nDim+1), NPad, nDOFs, matBasisInt, solDOFs, solAndGradInt, config);
3236 
3237  /*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3238  /*--- Step 2: Compute the total fluxes (inviscid fluxes minus the ---*/
3239  /*--- viscous fluxes), multiplied by minus the integration ---*/
3240  /*--- weight, in the integration points. ---*/
3241  /*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3242 
3243  /* Determine the offset between the solution variables and the r-derivatives,
3244  which is also the offset between the r- and s-derivatives and the offset
3245  between s- and t-derivatives. */
3246  const unsigned short offDeriv = NPad*nInt;
3247 
3248  /* Make a distinction between two and three space dimensions
3249  in order to have the most efficient code. */
3250  switch( nDim ) {
3251 
3252  case 2: {
3253 
3254  /* 2D simulation. Loop over the chunk of elements and loop over the
3255  integration points of the elements to compute the fluxes. */
3256  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
3257  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
3258  const unsigned long lInd = l + ll;
3259 
3260  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
3261  const unsigned short iNPad = i*NPad;
3262 
3263  /* Easier storage of the metric terms and grid velocities in this
3264  integration point and compute the inverse of the Jacobian. */
3265  const su2double *metricTerms = volElem[lInd].metricTerms.data()
3266  + i*nMetricPerPoint;
3267  const su2double *gridVel = volElem[lInd].gridVelocities.data() + i*nDim;
3268  const su2double Jac = metricTerms[0];
3269  const su2double JacInv = 1.0/Jac;
3270 
3271  /* Compute the true metric terms in this integration point. */
3272  const su2double drdx = JacInv*metricTerms[1];
3273  const su2double drdy = JacInv*metricTerms[2];
3274 
3275  const su2double dsdx = JacInv*metricTerms[3];
3276  const su2double dsdy = JacInv*metricTerms[4];
3277 
3278  /* Compute the metric terms multiplied by minus the integration weight.
3279  The minus sign comes from the integration by parts in the weak
3280  formulation. */
3281  const su2double wDrdx = -weights[i]*metricTerms[1];
3282  const su2double wDrdy = -weights[i]*metricTerms[2];
3283 
3284  const su2double wDsdx = -weights[i]*metricTerms[3];
3285  const su2double wDsdy = -weights[i]*metricTerms[4];
3286 
3287  /* Easier storage of the location where the solution data of this
3288  integration point starts. */
3289  const su2double *sol = solAndGradInt + iNPad + llNVar;
3290  const su2double *dSolDr = sol + offDeriv;
3291  const su2double *dSolDs = dSolDr + offDeriv;
3292 
3293  /*--- Compute the Cartesian gradients of the independent solution
3294  variables from the gradients in parametric coordinates and the
3295  metric terms in this integration point. ---*/
3296  const su2double dRhoDx = dSolDr[0]*drdx + dSolDs[0]*dsdx;
3297  const su2double dRhoUDx = dSolDr[1]*drdx + dSolDs[1]*dsdx;
3298  const su2double dRhoVDx = dSolDr[2]*drdx + dSolDs[2]*dsdx;
3299  const su2double dRhoEDx = dSolDr[3]*drdx + dSolDs[3]*dsdx;
3300 
3301  const su2double dRhoDy = dSolDr[0]*drdy + dSolDs[0]*dsdy;
3302  const su2double dRhoUDy = dSolDr[1]*drdy + dSolDs[1]*dsdy;
3303  const su2double dRhoVDy = dSolDr[2]*drdy + dSolDs[2]*dsdy;
3304  const su2double dRhoEDy = dSolDr[3]*drdy + dSolDs[3]*dsdy;
3305 
3306  /*--- Compute the velocities and static energy in this integration point. ---*/
3307  const su2double rhoInv = 1.0/sol[0];
3308  const su2double u = sol[1]*rhoInv;
3309  const su2double v = sol[2]*rhoInv;
3310  const su2double TotalEnergy = sol[3]*rhoInv;
3311  const su2double StaticEnergy = TotalEnergy - 0.5*(u*u + v*v);
3312 
3313  /*--- Compute the Cartesian gradients of the velocities and static energy
3314  in this integration point and also the divergence of the velocity. ---*/
3315  const su2double dudx = rhoInv*(dRhoUDx - u*dRhoDx);
3316  const su2double dudy = rhoInv*(dRhoUDy - u*dRhoDy);
3317 
3318  const su2double dvdx = rhoInv*(dRhoVDx - v*dRhoDx);
3319  const su2double dvdy = rhoInv*(dRhoVDy - v*dRhoDy);
3320 
3321  const su2double dStaticEnergyDx = rhoInv*(dRhoEDx - TotalEnergy*dRhoDx)
3322  - u*dudx - v*dvdx;
3323  const su2double dStaticEnergyDy = rhoInv*(dRhoEDy - TotalEnergy*dRhoDy)
3324  - u*dudy - v*dvdy;
3325 
3326  const su2double divVel = dudx + dvdy;
3327 
3328  /*--- Compute the pressure and the laminar viscosity. ---*/
3329  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(sol[0], StaticEnergy);
3330  const su2double Pressure = FluidModel->GetPressure();
3331  const su2double ViscosityLam = FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
3332 
3333  /*--- If an SGS model is used the eddy viscosity must be computed. ---*/
3334  su2double ViscosityTurb = 0.0;
3335  if( SGSModelUsed ) {
3336  const su2double lenScale = volElem[lInd].lenScale/nPoly;
3337  ViscosityTurb = SGSModel->ComputeEddyViscosity_2D(sol[0], dudx, dudy,
3338  dvdx, dvdy, lenScale,
3339  volElem[lInd].wallDistance[i]);
3340  }
3341 
3342  /* Compute the total viscosity and heat conductivity. Note that the heat
3343  conductivity is divided by the Cv, because gradients of internal energy
3344  are computed and not temperature. */
3345  const su2double Viscosity = ViscosityLam + ViscosityTurb;
3346  const su2double kOverCv = ViscosityLam *factHeatFlux_Lam
3347  + ViscosityTurb*factHeatFlux_Turb;
