5047 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::BC_Far_Field(CConfig *config,
5048  const unsigned long surfElemBeg,
5049  const unsigned long surfElemEnd,
5050  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
5051  su2double *resFaces,
5052  CNumerics *conv_numerics,
5053  su2double *workArray){
5054 
5055  /* Initialization of the counter in resFaces. */
5056  unsigned long indResFaces = 0;
5057 
5058  /* Determine the number of faces that are treated simultaneously
5059  in the matrix products to obtain good gemm performance. */
5060  const unsigned short nPadInput = config->GetSizeMatMulPadding();
5061  const unsigned short nFaceSimul = nPadInput/nVar;
5062 
5063  /* Determine the minimum padded size in the matrix multiplications, which
5064  corresponds to 64 byte alignment. */
5065  const unsigned short nPadMin = 64/sizeof(passivedouble);
5066 
5067  /*--- Loop over the requested range of surface faces. Multiple faces
5068  are treated simultaneously to improve the performance of the matrix
5069  multiplications. As a consequence, the update of the counter l
5070  happens at the end of this loop section. ---*/
5071  for(unsigned long l=surfElemBeg; l<surfElemEnd;) {
5072 
5073  /* Determine the end index for this chunk of faces and the padded
5074  N value in the gemm computations. */
5075  unsigned long lEnd;
5076  unsigned short ind, llEnd, NPad;
5077 
5078  MetaDataChunkOfElem(surfElem, l, surfElemEnd, nFaceSimul,
5079  nPadMin, lEnd, ind, llEnd, NPad);
5080 
5081  /*--- Get the information from the standard element, which is the same
5082  for all the faces in the chunks considered. ---*/
5083  const unsigned short nInt = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
5084 
5085  /*--- Set the pointers for the local arrays. ---*/
5086  su2double *solIntL = workArray;
5087  su2double *solIntR = solIntL + NPad*nInt;
5088  su2double *work = solIntR + NPad*nInt;
5089 
5090  /* Compute the left states in the integration points of the chunk of
5091  faces. The array workarray is used as temporary storage inside the
5092  function LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace. */
5093  LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace(config, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l],
5094  work, solIntL);
5095 
5096  /* Set the right state in the integration points to the free stream value. */
5097  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
5098  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
5099  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
5100  su2double *UR = solIntR + i*NPad + llNVar;
5101  for(unsigned short j=0; j<nVar; ++j)
5102  UR[j] = ConsVarFreeStream[j];
5103  }
5104  }
5105 
5106  /* The remainder of the boundary treatment is the same for all
5107  boundary conditions (except the symmetry plane). */
5108  ViscousBoundaryFacesBCTreatment(config, conv_numerics, llEnd, NPad,
5109  0.0, false, 0.0, false, &surfElem[l],
5110  solIntL, solIntR, work, resFaces,
5111  indResFaces, nullptr);
5112 
5113  /* Update the value of the counter l to the end index of the
5114  current chunk. */
5115  l = lEnd;
5116  }
5117 }
5118 
5119 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::BC_Sym_Plane(CConfig *config,
5120  const unsigned long surfElemBeg,
5121  const unsigned long surfElemEnd,
5122  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
5123  su2double *resFaces,
5124  CNumerics *conv_numerics,
5125  su2double *workArray){
5126 
5127  /* Initialization of the counter in resFaces. */
5128  unsigned long indResFaces = 0;
5129 
5130  /* Determine the number of faces that are treated simultaneously
5131  in the matrix products to obtain good gemm performance. */
5132  const unsigned short nPadInput = config->GetSizeMatMulPadding();
5133  const unsigned short nFaceSimul = nPadInput/nVar;
5134 
5135  /* Determine the minimum padded size in the matrix multiplications, which
5136  corresponds to 64 byte alignment. */
5137  const unsigned short nPadMin = 64/sizeof(passivedouble);
5138 
5139  /*--- Loop over the requested range of surface faces. Multiple faces
5140  are treated simultaneously to improve the performance of the matrix
5141  multiplications. As a consequence, the update of the counter l
5142  happens at the end of this loop section. ---*/
5143  for(unsigned long l=surfElemBeg; l<surfElemEnd;) {
5144 
5145  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
5146  /*--- Step 1: Initialization and computation of the left states. ---*/
5147  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
5148 
5149  /* Determine the end index for this chunk of faces and the padded
5150  N value in the gemm computations. */
5151  unsigned long lEnd;
5152  unsigned short ind, llEnd, NPad;
5153 
5154  MetaDataChunkOfElem(surfElem, l, surfElemEnd, nFaceSimul,
5155  nPadMin, lEnd, ind, llEnd, NPad);
5156 
5157  /*--- Get the information from the standard element, which is the same
5158  for all the faces in the chunks considered. ---*/
5159  const unsigned short nInt = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
5160  const unsigned short nDOFsElem = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNDOFsElem();
5161  const su2double *derBasisElem = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetMatDerBasisElemIntegration();
5162 
5163  /*--- Set the pointers for the local arrays. ---*/
5164  su2double *solIntL = workArray;
5165  su2double *solIntR = solIntL + NPad*nInt;
5166  su2double *viscosityInt = solIntR + NPad*nInt;
5167  su2double *kOverCvInt = viscosityInt + llEnd*nInt;
5168  su2double *gradSolInt = kOverCvInt + llEnd*nInt;
5169  su2double *fluxes = gradSolInt + NPad*nInt*nDim;
5170  su2double *viscFluxes = fluxes + NPad*max(nInt*nDim, (int) nDOFsElem);
5171 
5172  /* Compute the left states in the integration points of this chunk of
5173  faces. Use fluxes as a temporary storage array. */
5174  LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace(config, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l],
5175  fluxes, solIntL);
5176 
5177  /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
5178  /*--- Step 2: Computation of the gradients of the conservative ---*/
5179  /*--- variables w.r.t. the parametric coordinates. ---*/
5180  /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
5181 
5182  /* Set the pointer solElem to fluxes, just for readability. It is a temporary
5183  storage of the solution of the elements, such that the gradients can be
5184  computed efficiently. */
5185  su2double *solElem = fluxes;
5186 
5187  /* Loop over the faces of the chunk to set the conservative variables
5188  in the appropriate sequence. */
5189  for(unsigned long ll=l; ll<lEnd; ++ll) {
5190  const unsigned short llRel = ll - l;
5191  const unsigned short llNVar = llRel*nVar;
5192 
5193  /* Determine the time level of the boundary face, which is equal
5194  to the time level of the adjacent element. */
5195  const unsigned long elemID = surfElem[ll].volElemID;
5196  const unsigned short timeLevel = volElem[elemID].timeLevel;
5197 
5198  /* Determine the offset that must be applied to access the correct data for
5199  the adjacent element in the working vector of the solution. This is a
5200  boundary face, which has the same time level as the adjacent element. */
5201  const unsigned long offset = volElem[elemID].offsetDOFsSolLocal
5202  - volElem[elemID].offsetDOFsSolThisTimeLevel;
5203 
5204  /* Loop over the DOFs of the element and copy the solution. */
5205  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFsElem; ++i) {
5206  const su2double *solDOF = VecWorkSolDOFs[timeLevel].data()
5207  + nVar*(surfElem[ll].DOFsSolElement[i] - offset);
5208  for(unsigned short mm=0; mm<nVar; ++mm)
5209  solElem[NPad*i+llNVar+mm] = solDOF[mm];
5210  }
5211  }
5212 
5213  /* Compute the left gradients in the integration points. Call the general
5214  function to carry out the matrix product. */
5215  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*nDim, NPad, nDOFsElem, derBasisElem, solElem, gradSolInt, config);
5216 
5217  /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
5218  /*--- Step 3: Computation of the viscous fluxes in the integration ---*/
5219  /*--- points. ---*/
5220  /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
5221 
5222  /* Determine the offset between r- and -s-derivatives, which is also the
5223  offset between s- and t-derivatives. */
5224  const unsigned short offDeriv = NPad*nInt;
5225 
5226  /* Loop over the faces of the chunk. */
5227  for(unsigned long ll=l; ll<lEnd; ++ll) {
5228  const unsigned short llRel = ll - l;
5229  const unsigned short llNVar = llRel*nVar;
5230 
5231  /* Compute the length scale for the LES of the adjacent element. */
5232  const unsigned long elemID = surfElem[ll].volElemID;
5233  const unsigned short iind = volElem[elemID].indStandardElement;
5234 
5235  unsigned short nPoly = standardElementsSol[iind].GetNPoly();
5236  if(nPoly == 0) nPoly = 1;
5237 
5238  const su2double lenScale_LES = volElem[elemID].lenScale/nPoly;
5239 
5240  /* Easier storage of the wall distance array for this surface element. */
5241  const su2double *wallDistance = surfElem[ll].wallDistance.data();
5242 
5243  /* Make a distinction between two and three space dimensions
5244  in order to have the most efficient code. */
5245  switch( nDim ) {
5246 
5247  case 2: {
5248 
5249  /*--- 2D simulation. Loop over the integration points to apply the
5250  symmetry condition and to compute the viscous normal fluxes. This
5251  is done in the same loop, because the gradients in the right
5252  integration points are constructed using the symmetry boundary
5253  condition. ---*/
5254  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
5255 
5256  /* Easier storage of the left and right solution and the normals
5257  for this integration point. */
5258  const unsigned short pointerOffset = NPad*i + llNVar;
5259  const su2double *UL = solIntL + pointerOffset;
5260  su2double *UR = solIntR + pointerOffset;
5261  const su2double *normals = surfElem[ll].metricNormalsFace.data() + i*(nDim+1);
5262 
5263  /* Compute twice the normal component of the momentum variables. The
5264  factor 2 comes from the fact that the velocity must be mirrored. */
5265  const su2double rVn = 2.0*(UL[1]*normals[0] + UL[2]*normals[1]);
5266 
5267  /* Set the right state. Note that the total energy of the right state is
5268  identical to the left state, because the magnitude of the velocity
5269  remains the same. */
5270  UR[0] = UL[0];
5271  UR[1] = UL[1] - rVn*normals[0];
5272  UR[2] = UL[2] - rVn*normals[1];
5273  UR[3] = UL[3];
5274 
5275  /* Easier storage of the metric terms and left gradients of this
5276  integration point. */
5277  const su2double *metricTerms = surfElem[ll].metricCoorDerivFace.data()
5278  + i*nDim*nDim;
5279  const su2double *dULDr = gradSolInt + pointerOffset;
5280  const su2double *dULDs = dULDr + offDeriv;
5281 
5282  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point. */
5283  const su2double drdx = metricTerms[0];
5284  const su2double drdy = metricTerms[1];
5285  const su2double dsdx = metricTerms[2];
5286  const su2double dsdy = metricTerms[3];
5287 
5288  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the left solution. */
5289  su2double ULGradCart[4][2];
5290  ULGradCart[0][0] = dULDr[0]*drdx + dULDs[0]*dsdx;
5291  ULGradCart[1][0] = dULDr[1]*drdx + dULDs[1]*dsdx;
5292  ULGradCart[2][0] = dULDr[2]*drdx + dULDs[2]*dsdx;
5293  ULGradCart[3][0] = dULDr[3]*drdx + dULDs[3]*dsdx;
5294 
5295  ULGradCart[0][1] = dULDr[0]*drdy + dULDs[0]*dsdy;
5296  ULGradCart[1][1] = dULDr[1]*drdy + dULDs[1]*dsdy;
5297  ULGradCart[2][1] = dULDr[2]*drdy + dULDs[2]*dsdy;
5298  ULGradCart[3][1] = dULDr[3]*drdy + dULDs[3]*dsdy;
5299 
5300  /* Determine the normal gradients of all variables. */
5301  su2double ULGradNorm[4];
5302  ULGradNorm[0] = ULGradCart[0][0]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[0][1]*normals[1];
5303  ULGradNorm[1] = ULGradCart[1][0]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[1][1]*normals[1];
5304  ULGradNorm[2] = ULGradCart[2][0]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[2][1]*normals[1];
5305  ULGradNorm[3] = ULGradCart[3][0]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[3][1]*normals[1];
5306 
5307  /* For the construction of the gradients of the right solution, also
5308  the Cartesian gradients and the normal gradient of the normal
5309  momentum is needed. This is computed below. */
5310  su2double GradCartNormMomL[2];
5311  GradCartNormMomL[0] = ULGradCart[1][0]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[2][0]*normals[1];
5312  GradCartNormMomL[1] = ULGradCart[1][1]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[2][1]*normals[1];
5313 
5314  const su2double GradNormNormMomL = ULGradNorm[1]*normals[0] + ULGradNorm[2]*normals[1];
5315 
5316  /* Abbreviate twice the normal vector. */
5317  const su2double tnx = 2.0*normals[0], tny = 2.0*normals[1];
5318 
5319  /*--- Construct the gradients of the right solution. The tangential
5320  gradients of the normal momentum and normal gradients of the other
5321  variables, density, energy and tangential momentum, must be negated.
5322  For the common situation that the symmetry plane coincides with an
5323  x- or y-plane this boils down to a multiplication by -1 or +1,
5324  depending on the variable and gradient. However, the implementation
5325  below is valid for an arbitrary orientation of the symmetry plane. ---*/
5326  su2double URGradCart[4][2];
5327  URGradCart[0][0] = ULGradCart[0][0] - tnx*ULGradNorm[0];
5328  URGradCart[1][0] = ULGradCart[1][0] - tnx*ULGradNorm[1] - tnx*GradCartNormMomL[0] + tnx*tnx*GradNormNormMomL;
5329  URGradCart[2][0] = ULGradCart[2][0] - tnx*ULGradNorm[2] - tny*GradCartNormMomL[0] + tnx*tny*GradNormNormMomL;
5330  URGradCart[3][0] = ULGradCart[3][0] - tnx*ULGradNorm[3];
5331 
5332  URGradCart[0][1] = ULGradCart[0][1] - tny*ULGradNorm[0];
5333  URGradCart[1][1] = ULGradCart[1][1] - tny*ULGradNorm[1] - tnx*GradCartNormMomL[1] + tny*tnx*GradNormNormMomL;
5334  URGradCart[2][1] = ULGradCart[2][1] - tny*ULGradNorm[2] - tny*GradCartNormMomL[1] + tny*tny*GradNormNormMomL;
5335  URGradCart[3][1] = ULGradCart[3][1] - tny*ULGradNorm[3];
5336 
5337  /*--- Compute the viscous fluxes of the left and right state and average
5338  them to compute the correct viscous flux for a symmetry boundary. ---*/
5339  const su2double wallDist = wallDistance ? wallDistance[i] : 0.0;
5340  su2double viscFluxL[4], viscFluxR[4];
5341  su2double Viscosity, kOverCv;
5342 
5343  ViscousNormalFluxIntegrationPoint_2D(UR, URGradCart, normals, 0.0, 1.0,
5344  wallDist, lenScale_LES, Viscosity,
5345  kOverCv, viscFluxR);
5346  ViscousNormalFluxIntegrationPoint_2D(UL, ULGradCart, normals, 0.0, 1.0,
5347  wallDist, lenScale_LES, Viscosity,
5348  kOverCv, viscFluxL);
5349  viscosityInt[nInt*llRel+i] = Viscosity;
5350  kOverCvInt[nInt*llRel+i] = kOverCv;
5351 
5352  su2double *viscNormalFlux = viscFluxes + pointerOffset;
5353  viscNormalFlux[0] = 0.5*(viscFluxL[0] + viscFluxR[0]);
5354  viscNormalFlux[1] = 0.5*(viscFluxL[1] + viscFluxR[1]);
5355  viscNormalFlux[2] = 0.5*(viscFluxL[2] + viscFluxR[2]);
5356  viscNormalFlux[3] = 0.5*(viscFluxL[3] + viscFluxR[3]);
5357  }
5358 
5359  break;
5360  }
5361 
5362  /*--------------------------------------------------------------------*/
5363 
5364  case 3: {
5365 
5366  /*--- 3D simulation. Loop over the integration points to apply the
5367  symmetry condition and to compute the viscous normal fluxes. This
5368  is done in the same loop, because the gradients in the right
5369  integration points are constructed using the symmetry boundary
5370  condition. ---*/
5371  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
5372 
5373  /* Easier storage of the left and right solution and the normals
5374  for this integration point. */
5375  const unsigned short pointerOffset = NPad*i + llNVar;
5376  const su2double *UL = solIntL + pointerOffset;
5377  su2double *UR = solIntR + pointerOffset;
5378  const su2double *normals = surfElem[ll].metricNormalsFace.data() + i*(nDim+1);
5379 
5380  /* Compute twice the normal component of the momentum variables. The
5381  factor 2 comes from the fact that the velocity must be mirrored. */
5382  const su2double rVn = 2.0*(UL[1]*normals[0] + UL[2]*normals[1] + UL[3]*normals[2]);
5383 
5384  /* Set the right state. Note that the total energy of the right state is
5385  identical to the left state, because the magnitude of the velocity
5386  remains the same. */
5387  UR[0] = UL[0];
5388  UR[1] = UL[1] - rVn*normals[0];
5389  UR[2] = UL[2] - rVn*normals[1];
5390  UR[3] = UL[3] - rVn*normals[2];
5391  UR[4] = UL[4];
5392 
5393  /* Easier storage of the metric terms and left gradients of this
5394  integration point. */
5395  const su2double *metricTerms = surfElem[ll].metricCoorDerivFace.data()
5396  + i*nDim*nDim;
5397  const su2double *dULDr = gradSolInt + pointerOffset;
5398  const su2double *dULDs = dULDr + offDeriv;
5399  const su2double *dULDt = dULDs + offDeriv;
5400 
5401  /* Easier storage of the metric terms in this integration point. */
5402  const su2double drdx = metricTerms[0];
5403  const su2double drdy = metricTerms[1];
5404  const su2double drdz = metricTerms[2];
5405 
5406  const su2double dsdx = metricTerms[3];
5407  const su2double dsdy = metricTerms[4];
5408  const su2double dsdz = metricTerms[5];
5409 
5410  const su2double dtdx = metricTerms[6];
5411  const su2double dtdy = metricTerms[7];
5412  const su2double dtdz = metricTerms[8];
5413 
5414  /* Compute the Cartesian gradients of the left solution. */
5415  su2double ULGradCart[5][3];
5416  ULGradCart[0][0] = dULDr[0]*drdx + dULDs[0]*dsdx + dULDt[0]*dtdx;
5417  ULGradCart[1][0] = dULDr[1]*drdx + dULDs[1]*dsdx + dULDt[1]*dtdx;
5418  ULGradCart[2][0] = dULDr[2]*drdx + dULDs[2]*dsdx + dULDt[2]*dtdx;
5419  ULGradCart[3][0] = dULDr[3]*drdx + dULDs[3]*dsdx + dULDt[3]*dtdx;
5420  ULGradCart[4][0] = dULDr[4]*drdx + dULDs[4]*dsdx + dULDt[4]*dtdx;
5421 
5422  ULGradCart[0][1] = dULDr[0]*drdy + dULDs[0]*dsdy + dULDt[0]*dtdy;
5423  ULGradCart[1][1] = dULDr[1]*drdy + dULDs[1]*dsdy + dULDt[1]*dtdy;
5424  ULGradCart[2][1] = dULDr[2]*drdy + dULDs[2]*dsdy + dULDt[2]*dtdy;
5425  ULGradCart[3][1] = dULDr[3]*drdy + dULDs[3]*dsdy + dULDt[3]*dtdy;
5426  ULGradCart[4][1] = dULDr[4]*drdy + dULDs[4]*dsdy + dULDt[4]*dtdy;
5427 
5428  ULGradCart[0][2] = dULDr[0]*drdz + dULDs[0]*dsdz + dULDt[0]*dtdz;
5429  ULGradCart[1][2] = dULDr[1]*drdz + dULDs[1]*dsdz + dULDt[1]*dtdz;
5430  ULGradCart[2][2] = dULDr[2]*drdz + dULDs[2]*dsdz + dULDt[2]*dtdz;
5431  ULGradCart[3][2] = dULDr[3]*drdz + dULDs[3]*dsdz + dULDt[3]*dtdz;
5432  ULGradCart[4][2] = dULDr[4]*drdz + dULDs[4]*dsdz + dULDt[4]*dtdz;
5433 
5434  /* Determine the normal gradients of all variables. */
5435  su2double ULGradNorm[5];
5436  ULGradNorm[0] = ULGradCart[0][0]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[0][1]*normals[1] + ULGradCart[0][2]*normals[2];
5437  ULGradNorm[1] = ULGradCart[1][0]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[1][1]*normals[1] + ULGradCart[1][2]*normals[2];
5438  ULGradNorm[2] = ULGradCart[2][0]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[2][1]*normals[1] + ULGradCart[2][2]*normals[2];
5439  ULGradNorm[3] = ULGradCart[3][0]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[3][1]*normals[1] + ULGradCart[3][2]*normals[2];
5440  ULGradNorm[4] = ULGradCart[4][0]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[4][1]*normals[1] + ULGradCart[4][2]*normals[2];
5441 
5442  /* For the construction of the gradients of the right solution, also
5443  the Cartesian gradients and the normal gradient of the normal
5444  momentum is needed. This is computed below. */
5445  su2double GradCartNormMomL[3];
5446  GradCartNormMomL[0] = ULGradCart[1][0]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[2][0]*normals[1] + ULGradCart[3][0]*normals[2];
5447  GradCartNormMomL[1] = ULGradCart[1][1]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[2][1]*normals[1] + ULGradCart[3][1]*normals[2];
5448  GradCartNormMomL[2] = ULGradCart[1][2]*normals[0] + ULGradCart[2][2]*normals[1] + ULGradCart[3][2]*normals[2];
5449 
5450  const su2double GradNormNormMomL = ULGradNorm[1]*normals[0]
5451  + ULGradNorm[2]*normals[1]
5452  + ULGradNorm[3]*normals[2];
5453 
5454  /* Abbreviate twice the normal vector. */
5455  const su2double tnx = 2.0*normals[0], tny = 2.0*normals[1], tnz = 2.0*normals[2];
5456 
5457  /*--- Construct the gradients of the right solution. The tangential
5458  gradients of the normal momentum and normal gradients of the other
5459  variables, density, energy and tangential momentum, must be negated.
5460  For the common situation that the symmetry plane coincides with an
5461  x-, y- or z-plane this boils down to a multiplication by -1 or +1,
5462  depending on the variable and gradient. However, the implementation
5463  below is valid for an arbitrary orientation of the symmetry plane. ---*/
5464  su2double URGradCart[5][3];
5465  URGradCart[0][0] = ULGradCart[0][0] - tnx*ULGradNorm[0];
5466  URGradCart[1][0] = ULGradCart[1][0] - tnx*ULGradNorm[1] - tnx*GradCartNormMomL[0] + tnx*tnx*GradNormNormMomL;
5467  URGradCart[2][0] = ULGradCart[2][0] - tnx*ULGradNorm[2] - tny*GradCartNormMomL[0] + tnx*tny*GradNormNormMomL;
5468  URGradCart[3][0] = ULGradCart[3][0] - tnx*ULGradNorm[3] - tnz*GradCartNormMomL[0] + tnx*tnz*GradNormNormMomL;
5469  URGradCart[4][0] = ULGradCart[4][0] - tnx*ULGradNorm[4];
5470 
5471  URGradCart[0][1] = ULGradCart[0][1] - tny*ULGradNorm[0];
5472  URGradCart[1][1] = ULGradCart[1][1] - tny*ULGradNorm[1] - tnx*GradCartNormMomL[1] + tny*tnx*GradNormNormMomL;
5473  URGradCart[2][1] = ULGradCart[2][1] - tny*ULGradNorm[2] - tny*GradCartNormMomL[1] + tny*tny*GradNormNormMomL;
5474  URGradCart[3][1] = ULGradCart[3][1] - tny*ULGradNorm[3] - tnz*GradCartNormMomL[1] + tny*tnz*GradNormNormMomL;
5475  URGradCart[4][1] = ULGradCart[4][1] - tny*ULGradNorm[4];
5476 
5477  URGradCart[0][2] = ULGradCart[0][2] - tnz*ULGradNorm[0];
5478  URGradCart[1][2] = ULGradCart[1][2] - tnz*ULGradNorm[1] - tnx*GradCartNormMomL[2] + tnz*tnx*GradNormNormMomL;
5479  URGradCart[2][2] = ULGradCart[2][2] - tnz*ULGradNorm[2] - tny*GradCartNormMomL[2] + tnz*tny*GradNormNormMomL;
5480  URGradCart[3][2] = ULGradCart[3][2] - tnz*ULGradNorm[3] - tnz*GradCartNormMomL[2] + tnz*tnz*GradNormNormMomL;
5481  URGradCart[4][2] = ULGradCart[4][2] - tnz*ULGradNorm[4];
5482 
5483  /*--- Compute the viscous fluxes of the left and right state and average
5484  them to compute the correct viscous flux for a symmetry boundary. ---*/
5485  const su2double wallDist = wallDistance ? wallDistance[i] : 0.0;
5486  su2double viscFluxL[5], viscFluxR[5];
5487  su2double Viscosity, kOverCv;
5488 
5489  ViscousNormalFluxIntegrationPoint_3D(UR, URGradCart, normals, 0.0, 1.0,
5490  wallDist, lenScale_LES, Viscosity,
5491  kOverCv, viscFluxR);
5492  ViscousNormalFluxIntegrationPoint_3D(UL, ULGradCart, normals, 0.0, 1.0,
5493  wallDist, lenScale_LES, Viscosity,
5494  kOverCv, viscFluxL);
5495  viscosityInt[nInt*llRel+i] = Viscosity;
5496  kOverCvInt[nInt*llRel+i] = kOverCv;
5497 
5498  su2double *viscNormalFlux = viscFluxes + pointerOffset;
5499  viscNormalFlux[0] = 0.5*(viscFluxL[0] + viscFluxR[0]);
5500  viscNormalFlux[1] = 0.5*(viscFluxL[1] + viscFluxR[1]);
5501  viscNormalFlux[2] = 0.5*(viscFluxL[2] + viscFluxR[2]);
5502  viscNormalFlux[3] = 0.5*(viscFluxL[3] + viscFluxR[3]);
5503  viscNormalFlux[4] = 0.5*(viscFluxL[4] + viscFluxR[4]);
5504  }
5505 
5506  break;
5507  }
5508  }
5509  }
5510 
5511  /* The remainder of the boundary condition treatment is the same for all
5512  types of boundary conditions, including the symmetry plane. The function
5513  ResidualViscousBoundaryFace will carry out this task. */
5514  ResidualViscousBoundaryFace(config, conv_numerics, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l],
5515  solIntL, solIntR, gradSolInt, fluxes, viscFluxes,
5516  viscosityInt, kOverCvInt, resFaces, indResFaces);
5517 
5518  /* Update the value of the counter l to the end index of the
5519  current chunk. */
5520  l = lEnd;
5521  }
5522 }
5523 
5524 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::BC_Supersonic_Outlet(CConfig *config,
5525  const unsigned long surfElemBeg,
5526  const unsigned long surfElemEnd,
5527  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
5528  su2double *resFaces,
5529  CNumerics *conv_numerics,
5530  su2double *workArray){
5531 
5532  /* Initialization of the counter in resFaces. */
5533  unsigned long indResFaces = 0;
5534 
5535  /* Determine the number of faces that are treated simultaneously
5536  in the matrix products to obtain good gemm performance. */
5537  const unsigned short nPadInput = config->GetSizeMatMulPadding();
5538  const unsigned short nFaceSimul = nPadInput/nVar;
5539 
5540  /* Determine the minimum padded size in the matrix multiplications, which
5541  corresponds to 64 byte alignment. */
5542  const unsigned short nPadMin = 64/sizeof(passivedouble);
5543 
5544  /*--- Loop over the requested range of surface faces. Multiple faces
5545  are treated simultaneously to improve the performance of the matrix
5546  multiplications. As a consequence, the update of the counter l
5547  happens at the end of this loop section. ---*/
5548  for(unsigned long l=surfElemBeg; l<surfElemEnd;) {
5549 
5550  /* Determine the end index for this chunk of faces and the padded
5551  N value in the gemm computations. */
5552  unsigned long lEnd;
5553  unsigned short ind, llEnd, NPad;
5554 
5555  MetaDataChunkOfElem(surfElem, l, surfElemEnd, nFaceSimul,
5556  nPadMin, lEnd, ind, llEnd, NPad);
5557 
5558  /*--- Get the information from the standard element, which is the same
5559  for all the faces in the chunks considered. ---*/
5560  const unsigned short nInt = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
5561 
5562  /*--- Set the pointers for the local arrays. ---*/
5563  su2double *solIntL = workArray;
5564  su2double *solIntR = solIntL + NPad*nInt;
5565  su2double *work = solIntR + NPad*nInt;
5566 
5567  /* Compute the left states in the integration points of the chunk of
5568  faces. The array workarray is used as temporary storage inside the
5569  function LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace. */
5570  LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace(config, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l],
5571  work, solIntL);
5572 
5573  /* Set the right state in the integration points to the left state, i.e.
5574  no boundary condition is applied for a supersonic outlet. */
5575  for(unsigned short mm=0; mm<(NPad*nInt); ++mm)
5576  solIntR[mm] = solIntL[mm];
5577 
5578  /* The remainder of the boundary treatment is the same for all
5579  boundary conditions (except the symmetry plane). */
5580  ViscousBoundaryFacesBCTreatment(config, conv_numerics, llEnd, NPad,
5581  0.0, false, 0.0, false, &surfElem[l],
5582  solIntL, solIntR, work, resFaces,
5583  indResFaces, nullptr);
5584 
5585  /* Update the value of the counter l to the end index of the
5586  current chunk. */
5587  l = lEnd;
5588  }
5589 }

5591 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::BC_Inlet(CConfig *config,
5592  const unsigned long surfElemBeg,
5593  const unsigned long surfElemEnd,
5594  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
5595  su2double *resFaces,
5596  CNumerics *conv_numerics,
5597  unsigned short val_marker,
5598  su2double *workArray) {
5599 
5600  /* Initialization of the counter in resFaces. */
5601  unsigned long indResFaces = 0;
5602 
5603  /* Determine the number of faces that are treated simultaneously
5604  in the matrix products to obtain good gemm performance. */
5605  const unsigned short nPadInput = config->GetSizeMatMulPadding();
5606  const unsigned short nFaceSimul = nPadInput/nVar;
5607 
5608  /* Determine the minimum padded size in the matrix multiplications, which
5609  corresponds to 64 byte alignment. */
5610  const unsigned short nPadMin = 64/sizeof(passivedouble);
5611 
5612  /*--- Loop over the requested range of surface faces. Multiple faces
5613  are treated simultaneously to improve the performance of the matrix
5614  multiplications. As a consequence, the update of the counter l
5615  happens at the end of this loop section. ---*/
5616  for(unsigned long l=surfElemBeg; l<surfElemEnd;) {
5617 
5618  /* Determine the end index for this chunk of faces and the padded
5619  N value in the gemm computations. */
5620  unsigned long lEnd;
5621  unsigned short ind, llEnd, NPad;
5622 
5623  MetaDataChunkOfElem(surfElem, l, surfElemEnd, nFaceSimul,
5624  nPadMin, lEnd, ind, llEnd, NPad);
5625 
5626  /*--- Get the information from the standard element, which is the same
5627  for all the faces in the chunks considered. ---*/
5628  const unsigned short nInt = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
5629 
5630  /*--- Set the pointers for the local arrays. ---*/
5631  su2double *solIntL = workArray;
5632  su2double *solIntR = solIntL + NPad*nInt;
5633  su2double *work = solIntR + NPad*nInt;
5634 
5635  /* Compute the left states in the integration points of the chunk of
5636  faces. The array workarray is used as temporary storage inside the
5637  function LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace. */
5638  LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace(config, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l],
5639  work, solIntL);
5640 
5641  /* Compute the right state by applying the subsonic inlet BC's. */
5642  BoundaryStates_Inlet(config, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l], val_marker, solIntL, solIntR);
5643 
5644  /* The remainder of the boundary treatment is the same for all
5645  boundary conditions (except the symmetry plane). */
5646  ViscousBoundaryFacesBCTreatment(config, conv_numerics, llEnd, NPad,
5647  0.0, false, 0.0, false, &surfElem[l],
5648  solIntL, solIntR, work, resFaces,
5649  indResFaces, nullptr);
5650 
5651  /* Update the value of the counter l to the end index of the
5652  current chunk. */
5653  l = lEnd;
5654  }
5655 }
5656 
5657 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::BC_Outlet(CConfig *config,
5658  const unsigned long surfElemBeg,
5659  const unsigned long surfElemEnd,
5660  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
5661  su2double *resFaces,
5662  CNumerics *conv_numerics,
5663  unsigned short val_marker,
5664  su2double *workArray) {
5665 
5666  /* Initialization of the counter in resFaces. */
5667  unsigned long indResFaces = 0;
5668 
5669  /* Determine the number of faces that are treated simultaneously
5670  in the matrix products to obtain good gemm performance. */
5671  const unsigned short nPadInput = config->GetSizeMatMulPadding();
5672  const unsigned short nFaceSimul = nPadInput/nVar;
5673 
5674  /* Determine the minimum padded size in the matrix multiplications, which
5675  corresponds to 64 byte alignment. */
5676  const unsigned short nPadMin = 64/sizeof(passivedouble);
5677 
5678  /*--- Loop over the requested range of surface faces. Multiple faces
5679  are treated simultaneously to improve the performance of the matrix
5680  multiplications. As a consequence, the update of the counter l
5681  happens at the end of this loop section. ---*/
5682  for(unsigned long l=surfElemBeg; l<surfElemEnd;) {
5683 
5684  /* Determine the end index for this chunk of faces and the padded
5685  N value in the gemm computations. */
5686  unsigned long lEnd;
5687  unsigned short ind, llEnd, NPad;
5688 
5689  MetaDataChunkOfElem(surfElem, l, surfElemEnd, nFaceSimul,
5690  nPadMin, lEnd, ind, llEnd, NPad);
5691 
5692  /*--- Get the information from the standard element, which is the same
5693  for all the faces in the chunks considered. ---*/
5694  const unsigned short nInt = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
5695 
5696  /*--- Set the pointers for the local arrays. ---*/
5697  su2double *solIntL = workArray;
5698  su2double *solIntR = solIntL + NPad*nInt;
5699  su2double *work = solIntR + NPad*nInt;
5700 
5701  /* Compute the left states in the integration points of the chunk of
5702  faces. The array workarray is used as temporary storage inside the
5703  function LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace. */
5704  LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace(config, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l],
5705  work, solIntL);
5706 
5707  /* Compute the right state by applying the subsonic outlet BC's. */
5708  BoundaryStates_Outlet(config, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l], val_marker, solIntL, solIntR);
5709 
5710  /* The remainder of the boundary treatment is the same for all
5711  boundary conditions (except the symmetry plane). */
5712  ViscousBoundaryFacesBCTreatment(config, conv_numerics, llEnd, NPad,
5713  0.0, false, 0.0, false, &surfElem[l],
5714  solIntL, solIntR, work, resFaces,
5715  indResFaces, nullptr);
5716 
5717  /* Update the value of the counter l to the end index of the
5718  current chunk. */
5719  l = lEnd;
5720  }
5721 }
5722 
5723 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::BC_HeatFlux_Wall(CConfig *config,
5724  const unsigned long surfElemBeg,
5725  const unsigned long surfElemEnd,
5726  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
5727  su2double *resFaces,
5728  CNumerics *conv_numerics,
5729  unsigned short val_marker,
5730  su2double *workArray) {
5731 
5732  /* Set the factor for the wall velocity. For factWallVel = 0, the right state
5733  contains the wall velocity. For factWallVel = 1.0, the velocity of the
5734  right state is obtained by negating the interior velocity w.r.t. the
5735  velocity of the wall. */
5736  const su2double factWallVel = 0.0;
5737  // const su2double factWallVel = 1.0;
5738 
5739  /* Get the wall heat flux. */
5740  const string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(val_marker);
5741  const su2double Wall_HeatFlux = config->GetWall_HeatFlux(Marker_Tag);
5742 
5743  /* Initialization of the counter in resFaces. */
5744  unsigned long indResFaces = 0;
5745 
5746  /* Determine the number of faces that are treated simultaneously
5747  in the matrix products to obtain good gemm performance. */
5748  const unsigned short nPadInput = config->GetSizeMatMulPadding();
5749  const unsigned short nFaceSimul = nPadInput/nVar;
5750 
5751  /* Determine the minimum padded size in the matrix multiplications, which
5752  corresponds to 64 byte alignment. */
5753  const unsigned short nPadMin = 64/sizeof(passivedouble);
5754 
5755  /*--- Loop over the requested range of surface faces. Multiple faces
5756  are treated simultaneously to improve the performance of the matrix
5757  multiplications. As a consequence, the update of the counter l
5758  happens at the end of this loop section. ---*/
5759  for(unsigned long l=surfElemBeg; l<surfElemEnd;) {
5760 
5761  /* Determine the end index for this chunk of faces and the padded
5762  N value in the gemm computations. */
5763  unsigned long lEnd;
5764  unsigned short ind, llEnd, NPad;
5765 
5766  MetaDataChunkOfElem(surfElem, l, surfElemEnd, nFaceSimul,
5767  nPadMin, lEnd, ind, llEnd, NPad);
5768 
5769  /*--- Get the information from the standard element, which is the same
5770  for all the faces in the chunks considered. ---*/
5771  const unsigned short nInt = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
5772 
5773  /*--- Set the pointers for the local arrays. ---*/
5774  su2double *solIntL = workArray;
5775  su2double *solIntR = solIntL + NPad*nInt;
5776  su2double *work = solIntR + NPad*nInt;
5777 
5778  /* Compute the left states in the integration points of the chunk of
5779  faces. The array workarray is used as temporary storage inside the
5780  function LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace. */
5781  LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace(config, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l],
5782  work, solIntL);
5783 
5784  /*--- Compute the right states. A distinction must be made whether or not
5785  all functions are used. ---*/
5786  if( boundaries[val_marker].wallModel ) {
5787 
5788  /*--- Wall functions are used to model the lower part of the boundary
5789  layer. Consequently, a slip boundary condition is used for the
5790  velocities and the skin friction and heat flux from the wall
5791  should drive the velocities towards the no-slip and prescribed
5792  heat flux. Therefore the right states for the actual flow solver
5793  can be computed using BoundaryStates_Euler_Wall. ---*/
5794  BoundaryStates_Euler_Wall(config, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l],
5795  solIntL, solIntR);
5796  }
5797  else {
5798 
5799  /*--- Integration to the wall is used, so the no-slip condition is enforced,
5800  albeit weakly. Loop over the number of faces in this chunk and the
5801  number of integration points and apply the heat flux wall boundary
5802  conditions to compute the right state. There are two options. Either
5803  the velocity is negated or it is set to zero. Some experiments are
5804  needed to see which formulation gives better results. ---*/
5805  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
5806  const unsigned long lll = l + ll;
5807  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
5808 
5809  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
5810 
5811  /* Easier storage of the grid velocity and the left and right solution
5812  for this integration point. */
5813  const su2double *gridVel = surfElem[lll].gridVelocities.data() + i*nDim;
5814  const su2double *UL = solIntL + NPad*i + llNVar;
5815  su2double *UR = solIntR + NPad*i + llNVar;
5816 
5817  /* Set the right state. The initial value of the total energy is the
5818  energy of the left state. Also compute the difference in kinetic
5819  energy between the left and right state. */
5820  UR[0] = UL[0];
5821  UR[nDim+1] = UL[nDim+1];
5822 
5823  su2double DensityInv = 1.0/UL[0];
5824  su2double diffKin = 0.0;
5825  for(unsigned short iDim=0; iDim<nDim; ++iDim) {
5826  const su2double velL = DensityInv*UL[iDim+1];
5827  const su2double dV = factWallVel*(velL-gridVel[iDim]);
5828  const su2double velR = gridVel[iDim] - dV;
5829 
5830  UR[iDim+1] = UR[0]*velR;
5831  diffKin += velL*velL - velR*velR;
5832  }
5833 
5834  /* As only the internal energy of UR is equal to UL, the difference
5835  in kinetic energy must be subtracted. */
5836  UR[nDim+1] -= 0.5*UR[0]*diffKin;
5837  }
5838  }
5839  }
5840 
5841  /* The remainder of the boundary treatment is the same for all
5842  boundary conditions (except the symmetry plane). */
5843  ViscousBoundaryFacesBCTreatment(config, conv_numerics, llEnd, NPad,
5844  Wall_HeatFlux, true, 0.0, false,
5845  &surfElem[l], solIntL, solIntR,
5846  work, resFaces, indResFaces,
5847  boundaries[val_marker].wallModel);
5848 
5849  /* Update the value of the counter l to the end index of the
5850  current chunk. */
5851  l = lEnd;
5852  }
5853 }
5854 
5855 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::BC_Isothermal_Wall(CConfig *config,
5856  const unsigned long surfElemBeg,
5857  const unsigned long surfElemEnd,
5858  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
5859  su2double *resFaces,
5860  CNumerics *conv_numerics,
5861  unsigned short val_marker,
5862  su2double *workArray) {
5863 
5864  /* Set the factor for the wall velocity. For factWallVel = 0, the right state
5865  contains the wall velocity. For factWallVel = 1.0, the velocity of the
5866  right state is obtained by negating the interior velocity w.r.t. the
5867  velocity of the wall. */
5868  const su2double factWallVel = 0.0;
5869  // const su2double factWallVel = 1.0;
5870 
5871  /* Get the wall temperature. */
5872  const string Marker_Tag = config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(val_marker);
5873  const su2double TWall = config->GetIsothermal_Temperature(Marker_Tag)/config->GetTemperature_Ref();
5874 
5875  /* Compute the prescribed value of the energy (per unit mass). */
5876  const su2double Gas_Constant = config->GetGas_ConstantND();
5877  const su2double Cv = Gas_Constant/Gamma_Minus_One;
5878  const su2double StaticEnergy = Cv*TWall;
5879 
5880  /* Initialization of the counter in resFaces. */
5881  unsigned long indResFaces = 0;
5882 
5883  /* Determine the number of faces that are treated simultaneously
5884  in the matrix products to obtain good gemm performance. */
5885  const unsigned short nPadInput = config->GetSizeMatMulPadding();
5886  const unsigned short nFaceSimul = nPadInput/nVar;
5887 
5888  /* Determine the minimum padded size in the matrix multiplications, which
5889  corresponds to 64 byte alignment. */
5890  const unsigned short nPadMin = 64/sizeof(passivedouble);
5891 
5892  /*--- Loop over the requested range of surface faces. Multiple faces
5893  are treated simultaneously to improve the performance of the matrix
5894  multiplications. As a consequence, the update of the counter l
5895  happens at the end of this loop section. ---*/
5896  for(unsigned long l=surfElemBeg; l<surfElemEnd;) {
5897 
5898  /* Determine the end index for this chunk of faces and the padded
5899  N value in the gemm computations. */
5900  unsigned long lEnd;
5901  unsigned short ind, llEnd, NPad;
5902 
5903  MetaDataChunkOfElem(surfElem, l, surfElemEnd, nFaceSimul,
5904  nPadMin, lEnd, ind, llEnd, NPad);
5905 
5906  /*--- Get the information from the standard element, which is the same
5907  for all the faces in the chunks considered. ---*/
5908  const unsigned short nInt = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
5909 
5910  /*--- Set the pointers for the local arrays. ---*/
5911  su2double *solIntL = workArray;
5912  su2double *solIntR = solIntL + NPad*nInt;
5913  su2double *work = solIntR + NPad*nInt;
5914 
5915  /* Compute the left states in the integration points of the chunk of
5916  faces. The array workarray is used as temporary storage inside the
5917  function LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace. */
5918  LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace(config, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l],
5919  work, solIntL);
5920 
5921  /*--- Integration to the wall is used, so the no-slip condition is enforced,
5922  albeit weakly. Loop over the number of faces in this chunk and the
5923  number of integration points and apply the isothermal wall boundary
5924  conditions to compute the right state. There are two options. Either
5925  the velocity is negated or it is set to zero. Some experiments are
5926  needed to see which formulation gives better results. ---*/
5927  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
5928  const unsigned long lll = l + ll;
5929  const unsigned short llNVar = ll*nVar;
5930 
5931  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
5932 
5933  /* Easier storage of the grid velocity and the left and right solution
5934  for this integration point. */
5935  const su2double *gridVel = surfElem[lll].gridVelocities.data() + i*nDim;
5936  const su2double *UL = solIntL + NPad*i + llNVar;
5937  su2double *UR = solIntR + NPad*i + llNVar;
5938 
5939  /* Set the right state for the density and the momentum variables of the
5940  right state. Compute twice the possible kinetic energy. */
5941  UR[0] = UL[0];
5942  su2double DensityInv = 1.0/UL[0];
5943  su2double kinEner = 0.0;
5944  for(unsigned short iDim=0; iDim<nDim; ++iDim) {
5945  const su2double velL = DensityInv*UL[iDim+1];
5946  const su2double dV = factWallVel*(velL-gridVel[iDim]);
5947  const su2double velR = gridVel[iDim] - dV;
5948 
5949  UR[iDim+1] = UR[0]*velR;
5950  kinEner += velR*velR;
5951  }
5952 
5953  /* Compute the total energy of the right state. */
5954  UR[nDim+1] = UR[0]*(StaticEnergy + 0.5*kinEner);
5955  }
5956  }
5957 
5958  /* The remainder of the boundary treatment is the same for all
5959  boundary conditions (except the symmetry plane). */
5960  ViscousBoundaryFacesBCTreatment(config, conv_numerics, llEnd, NPad,
5961  0.0, false, TWall, true,
5962  &surfElem[l], solIntL, solIntR,
5963  work, resFaces, indResFaces,
5964  boundaries[val_marker].wallModel);
5965 
5966  /* Update the value of the counter l to the end index of the
5967  current chunk. */
5968  l = lEnd;
5969  }
5970 }

6038 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::BC_Custom(CConfig *config,
6039  const unsigned long surfElemBeg,
6040  const unsigned long surfElemEnd,
6041  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
6042  su2double *resFaces,
6043  CNumerics *conv_numerics,
6044  su2double *workArray) {
6045 
6046  /* Initialization of the counter in resFaces. */
6047  unsigned long indResFaces = 0;
6048 
6049  /* Determine the number of faces that are treated simultaneously
6050  in the matrix products to obtain good gemm performance. */
6051  const unsigned short nPadInput = config->GetSizeMatMulPadding();
6052  const unsigned short nFaceSimul = nPadInput/nVar;
6053 
6054  /* Determine the minimum padded size in the matrix multiplications, which
6055  corresponds to 64 byte alignment. */
6056  const unsigned short nPadMin = 64/sizeof(passivedouble);
6057 
6058  /*--- Get the physical time if necessary. ---*/
6059  su2double time = 0.0;
6060  if (config->GetTime_Marching() != TIME_MARCHING::STEADY) time = config->GetPhysicalTime();
6061 
6062  /*--- Loop over the requested range of surface faces. Multiple faces
6063  are treated simultaneously to improve the performance of the matrix
6064  multiplications. As a consequence, the update of the counter l
6065  happens at the end of this loop section. ---*/
6066  for(unsigned long l=surfElemBeg; l<surfElemEnd;) {
6067 
6068  /* Determine the end index for this chunk of faces and the padded
6069  N value in the gemm computations. */
6070  unsigned long lEnd;
6071  unsigned short ind, llEnd, NPad;
6072 
6073  MetaDataChunkOfElem(surfElem, l, surfElemEnd, nFaceSimul,
6074  nPadMin, lEnd, ind, llEnd, NPad);
6075 
6076  /*--- Get the information from the standard element, which is the same
6077  for all the faces in the chunks considered. ---*/
6078  const unsigned short nInt = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
6079 
6080  /*--- Set the pointers for the local arrays. ---*/
6081  su2double *solIntL = workArray;
6082  su2double *solIntR = solIntL + NPad*nInt;
6083  su2double *work = solIntR + NPad*nInt;
6084 
6085  /* Compute the left states in the integration points of the chunk of
6086  faces. The array workarray is used as temporary storage inside the
6087  function LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace. */
6088  LeftStatesIntegrationPointsBoundaryFace(config, llEnd, NPad, &surfElem[l],
6089  work, solIntL);
6090 
6091  /* Check for a verification solution. */
6092  if( VerificationSolution ) {
6093 
6094  /*--- Loop over the number of simultaneously treated faces and integration points
6095  to compute the right state for the boundary conditions. ---*/
6096  for(unsigned short ll=0; ll<llEnd; ++ll) {
6097  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
6098 
6099  /* Determine the pointer to the coordinates of this integration
6100  point and the pointer to the solution and call the function
6101  GetBCState to determine the actual boundary state. */
6102  const su2double *coor = surfElem[ll+l].coorIntegrationPoints.data() + i*nDim;
6103  su2double *UR = solIntR + NPad*i + ll*nVar;
6104 
6105  VerificationSolution->GetBCState(coor, time, UR);
6106  }
6107  }
6108  }
6109  else {
6110 
6111  /* The user must specify the custom BC's here. */
6112  SU2_MPI::Error("Implement customized boundary conditions here.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
6113  }
6114 
6115 
6116  /* The remainder of the boundary treatment is the same for all
6117  boundary conditions (except the symmetry plane). */
6118  ViscousBoundaryFacesBCTreatment(config, conv_numerics, llEnd, NPad,
6119  0.0, false, 0.0, false, &surfElem[l],
6120  solIntL, solIntR, work,
6121  resFaces, indResFaces, nullptr);
6122 
6123  /* Update the value of the counter l to the end index of the
6124  current chunk. */
6125  l = lEnd;
6126  }
6127 }
6128 
6129 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::ViscousBoundaryFacesBCTreatment(
6130  CConfig *config,
6131  CNumerics *conv_numerics,
6132  const unsigned short nFaceSimul,
6133  const unsigned short NPad,
6134  const su2double Wall_HeatFlux,
6135  const bool HeatFlux_Prescribed,
6136  const su2double Wall_Temperature,
6137  const bool Temperature_Prescribed,
6138  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
6139  const su2double *solIntL,
6140  const su2double *solIntR,
6141  su2double *workArray,
6142  su2double *resFaces,
6143  unsigned long &indResFaces,
6144  CWallModel *wallModel) {
6145 
6146  /*--- Get the information from the standard element, which is the same
6147  for all the faces in the chunks considered. ---*/
6148  const unsigned short ind = surfElem[0].indStandardElement;
6149  const unsigned short nInt = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
6150  const unsigned short nDOFsElem = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNDOFsElem();
6151  const su2double *derBasisElem = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetMatDerBasisElemIntegration();
6152 
6153  /*--- Set the pointers for the local arrays. ---*/
6154  su2double *viscosityInt = workArray;
6155  su2double *kOverCvInt = viscosityInt + nFaceSimul*nInt;
6156  su2double *gradSolInt = kOverCvInt + nFaceSimul*nInt;
6157  su2double *fluxes = gradSolInt + NPad*nInt*nDim;
6158  su2double *viscFluxes = fluxes + NPad*max(nInt*nDim, (int) nDOFsElem);
6159 
6160  /* Compute the viscous fluxes in the integration points of the faces that
6161  are treated simulaneously. Make a distinction between a wall function
6162  treatment and a standard computation of the viscous fluxes. */
6163  if( wallModel ) {
6164  WallTreatmentViscousFluxes(config, nFaceSimul, NPad, nInt, Wall_HeatFlux,
6165  HeatFlux_Prescribed, Wall_Temperature,
6166  Temperature_Prescribed, surfElem, solIntL,
6167  gradSolInt, viscFluxes, viscosityInt,
6168  kOverCvInt, wallModel);
6169  }
6170  else {
6171  ComputeViscousFluxesBoundaryFaces(config, nFaceSimul, NPad, nInt, nDOFsElem,
6172  Wall_HeatFlux, HeatFlux_Prescribed,
6173  derBasisElem, surfElem, solIntL,
6174  fluxes, gradSolInt, viscFluxes,
6175  viscosityInt, kOverCvInt);
6176  }
6177 
6178  /* The remainder of the boundary condition treatment is the same for all
6179  types of boundary conditions, including the symmetry plane and the
6180  wall function treatment. The function ResidualViscousBoundaryFace will
6181  carry out this task. */
6182 
6183  ResidualViscousBoundaryFace(config, conv_numerics, nFaceSimul, NPad, surfElem,
6184  solIntL, solIntR, gradSolInt, fluxes, viscFluxes,
6185  viscosityInt, kOverCvInt, resFaces, indResFaces);
6186 }
6187 
6188 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::ComputeViscousFluxesBoundaryFaces(
6189  CConfig *config,
6190  const unsigned short nFaceSimul,
6191  const unsigned short NPad,
6192  const unsigned short nInt,
6193  const unsigned short nDOFsElem,
6194  const su2double Wall_HeatFlux,
6195  const bool HeatFlux_Prescribed,
6196  const su2double *derBasisElem,
6197  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
6198  const su2double *solIntL,
6199  su2double *solElem,
6200  su2double *gradSolInt,
6201  su2double *viscFluxes,
6202  su2double *viscosityInt,
6203  su2double *kOverCvInt) {
6204 
6205  /*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
6206  /*--- Step 1: Compute the gradients of the conservative variables in the ---*/
6207  /*--- integration points of the faces. ---*/
6208  /*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
6209 
6210  /* Loop over the simultaneously treated faces to set the solution of the elements. */
6211  for(unsigned short l=0; l<nFaceSimul; ++l) {
6212  const unsigned short llNVar = l*nVar;
6213 
6214  /* Determine the offset that must be applied to access the correct data for
6215  this element in the working vector of the solution. Per definition the
6216  boundary face has the same time level as the adjacent element, hence
6217  offsetDOFsSolThisTimeLevel is used. */
6218  const unsigned long elemID = surfElem[l].volElemID;
6219  const unsigned short timeLevel = volElem[elemID].timeLevel;
6220  const unsigned long offset = volElem[elemID].offsetDOFsSolLocal
6221  - volElem[elemID].offsetDOFsSolThisTimeLevel;
6222 
6223  /* Loop over the DOFs of the element and copy the solution to the appropriate
6224  position in solElem. */
6225  const unsigned long *DOFsElem = surfElem[l].DOFsSolElement.data();
6226  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFsElem; ++i) {
6227  const su2double *solDOF = VecWorkSolDOFs[timeLevel].data()
6228  + nVar*(DOFsElem[i] - offset);
6229  su2double *sol = solElem + NPad*i + llNVar;
6230  for(unsigned short mm=0; mm<nVar; ++mm)
6231  sol[mm] = solDOF[mm];
6232  }
6233  }
6234 
6235  /* Compute the gradients in the integration points. Call the general function to
6236  carry out the matrix product. */
6237  blasFunctions->gemm(nInt*nDim, NPad, nDOFsElem, derBasisElem, solElem, gradSolInt, config);
6238 
6239  /*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
6240  /*--- Step 2: Compute the viscous normal fluxes in the integration points ---*/
6241  /*--- of the faces. ---*/
6242  /*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
6243 
6244  /* Loop over the simultaneously treated faces. */
6245  for(unsigned short l=0; l<nFaceSimul; ++l) {
6246 
6247  /* Determine the ID of the adjacent element. */
6248  const unsigned long elemID = surfElem[l].volElemID;
6249 
6250  /* Call the general function to compute the viscous flux in normal
6251  direction for the face. */
6252  ViscousNormalFluxFace(&volElem[elemID], l, nInt, NPad, Wall_HeatFlux,
6253  HeatFlux_Prescribed, solIntL, gradSolInt,
6254  surfElem[l].metricCoorDerivFace.data(),
6255  surfElem[l].metricNormalsFace.data(),
6256  surfElem[l].wallDistance.data(),
6257  viscFluxes, viscosityInt, kOverCvInt);
6258  }
6259 }
6260 
6261 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::WallTreatmentViscousFluxes(
6262  CConfig *config,
6263  const unsigned short nFaceSimul,
6264  const unsigned short NPad,
6265  const unsigned short nInt,
6266  const su2double Wall_HeatFlux,
6267  const bool HeatFlux_Prescribed,
6268  const su2double Wall_Temperature,
6269  const bool Temperature_Prescribed,
6270  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
6271  const su2double *solIntL,
6272  su2double *workArray,
6273  su2double *viscFluxes,
6274  su2double *viscosityInt,
6275  su2double *kOverCvInt,
6276  CWallModel *wallModel) {
6277 
6278  /* Loop over the simultaneously treated faces. */
6279  for(unsigned short l=0; l<nFaceSimul; ++l) {
6280  const unsigned short llNVar = l*nVar;
6281 
6282  /* Loop over the donors for this boundary face. */
6283  for(unsigned long j=0; j<surfElem[l].donorsWallFunction.size(); ++j) {
6284 
6285  /* Easier storage of the element ID of the donor and set the pointer
6286  where the solution of this element starts. Note that by construction
6287  the time level of the donor element is the same as the time level
6288  of the boundary face. */
6289  const unsigned long donorID = surfElem[l].donorsWallFunction[j];
6290  const unsigned short timeLevel = volElem[donorID].timeLevel;
6291  const unsigned short nDOFsElem = volElem[donorID].nDOFsSol;
6292  const su2double *solDOFsElem = VecWorkSolDOFs[timeLevel].data()
6293  + nVar*volElem[donorID].offsetDOFsSolThisTimeLevel;
6294 
6295  /* Determine the number of integration points for this donor and
6296  interpolate the solution for the corresponding exchange points. */
6297  const unsigned short nIntThisDonor = surfElem[l].nIntPerWallFunctionDonor[j+1]
6298  - surfElem[l].nIntPerWallFunctionDonor[j];
6299 
6300  blasFunctions->gemm(nIntThisDonor, nVar, nDOFsElem, surfElem[l].matWallFunctionDonor[j].data(),
6301  solDOFsElem, workArray, config);
6302 
6303  /* Loop over the integration points for this donor element. */
6304  for(unsigned short i=surfElem[l].nIntPerWallFunctionDonor[j];
6305  i<surfElem[l].nIntPerWallFunctionDonor[j+1]; ++i) {
6306 
6307  /* Easier storage of the actual integration point. */
6308  const unsigned short ii = surfElem[l].intPerWallFunctionDonor[i];
6309 
6310  /* Determine the normal and the wall velocity for this integration point. */
6311  const su2double *normals = surfElem[l].metricNormalsFace.data() + ii*(nDim+1);
6312  const su2double *gridVel = surfElem[l].gridVelocities.data() + ii*nDim;
6313 
6314  /* Determine the velocities and pressure in the exchange point. */
6315  const su2double *solInt = workArray
6316  + nVar*(i-surfElem[l].nIntPerWallFunctionDonor[j]);
6317 
6318  su2double rhoInv = 1.0/solInt[0];
6319  su2double vel[] = {0.0, 0.0, 0.0};
6320  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k) vel[k] = rhoInv*solInt[k+1];
6321 
6322  su2double vel2Mag = vel[0]*vel[0] + vel[1]*vel[1] + vel[2]*vel[2];
6323  su2double eInt = rhoInv*solInt[nVar-1] - 0.5*vel2Mag;
6324 
6325  FluidModel->SetTDState_rhoe(solInt[0], eInt);
6326  const su2double Pressure = FluidModel->GetPressure();
6327  const su2double Temperature = FluidModel->GetTemperature();
6328  const su2double LaminarViscosity= FluidModel->GetLaminarViscosity();
6329 
6330  /* Subtract the prescribed wall velocity, i.e. grid velocity
6331  from the velocity in the exchange point. */
6332  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k) vel[k] -= gridVel[k];
6333 
6334  /* Determine the tangential velocity by subtracting the normal
6335  velocity component. */
6336  su2double velNorm = 0.0;
6337  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k) velNorm += normals[k]*vel[k];
6338  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k) vel[k] -= normals[k]*velNorm;
6339 
6340  /* Determine the magnitude of the tangential velocity as well
6341  as its direction (unit vector). */
6342  su2double velTan = sqrt(vel[0]*vel[0] + vel[1]*vel[1] + vel[2]*vel[2]);
6343  velTan = max(velTan,1.e-25);
6344 
6345  su2double dirTan[] = {0.0, 0.0, 0.0};
6346  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k) dirTan[k] = vel[k]/velTan;
6347 
6348  /* Compute the wall shear stress and heat flux vector using
6349  the wall model. */
6350  su2double tauWall, qWall, ViscosityWall, kOverCvWall;
6351 
6352  wallModel->WallShearStressAndHeatFlux(Temperature, velTan, LaminarViscosity, Pressure,
6353  Wall_HeatFlux, HeatFlux_Prescribed,
6354  Wall_Temperature, Temperature_Prescribed,
6355  FluidModel, tauWall, qWall, ViscosityWall,
6356  kOverCvWall);
6357 
6358  /* Compute the wall velocity in tangential direction. */
6359  const su2double *solWallInt = solIntL + NPad*ii + llNVar;
6360  su2double velWallTan = 0.0;
6361  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k)
6362  velWallTan += solWallInt[k+1]*dirTan[k];
6363  velWallTan /= solWallInt[0];
6364 
6365  /* Determine the position where the viscous fluxes, viscosity and
6366  thermal conductivity must be stored. */
6367  su2double *normalFlux = viscFluxes + NPad*ii + llNVar;
6368 
6369  const unsigned short ind = l*nInt + ii;
6370  viscosityInt[ind] = ViscosityWall;
6371  kOverCvInt[ind] = kOverCvWall;
6372 
6373  /* Compute the viscous normal flux. Note that the unscaled normals
6374  must be used, hence the multiplication with normals[nDim]. */
6375  normalFlux[0] = 0.0;
6376  for(unsigned short k=0; k<nDim; ++k)
6377  normalFlux[k+1] = -normals[nDim]*tauWall*dirTan[k];
6378  normalFlux[nVar-1] = normals[nDim]*(qWall - tauWall*velWallTan);
6379  }
6380  }
6381  }
6382 }
6383 
6384 void CFEM_DG_NSSolver::ResidualViscousBoundaryFace(
6385  CConfig *config,
6386  CNumerics *conv_numerics,
6387  const unsigned short nFaceSimul,
6388  const unsigned short NPad,
6389  const CSurfaceElementFEM *surfElem,
6390  const su2double *solInt0,
6391  const su2double *solInt1,
6392  su2double *paramFluxes,
6393  su2double *fluxes,
6394  su2double *viscFluxes,
6395  const su2double *viscosityInt,
6396  const su2double *kOverCvInt,
6397  su2double *resFaces,
6398  unsigned long &indResFaces) {
6399 
6400  /*--- Get the required information from the standard element, which is the
6401  same for all faces considered. ---*/
6402  const unsigned short ind = surfElem[0].indStandardElement;
6403  const unsigned short nInt = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNIntegration();
6404  const unsigned short nDOFs = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNDOFsFace();
6405  const unsigned short nDOFsElem = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetNDOFsElem();
6406  const su2double ConstPenFace = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetPenaltyConstant();
6407  const su2double *weights = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetWeightsIntegration();
6408 
6409  /*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
6410  /*--- Step 1: Compute the sum of the inviscid, viscous and penalty ---*/
6411  /*--- fluxes in the integration points of the faces. ---*/
6412  /*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
6413 
6414  /* Store the normals and grid velocities of the faces in an array of
6415  pointers to be used in the call to ComputeInviscidFluxesFace. */
6416  const su2double* arrNorm[SIZE_ARR_NORM];
6417  const su2double* arrGridVel[SIZE_ARR_NORM];
6418 
6419  if(nFaceSimul > SIZE_ARR_NORM)
6420  SU2_MPI::Error("SIZE_ARR_NORM is too small. Increase it or decrease ALIGNED_BYTES_MATMUL",
6421  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
6422 
6423  for(unsigned short l=0; l<nFaceSimul; ++l) {
6424  arrNorm[l] = surfElem[l].metricNormalsFace.data();
6425  arrGridVel[l] = surfElem[l].gridVelocities.data();
6426  }
6427 
6428  /* General function to compute the inviscid fluxes, using an approximate
6429  Riemann solver in the integration points. */
6430  ComputeInviscidFluxesFace(config, nFaceSimul, NPad, nInt, arrNorm, arrGridVel,
6431  solInt0, solInt1, fluxes, conv_numerics);
6432 
6433  /* Subtract the viscous fluxes from the inviscid fluxes. */
6434  for(unsigned short j=0; j<(NPad*nInt); ++j) fluxes[j] -= viscFluxes[j];
6435 
6436  /*--- Loop over the faces in this chunk to compute the penalty fluxes. ---*/
6437  for(unsigned short l=0; l<nFaceSimul; ++l) {
6438 
6439  /* Get the length scale for the adjacent element. */
6440  const su2double lenScale = volElem[surfElem[l].volElemID].lenScale;
6441 
6442  /* Call the function PenaltyTermsFluxFace to compute the actual penalty
6443  terms. Use the array viscFluxes as storage. */
6444  PenaltyTermsFluxFace(l, nInt, NPad, solInt0, solInt1, viscosityInt,
6445  viscosityInt, kOverCvInt, kOverCvInt, ConstPenFace,
6446  lenScale, lenScale, surfElem[l].metricNormalsFace.data(),
6447  viscFluxes);
6448  }
6449 
6450  /* Add the penalty fluxes to the earlier computed fluxes. */
6451  for(unsigned short j=0; j<(NPad*nInt); ++j) fluxes[j] += viscFluxes[j];
6452 
6453  /* Multiply the fluxes with the integration weight of the corresponding
6454  integration point. */
6455  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nInt; ++i) {
6456  su2double *flux = fluxes + i*NPad;
6457 
6458  for(unsigned short j=0; j<NPad; ++j)
6459  flux[j] *= weights[i];
6460  }
6461 
6462  /*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
6463  /*--- Step 2: Compute the contribution to the residuals from the ---*/
6464  /*--- integration over the surface element of the invisid ---*/
6465  /*--- fluxes, viscous fluxes and penalty terms. ---*/
6466  /*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
6467 
6468  /* Set the value of the offset of the residual between each of the
6469  faces. This depends whether or not symmetrizing terms are stored.
6470  Also set the location where the symmetrizing terms of the first face
6471  must be stored. */
6472  unsigned long offsetRes = nDOFs;
6473  if( symmetrizingTermsPresent ) offsetRes += nDOFsElem;
6474 
6475  unsigned long indResSym = indResFaces + nDOFs;
6476 
6477  /* Get the correct form of the basis functions needed for the matrix
6478  multiplication to compute the residual. */
6479  const su2double *basisFaceTrans = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetBasisFaceIntegrationTranspose();
6480 
6481  /* Call the general function to carry out the matrix product. Use viscFluxes
6482  as temporary storage for the result. */
6483  blasFunctions->gemm(nDOFs, NPad, nInt, basisFaceTrans, fluxes, viscFluxes, config);
6484 
6485  /* Loop over the number of faces in this chunk to store the residual in
6486  the correct locations in resFaces. */
6487  for(unsigned short l=0; l<nFaceSimul; ++l) {
6488  const unsigned short llNVar = l*nVar;
6489 
6490  /* Easier storage of the position in the residual array for this face
6491  and update the corresponding counter. */
6492  su2double *resFace = resFaces + indResFaces*nVar;
6493  indResFaces += offsetRes;
6494 
6495  /* Loop over the DOFs and copy the data. */
6496  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFs; ++i)
6497  for(unsigned short mm=0; mm<nVar; ++mm)
6498  resFace[nVar*i+mm] = viscFluxes[NPad*i+llNVar+mm];
6499  }
6500 
6501  /*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
6502  /*--- Step 3: Compute and distribute the symmetrizing terms, if ---*/
6503  /*--- present. Note that these terms must be distributed to ---*/
6504  /*--- DOFs of the adjacent element, not only of the face. ---*/
6505  /*------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
6506 
6507  if( symmetrizingTermsPresent ) {
6508 
6509  /* The symmetrizing fluxes will be multiplied by 0.5 times the theta
6510  parameter. Store this factor a bit easier. */
6511  const su2double halfTheta = 0.5*config->GetTheta_Interior_Penalty_DGFEM();
6512 
6513  /* Loop over the simultaneously treated faces. */
6514  for(unsigned short l=0; l<nFaceSimul; ++l) {
6515 
6516  /* Compute the symmetrizing fluxes in the nDim directions. */
6517  SymmetrizingFluxesFace(l, nInt, NPad, solInt0, solInt1, viscosityInt,
6518  viscosityInt, kOverCvInt, kOverCvInt,
6519  surfElem[l].metricNormalsFace.data(), fluxes);
6520 
6521  /* Transform the fluxes, such that they must be multiplied with the
6522  gradients w.r.t. the parametric coordinates rather than the
6523  Cartesian coordinates of the basis functions. Also a multiplication
6524  with the integration weight and the theta parameter is carried out. */
6525  TransformSymmetrizingFluxes(l, nInt, NPad, halfTheta, fluxes, weights,
6526  surfElem[l].metricCoorDerivFace.data(),
6527  paramFluxes);
6528  }
6529 
6530  /* Call the general function to carry out the matrix product to compute
6531  the residual. Use fluxes as temporary storage for the result. */
6532  const su2double *derBasisElemTrans = standardBoundaryFacesSol[ind].GetMatDerBasisElemIntegrationTranspose();
6533 
6534  blasFunctions->gemm(nDOFsElem, NPad, nInt*nDim, derBasisElemTrans, paramFluxes, fluxes, config);
6535 
6536  /* Loop over the faces of this chunk to store the residual in
6537  the correct locations in resFaces. */
6538  for(unsigned short l=0; l<nFaceSimul; ++l) {
6539  const unsigned short llNVar = l*nVar;
6540 
6541  /* Easier storage of the position in the residual array for this face
6542  and update the corresponding counter. */
6543  su2double *resElem = resFaces + indResSym*nVar;
6544  indResSym += offsetRes;
6545 
6546  /* Loop over the DOFs of the element and copy the data. */
6547  for(unsigned short i=0; i<nDOFsElem; ++i)
6548  for(unsigned short mm=0; mm<nVar; ++mm)
6549  resElem[nVar*i+mm] = fluxes[NPad*i+llNVar+mm];
6550  }
6551  }
6552 }
